title: marshmallow crunchies
directions: Butter a 13 x 9-inch pan.
In a 3-quart pan, melt margarine and marshmallows over low heat.
Stir until melted.
Remove from heat.
Add Rice Krispies and coat real well.
Press into 13 x 9-inch buttered pan.
Cool and cut into squares.

title: egg custard pie
directions: Mix sugar and eggs.
Add a dash of salt and vanilla.
Scald milk and add to egg mixture slowly.
Pour in pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until crust is golden brown.

title: beef burgundy
directions: Cut steak into 1-inch cubes.
Dip in flour.
Brown in hot fat. Add remaining ingredients and cook slowly for 1 hour.

title: fruit slaw
directions: Drain pineapple chunks, reserving 2 tablespoons juice.
Set juice aside.
In a large salad bowl, combine pineapple, cabbage, apple, carrot and green pepper.

title: corn dog bites
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Lightly coat cookie sheet with nonstick spray.
Separate dough into 16 pieces.
Cut each one in half to make 32 pieces.
Roll each into a ball and flatten with hand into a small circle, about 1/4-inch thick.
Put a piece of hot dog into a circle, closing dough around hot dog and seal seams.
Place on baking sheet and bake for 10 to 13 minutes or until golden.

title: chocolate cheesecake
directions: In medium bowl, combine crumbs almonds, sugar and butter; mix well.
Press firmly into bottom and pinch up sides of 9-inch spring-form pan.

title: cauliflower casserole
directions: Grease casserole dish with margarine.
Add a layer of frozen cauliflower.
Add 2 layers of Velveeta cheese.
Mix and heat. Pour over casserole. Cover and bake at 325° for 1 hour.
Uncover and bake 15 to 20 minutes longer.

title: taco casserole
directions: Brown meat.
Drain off excess fat.
Add taco sauce and chilies. Simmer for 10 minutes.
Add soups and heat well.
Pour over chips in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Top with cheese.
Bake 25 minutes at 350°. Garnish with additional chips.

title: 1-2-3 stew
directions: Brown meat in skillet until very dark brown.
Cover with soups and 1 1/2 cups water.
Cook over very low heat for 30 minutes to 1 hour.
Serve over cooked rice or mashed potatoes.
This is very good served with garlic bread and salad.

title: chicken con queso
directions: Combine soup, 1 cup Cheddar cheese, milk, chilies and onions in bowl.
Stir to blend.
Place 1/3 cup chips in bottom of 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Top with 1/2 of chicken, then 1/2 soup mixture.
Repeat layers.
Sprinkle remaining cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Garnish, if desired, with tomatoes, peppers or olives.

title: strawberry shortcake
directions: First bake cake and let cool. Beat cornstarch, sugar, milk, and egg while cooking on medium heat. This should take about 15 to 20 minutes for the pudding to thicken. Once pudding is thick, set off burner and add vanilla. Let cool.

title: microwave fudge
directions: Mix well in 3 to 3 1/2-quart bowl.
Microwave on High 10 to 14 minutes.
Test drop in water.

title: crunchy ice cream pie
directions: Stir together butter (softened) and sugar.
Mix corn flakes, nuts and coconut.
Put half mixture in pan.
Spread ice cream on top.
Sprinkle rest of mixture on top.
Top with hot fudge.
Makes 9 x 13-inch or 2 pie pans.

title: crock-pot ribs
directions: Season ribs and broil for 10 minutes to remove excess fat. Place ribs in crock-pot and cover with sauce.
Pour water over top.
Place onion slices on top.
Cook on low setting for 8 to 10 hours.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: Combine sour cream with dressing mix.
Add diced chicken, 1 cup of the Cheddar cheese and olives.
Spoon onto uncooked tortillas. Spread mixture on each and roll up.
Place seam side down in 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle with remaining cup of cheese.
Bake in 375° oven for 25 minutes.
Remove from oven and top with salsa. Serve immediately.

title: the best "no bake" cookie recipe you'll ever have
directions: Bring sugar, cocoa, shortening and milk to boil; boil for 2 minutes.
In a bowl, mix oatmeal and coconut or pecans.
Mix all ingredients and drop on wax paper.

title: ann lynn's rice casserole
directions: Melt margarine in ovenproof casserole (2 to 3-quart Pyrex or Corning Ware square).
Saute onions until translucent.
Stir in rice and almonds.
Pour in consomme and broth.
Bake, covered, at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes, until liquid is absorbed.

title: squash puppies
directions: Combine all ingredients in mixing bowl and beat. Drop from tsp. into hot deep oil. Brown on both sides on medium heat. Drain on paper towel. Serve while warm.

title: pretzel salad
directions: Mix crushed pretzels, oleo and 3 tablespoons white sugar. Press into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 15 minutes at 350°.
Cool.

title: chicken-broccoli casserole
directions: In a 9 x 13-inch baking dish, crush Ritz crackers.
Cook and drain broccoli spears.
Place on top of crackers, then sliced chicken on top of broccoli.
Add mushrooms.
In 1/2 to 3/4-quart of broth, melt 1 pound Velveeta cheese.
Pour over chicken, broccoli and crackers.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
May cover with foil. (I have used canned broth with good results.)

title: seafood brochettes(serves 4)
directions: Remove veins from prawns.
Combine cilantro, olive oil, Tabasco sauce, lime juice and white wine for marinade.
Add seafood and refrigerate 1 hour.
Thread seafood and vegetables onto skewers and barbecue or broil until done, basting occasionally with marinade. Serve over steamed rice.

title: large banana pudding
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients together, then fold in Cool Whip.

In a 9 x 13-inch dish, spread a thin layer of pudding mixture over bottom of dish, then put a layer of wafers over this. a layer of pudding, then bananas. Continue doing this until you finish with a layer of pudding. Refrigerate several hours before serving.

title: chocolate pie(dad and i were never late for mom's chocolate pie)
directions: In a saucepan mix sugar, cocoa, butter and cornstarch.
Add egg yolks and water.
Boil mixture until thick.
Pour into baked pie crust.

title: sweet potato pudding
directions: Cook in large iron skillet inside oven at 350° for about 45 to 50 minutes or until thick.
Stir away from sides of skillet two or three times.
Stir after 20 minutes; cook 15 more minutes and stir again.

title: copper penny carrots
directions: Peel and slice carrots.
Cover and cook in small amount of water 5 minutes until crisp and tender.
Rinse under cold water; drain and cool.
Separate onion into rings.
Alternate carrots, peas, onion rings and green pepper in another bowl.
Mix remaining ingredients until smooth.
Pour over vegetables.
Cover and refrigerate.
Makes 8 servings.
May be stored for up to 2 weeks.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix ingredients.
May put sausage in microwave to get some grease off.
Form into balls and bake in oven on a cookie sheet until brown at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: chicken burgers
directions: Mix ground chicken with ground garlic cloves and buttermilk. Form into six balls and carefully press into bread crumbs in patty shape.
Saute for one minute on each side in olive oil and place in baking dish.
Bake for 10 to 12 minutes at 325°.
Serve with honey-mustard mayonnaise.

title: grandmother burgess' chocolate cream pie
directions: Add chocolate to milk and heat in double boiler.
When chocolate is melted, beat with rotary eggbeater for 1 minute or until smooth.
Combine flour, sugar and salt. Add to egg yolks. Pour small amount of milk mixture over egg mixture, stirring continuously.
Return to double boiler and cook until thickened, stirring constantly.
Add butter and vanilla.
Cool.
Pour into pie shell and cover with meringue made by folding sugar into egg whites.
Bake at 300° for 12 minutes or until delicate brown.

title: fried turkey
directions: Clean and season turkey or hen thoroughly.
Dice onions and green peppers and place under skin throughout the turkey. Seasonings can include Cajun, garlic salt, pepper, salt, poultry, Season-All, etc.
Flour turkey before frying.
Oil should be very hot.
(Pot used should be able to withstand heat.)
Oil should cover turkey; check occasionally for doneness.
Be careful with the hot oil.
When you put the turkey in the oil initially, the oil will boil up.
Any question, call me.

title: golden baked chicken
directions: In a bowl, combine the potato flakes, parmesan cheese, parsley, paprika, garlic salt, onion powder and pepper.
Dip chicken into butter, then into potato flake mixture.
Place on 2 greased 15 x 10 x 1 inch baking pans.
Bake at 375° for 50 to 60 minutes or until juices run clear.
Yield: 12 servings.

title: herbed potato bake
directions: Combine margarine, soup mix and rosemary.
Scrub potatoes and cut into 1/2-inch thick.
Combine margarine mixture and potatoes. Toss gently.
Arrange in shallow baking dish.
Cover and bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Makes 3 to 4 servings.

title: mother's old fashion molasses cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together well except water.
After ingredients are mixed well; add the hot water.
Bake in a 375° oven for 35 minutes in a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: holly's marinated sweet onions
directions: Cover sliced onions with all ingredients.
Place in 2-quart covered dish.
Chill at least 24 hours, stirring occasionally.

title: potato pancakes
directions: Wash, peel and grate potatoes.
Add remaining ingredients.
Fry and then cover until ready to eat them.

title: rhubarb dessert
directions: Wash and cut rhubarb and fill a greased cake pan half full of rhubarb.
Sprinkle sugar over rhubarb, then sprinkle dry package Jell-O over sugar.
Spread dry yellow cake mix on top of Jell-O. Pour 1 1/2 cups water over the top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until rhubarb is done.
Cool and refrigerate.

title: barbecued ribs
directions: Cut ribs into serving sized pieces.
Place into a Dutch oven and cover with water.
Add 3/4 teaspoon salt and bring to a boil. Cover; reduce heat and simmer 45 minutes; drain.
Place ribs in shallow baking pan.
Combine next nine ingredients, mixing well. Pour sauce over ribs; bake uncovered at 350° for 25 minutes, basting occasionally.
Garnish with green onions, if desired. Makes 3 to 4 servings.

title: cherry winks
directions: Sift together flour, baking powder, soda and salt.
Combine shortening and sugar and cream well.
Blend in eggs, milk and vanilla.
Add dry ingredients and 1/3 cup maraschino cherries. Crush cornflakes.
Pull off walnut-size pieces of dough and roll into balls.
Roll balls in cornflakes.
Place on a greased cookie sheet.
Top each cookie with 1/4 of a cherry.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: pizza wheels
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients and salt.
Add meat; mix well. In shallow baking pan, shape into 7 or 8 circles about 4 to 4 1/2-inches in diameter, building a 1-inch high edge.
Combine tomato sauce, mushrooms and basil; spoon into patties.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.
Lay cheese spoke-fashion atop pizzas.
Bake 2 minutes longer or until cheese melts.
Serves 7 or 8.

title: oatmeal-raisin cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees.
In small mixing bowl combine flour, oats, raisins, baking soda, and cinnamon, set aside.

title: pepper jelly
directions: In a large saucepan, bring peppers, sugar and vinegar to a hard rolling boil.
Remove pan from heat and cool for 5 minutes.
Add Certo and food color.
Pour into sterilized jars.
Usually add all green, but at Christmastime, halve the mixture with red and green.
Makes about 12 baby food jars or 4 to 5 half-pint jelly jars.

title: baked onions(serves 6)
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
In a small saucepan, combine honey, butter and salt.
Melt and stir over heat.
In a 9 x 13-inch baking dish, arrange sliced onions.
Bake 45 minutes, until onions are golden brown.

title: turkey meat loaf
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Mix all ingredients together, saving extra ketchup.
Mold into loaf and put in baking dish.
Cover top with extra ketchup.
Bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: chocolate cake
directions: Sift flour and sugar into large mixing bowl.
In saucepan, bring next 4 ingredients to a rapid boil.
Stir in sugar and flour.
Mix in other ingredients.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 400° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: cinnamon cake
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients (mixture will be very thick).
Mix sugar and cinnamon; stir in cake mixture.
Save a few tablespoons to sprinkle on top of cake, after cake has been baked.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes in tube pan.

title: chutney cheese spread
directions: Blend the first 4 ingredients well.
Chill 4 hours.
Scrape out pineapple half and fill with mixture.
Top with almonds. Serve with crackers.

title: 8 minute cheesecake
directions: Beat cheese until smooth.
Gradually beat in sugar.
Fold in sour cream and vanilla.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Blend well.
Spoon into crust.
Chill at least 4 hours until set.
Garnish with fresh strawberries or pie filling.

title: peanut butter jumbos
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Lightly grease cookie sheets or line with parchment paper.
Cream butter, sugars, peanut butter and eggs in large bowl until light.
Blend in baking soda, vanilla and oats until well mixed.
Stir in chocolate chips and candy pieces.

title: pineapple cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugars together.
Add eggs and beat well. Sift dry ingredients and add alternately with pineapple to the shortening mixture.
Bake at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: fudge
directions: Add peanut butter to melted butter and mix well.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Refrigerate 1/2 hour.
Score and refrigerate until solid.

title: pecan tarts
directions: Prepare medium syrup by boiling sugar and water together; set aside to cool.
Add flour and salt to lightly beaten eggs.
Add milk and mix well.
Cook mixture in double boiler until thick and smooth, stirring constantly.
To this add half of the brown syrup and shortening. Remove from fire.
Add vanilla and cool.
Put 2 tablespoons of mixture in each tart shell.
Place 4 pecans on top. Use remaining syrup to cover the pecans and put a tablespoon of whipped cream in the center of each.
Put in icebox and chill. Makes 12 tarts.

title: light peanut butter fudge
directions: Mix milk, sugar and salt well in 1 1/2 to 2-quart saucepan. Stir until it begins to boil (medium heat).
Turn stove to simmer and let cook for 5 minutes, without stirring (time).
Remove from burner.
Mix in peanut butter and marshmallow cream, stirring until completely mixed.
Pour into greased 8-inch square pan. Very easy recipe.

title: turkey salad for a large group
directions: Cook Creamettes.
Drain.
Cook turkey.
Skin and debone.
Cut in small pieces.
Hard cook the eggs.
Peel and dice.
Chop celery and pimentos.
Combine these ingredients with salad dressing. Season with salt and pepper to taste.
Serves 30.
Keep refrigerated.

title: party puffs
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Cut each biscuit into 4 pieces.
Melt butter in a saucepan.
Stir in onion soup mix and biscuit pieces over low heat, tossing gently, until biscuit pieces are thoroughly coated.

title: peppernuts
directions: Baking Temperature: 350°.
Baking Time: 8 to 10 minutes.

title: jane's eggplant parmesan
directions: Peel eggplant, cut into 1/2-inch slices.
Dip each slice in egg and then in bread crumbs.

Brown in oil, drain on paper towel. Place a layer of eggplant in a casserole dish, sprinkle with Parmesan cheese and spoon a layer of spaghetti sauce over top. Repeat until all eggplant is used, topping last layer of sauce with Mozzarella cheese (a jar of sliced mushrooms is very good layered with this).
Bake uncovered 15 to 20 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: mexican delight
directions: Mix onion, garlic and beef and brown lightly.
Add tomato sauce and 3/4 of the olives.
Mix sour cream, cottage cheese and chopped chilies.
Set this mixture aside.
Crush tortilla chips and put into a baking dish that has been oiled or "Pamed" for the crust. Save some of the chips for garnish.
Spoon meat mixture over the chips, spread cheese mixture over the meat.
Grate Monterey Jack cheese over all; garnish with the leftover chips and 1/2 cup of the sliced olives.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: tuna noodle casserole
directions: Cook noodles; drain.
Combine noodles, tuna (drained), mayonnaise, celery and onion.
Blend soup and milk; heat through. Add shredded cheese; heat until cheese melts.
Add to noodle mixture.
Turn into 2-quart casserole.
Bake, uncovered, at 425° for 20 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: all american burger
directions: Combine first eight ingredients (garlic, catsup, steak sauce, oil, Worcestershire sauce, sugar, vinegar and hot sauce) in saucepan.
Bring to a boil; simmer, uncovered, for 5 minutes. Combine beef, salt and pepper; form into 4 (3/4-inch thick) patties.
Grill over medium-hot coals for 15 to 18 minutes (until done, turning once and brushing often with sauce).
Serve on buns with desired toppings.

title: homemade noodles
directions: Beat eggs.
Add salt and water.
Mix in flour.
Roll out thin on floured table.
Slice in finger width slices.
Cook in boiling chicken broth for about 20 minutes.

title: cornbread salad
directions: Combine cornbread mix, egg and milk.
Stir well.
Spoon mixture into a greased 8-inch baking pan.
Bake for 15 to 20 minutes.
Cool and crumble cornbread.
Set aside.

title: easy cobbler
directions: Mix sugar, butter, milk, flour, salt and baking powder and spread in an ungreased pan.
Arrange peaches on batter; sprinkle over peaches the 1 cup of sugar.
Heat 1 cup of peach juice and pour over all.
Bake in slow oven 1 hour.
Add water to juice if necessary for 1 cup.

title: skillet spanish rice(with meat, optional)
directions: Heat oil in skillet.
Add onion, green pepper, rice and beef. Stir over
high
heat until lightly browned.
Add sauce and remaining ingredients.
Mix
well.
Bring
quickly
to
a boil. Heat to simmer for 25 to 30 minutes.
Makes 4 servings. Meat may be omitted.
Two cups grated cheese may be added just before serving.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Melt butter.
Add onions and celery; cook until soft.
Add mushrooms; cook 3 minutes.
Stir in flour; cook 1 minute.
Stir in chicken broth and milk; cook until thickened.
Add peas and seasoning; set aside.
Cook carrots in 1 cup water for 5 minutes.
Drain and add with chicken to sauce. Spoon into a 12 x 9-inch baking dish.
Top with "Corn Bread Crust" (recipe in book).

title: pretzel delight
directions: Make a crust from the pretzels, margarine and 3 teaspoons sugar.
Press in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes. Cool.

title: oyster cracker snack
directions: Put crackers in brown bag.
Mix dry ingredients.
Put in crackers.
Shake.
Pour on oil.
Shake.
Let set until oil soaks in, about 1 hour.
Store in airtight container.

title: japanese salad
directions: Peel and thinly slice cucumber.
Set aside.
In a medium bowl, combine vinegar, sugar and soy sauce.
Add salt to taste.
Toss sliced cucumber with mixture and chill for about 1 hour.
Makes 3 servings.

title: meat loaf topping
directions: In a mug, mix ketchup, water, mustard, vinegar and brown sugar.
Pour over meat loaf.
The Amish topping will make your meat loaf delicious!

title: chicken and broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli, drain and place in a greased casserole dish. Boil chicken breasts.
Put chicken pieces on top of broccoli.
Mix together chicken soup and sweet milk;
pour over chicken and broccoli.
Sprinkle desired amount of bread crumbs or cracker crumbs on top.
When it is almost cooked, put some grated cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes.

title: honey mustard chicken
directions: Mix salad dressing, mustard and honey.
Place chicken on greased grill over medium-hot coals (coals will have slight glow) or rack of broiler pan 5 to 7 inches from heat.
Brush with 1/2 of the salad dressing mixture.
Cook 8 to 10 minutes and turn.
Brush with remaining salad dressing mixture.
Continue cooking 8 to 10 minutes or until tender.

title: chili con carne
directions: In a Dutch oven or large wide saucepan over moderately low heat, brown the beef, crumbling it with a fork; push beef to one side and spoon off any fat.
Sprinkle meat with chili powder, salt and sugar; mix well.
Add onion, green pepper, tomato sauce, water and bay leaf.
Cover and simmer, stirring occasionally, for 1 hour.
Remove bay leaf.

title: congealed salad
directions: Mix jello with sugar and boiling water.
Add warm cheese; mix well.
Add apricots.
Mix well.
Add large size carton whipped topping.
Mix well.
Place in refrigerator to chill.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Saute onion in margarine or butter.
Add soup.
Stir and add pepper, sugar and Tabasco.
In casserole, put 1 can of drained beans and 1/2 can bean sprouts.
Sprinkle 1/2 water chestnuts and 1/2 of the fried onion rings on this.
Cover with 1/2 of soup mixture.
Repeat this for 2 layers.
Sprinkle with grated cheese and bake in 350° oven until bubbly.

title: miracle cobbler
directions: Mix and pour into buttered baking dish.
Over batter, spread fruit.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.

title: ham, broccoli casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cook broccoli and drain.
Trim crusts from bread.
In buttered 12 x 8 x 2-inch pan, arrange 6 slices bread on bottom.
Top with cheese, then broccoli, then ham.
Cut rest of bread diagonally and arrange overlapping on top of casserole.
Butter each slice on top.
Beat eggs slightly; add milk, salt and mustard.
Pour over casserole.
Bake 45 minutes until set.
Cover with foil if bread gets too brown.
Serves 6 to 8.
Make night before and refrigerate.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli and rice as directed on package. Saut onions and celery in butter. Add soup and cheese whiz. Add to broccoli and rice. Bake in oven until heated thoroughly.

title: quick rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in water.
Blend together Crisco and sugar in large bowl.
Add water mixture.
Gradually add flour until dough is thick.
Cover; let stand in warm place 15 minutes.
Roll dough out on lightly floured surface; cut out with a biscuit cutter. Put a pat of butter on each.
Fold over; seal edges with a fork or by pinching.
Bake at 400° until golden brown.

title: honey bun cake
directions: Mix cake mix, oil, eggs and sour cream until well blended. Pour half of mixture into 13 x 9-inch baking dish, greased and floured.

title: seafood salad
directions: Mix the the first 3 ingredients the night before in an airtight container.
(I store this in the refrigerator, but the original recipe says to leave at room temperature.)
At least 4 hours before serving, add the crab, shrimp, mayonnaise, salt and pepper.
Mix well and refrigerate until ready to serve.
This is really yummy!

title: cheese wafer
directions: Grate the cheese. Add softened oleo; mix well. Add flour, salt, pepper and nuts. Add a few drops of water to make into balls.
Flatten balls between waxed paper.
Bake about 15 minutes at 325°.

title: nighty nighty cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Beat egg whites until firm.
Gradually add sugar until stiff.
Stir in nuts and chocolate chips.
Drop by teaspoon on foil cookie sheet.
Put in oven.
Close door.
Turn off oven.
Do not open oven door.
Go to bed.
Wake up to cookies.

title: tuna salad
directions: Drain tuna.
Dice onion, celery and green pepper.
Chop the boil eggs.
Mix all the ingredients and add seasoning to taste. Place in refrigerator for about 2 hours before serving.

title: dublin potato salad
directions: Cook potatoes until tender.
Drain and cool.
Add remaining ingredients and chill.

title: poppy seed cake
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients, then add eggs, one at a time.
Grease and flour Bundt pan and sprinkle with sugar.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Take cake out while still hot.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar for decoration.

title: monster cookies
directions: Mix in order.
Drop by teaspoon.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix soup, sour cream, melted margarine, salt and cheese; add hash browns and mix thoroughly.
Spoon into greased casserole dish.
Mix corn flake crumbs with small amount of melted margarine.
Sprinkle over top of casserole and bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: fluffy lime salad
directions: Fold all ingredients together and place in mold or 9-inch square dish.
Let set overnight if possible.
Should jell for at least 2 hours.

title: rhubarb dumplings
directions: Mix all except butter.
Melt butter in casserole bowl.
Mix together sugar, flour and milk.
Pour batter on the melted butter and fruit mixture on the batter.
Do not mix.
Bake at 350°.

title: louisiana dirty rice
directions: Brown bacon in skillet and set aside.
Brown onions in bacon grease until brown.
Add livers and stir until not wet looking. Add raw rice and stir until rice is a nutty light brown.
Add all other ingredients and cook slowly until rice is done.
Do not overcook.
Season with salt and red pepper to taste.

title: pork chop casserole
directions: Put rice in bottom of pan.
Pour onion soup over rice, then pour water.
Place pork chops on soup.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: pumpkin raisin bread
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients in a medium size bowl.
Sift together the next 6 ingredients in a large bowl.
Make a well in center and add pumpkin mixture.
Stir in raisins.
Turn into greased 8 1/2 x 4 1/2 x 2 1/2-inch pans.
Makes 3 medium loaves. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Test center with toothpick.

title: easy frosting
directions: Cook over medium heat until thick or bring to a slight boil the flour and milk.
Cool.
Beat Crisco, granulated sugar and cooled milk and flour mixture until smooth.
Add softened butter or margarine.
Beat until light and fluffy.
Frosts 8 or 9-inch layer cake.
May add flavoring if so desired.

title: apple crumb pie
directions: Arrange apples in pie shell.
Combine 1/2 cup sugar with cinnamon and sprinkle over the apples.
Sift the remaining 1/2 cup sugar with the flour.
Cut in the butter until mixture is crumbly and sprinkle evenly over the apples.
Bake in a hot 450 degree oven for 10 minutes.
Reduce heat to 350 degrees and continue baking for 40 minutes until apples are tender.

title: jello party salad
directions: Combine
jello,
cream	cheese and boiling water; chill until cold and syrupy.
Fold remaining ingredients into jello and let set overnight.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: Combine chicken and onion together. Spoon onto tortillas, sprinkle with cheese and roll up. Place in pan with sides touching in casserole dish.

title: grandmother's delicious gingerbread
directions: Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Serve warm with ice cream, whipped cream or applesauce.

title: special lemon pie
directions: In medium bowl, combine Eagle Brand, ReaLemon and food coloring; mix well.
In small bowl, beat egg whites with cream of tartar until stiff but not dry; gently fold into Eagle Brand mixture.
Turn into crust.
Chill 3 hours or until set.
Garnish with whipped cream and lemon slices, if desired.
Refrigerate leftovers.

title: spinach casserole
directions: Beat eggs slightly and add all other ingredients.
Mix and pour into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Cook ingredients for 5 or 6 minutes, or until thick.
While still hot, add 3 tablespoons strawberry jello.
Cool.
Pour over fresh strawberries in baked pie shell.
Top with whipped cream if desired and refrigerate.

title: mom's oven pot roast
directions: Have the foil wrap large enough to be able to wrap and seal the roast.
(Foil is easy to double and mold to make larger.) Place foil wrap in a shallow baking pan.
On bottom of foil wrap, first sprinkle 1/2 the package of soup mix. Next add 1 can of mushrooms. Then in slices, add 1/2 stick butter.

Then lay the roast (lightly seasoned with salt and pepper) on top of butter. Spread the remaining 1/2 packet of soup mix, the second can of mushrooms and last half of butter (in slices) on top of the roast. Bring the aluminum foil wrap up and seal the top with a double fold and seal ends well.
Bake the foil wrapped roast (in baking pan) at 300 degrees for 3 hours.
Cook egg noodles according to package directions.
Top noodles with pot roast and mushroom juice.
Makes 10 servings.
This is a great easy recipe for company that makes others think you are such a gourmet!

title: texas pecan cake
directions: Separate eggs.
Cream butter and sugar.
Add egg yolks and beat well.
Beat egg whites until fluffy but not stiff.
Fold into creamed mixture.
Stir in the flour.
Now stir in the nuts and the fruit.
Refrigerate dough overnight.
The next morning, put dough into an ungreased tube pan.
It will go in the pan in chunks, as it is cold, but it will spread as it bakes.
Bake 3 hours, beginning at 250° and gradually increasing heat the last hour and a half until it reaches 350°.
The long slow cooking browns the pecans and makes this cake especially good.
To decorate the cake, put whole pecans and pieces of pineapple and cherry halves on top of the cake as it rises and begins to bake.
Serves 10.

title: cheese ball
directions: Knead all ingredients, except nuts, into a ball.
Put chopped nuts on a tea towel and roll ball to coat.
To store, wrap in foil and freeze.
Thaw in refrigerator for a day.

title: raspberry hazelnut meringue cake
directions: Butter and flour the sides of the sandwich tins and line the bottom with a disc of non-stick (silicone) cooking paper.
Set the oven at 375°.

Whisk the egg whites until stiff with a rotary or electric beater, add the sugar 1 tablespoon at a time and continue beating until the mixture is very stiff and stands in peaks. Whisk in the vanilla essence and vinegar, then fold in prepared nuts.

Divide the mixture between the two prepared tins and smooth the top with a pallette knife; bake 30-40 minutes but no longer. The top of the meringue will be crisp and the inside soft like a marshmallow.
Turn on to wire racks to cool.

title: heart smart baked chicken
directions: In blender place oatmeal, Parmesan cheese, salt, paprika and pepper. Cover and blend about 1 minute or until thoroughly mixed.

title: lake erie perch
directions: Mix eggs and milk in one bowl. Mix flour and corn meal in another bowl. Dip perch, one piece at a time, into egg mixture, then dip perch, one piece at a time, into flour mixture. In a deep-fryer, heat oil to 370°. Add perch and deep-fry until each side is golden brown.

title: lasagna rolls
directions: Cut sausage into 6 equal pieces (uncooked).
Slice sausage 3/4 of the way lengthwise.
Put a slice of Mozzarella cheese in sausage.
Cook lasagna noodles.
Wrap sausage and cheese with noodle.
Hold together with a toothpick.
Place in baking dish. Pour spaghetti sauce over noodles.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: biscuits
directions: Mix all ingredients together and roll or pat 1/2 inch thick and cut with biscuit cutter (makes 16 biscuits).
Bake at 450° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: yellow rice casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients and put in casserole dish.
Cover with grated cheese and bake at 350° until cheese is melted and bubbling.

title: mary's pot roast and veggie gravy
directions: Sear roast in oil in Dutch oven. Add remaining ingredients but do not add any water. Seal top of Dutch oven by covering completely with foil and then covering with lid. Cook in a 350° oven about 3 hours. Do not open during cooking as it would allow the sealed juices and steam to escape. You do not want to lose any of the flavor. Also, it is easy to get burned. Let cool until lid can be safely removed.

title: tuna casserole
directions: Saute onions and green peppers in butter.
Remove from heat and add small can of tuna, salad dressing, mustard, milk and soup. Add cooked macaroni.
Sprinkle with cracker crumbs or potato chips.
Dot with butter.
Bake 30 minutes at 375°.

title: soben fruit salad
directions: Pour all ingredients in a bowl, stir and chill.
(Fat Free)

title: lemon meringue pie
directions: Combine sugar, water and cornstarch and cook over medium heat until mixture boils, stirring constantly. Boil 1 minute. Stir 1/2 of mixture into 6 beaten egg yolks. Blend all together and cook 1 minute more. Remove from heat and add remaining ingredients. Pour into baked pie shell and top with meringue.

title: strawberry cake
directions: Mix all ingredients and beat well.
Pour into angel food or Bundt cake pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until done.
Can be served plain, with whipped cream or iced.

title: cheese cake (in pie plate)
directions: Cream cheese and 2/3 cup sugar until fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Oil pie plate.
Pour mixture in pie plate.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Remove and cool 20 minutes.
Mix 3 tablespoons sugar, sour cream and vanilla.
Pour over pie.
Bake 10 minutes longer.

title: strawberry preserves
directions: Combine berries and sugar.
Let stand 20 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Stir Sure-Jell into water.
Bring to a rapid boil.
Boil 1 minute, stirring constantly.
Remove from stove and add to berries.
Stir about 2 minutes.
Cover bowl with paper towel and let stand 24 hours.
Put in jelly jars. Top with wax paper rounds and then lids. Store in freezer.
Recipe can be doubled.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream sugars and margarine.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each.
Stir in milk, vanilla and oatmeal.
Add dry ingredients (sifted together).
Add raisins, chips and nuts.
Drop by spoonfuls onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10-12 min.
Makes 60 cookies.

title: blonde brownies
directions: Mix the top 4 ingredients until crumbly. Spread in a greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: chicken enchilada verde
directions: Mix together chicken, cheese, sour cream, onion and green chilies.
In a large saute pan, heat enchilada sauce and cream of chicken soup until warm and blended.
Heat each tortilla in sauce until soft.
Remove and roll with 2-3 tablespoons of filling mixture.
Place filled tortilla, seam down, in 13 x 9 pan coated with non-stick cooking spray.
Place close together.
Cover with remaining sauce.
Cover pan with foil. Bake at 350 degrees for 20 minutes.
Uncover and bake additional 10-15 minutes.
Depending on how full each tortilla is, another pan may be needed.

title: hamburger soup
directions: Heat 5-quart kettle over medium heat.
Add meat and cook until brown and crumbly.
Add onion, cook until translucent.
Stir in water, bouillon cubes, carrots, celery, bay leaf, green beans, basil, tomato sauce and macaroni.
Cover and simmer 30 minutes or until pasta and vegetables are done to your liking.
Before serving, stir in wine or fruit juice and remove bay leaf.
Makes about 4 quarts.

title: onion dip
directions: Mix in blender until smooth.
Add 1/2 envelope onion soup mix. Chill and serve.
If too thick, add milk until desired consistency.

title: dump cake
directions: Grease a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix the first 2 ingredients and "dump" into cake pan.
Spread the remaining ingredients, one layer at a time, into the pan in the order they are listed.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Boil the top 3 ingredients to a soft ball stage.
Then add 1 pound peanuts, 1/4 teaspoon of salt, continue boiling.
Stirring all the while until syrup turns light brown.
Remove from flame. Add 2 tbsp butter and 2 tsp of soda and 1/2 teaspoon of vanilla. Stir well, pour in well buttered pan.

title: oatmeal pie
directions: Beat eggs; add sugar, syrup and oatmeal.
Bake in unbaked pie shell at 425° for 10 minutes and reduce temperature to 350° for 35 minutes.
Makes 1 pie.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: Place chicken breast in large bowl.
Mix in the cheese and jalapenos.
Put mixture on the tortilla shells.
Roll and place in 9 x 12 sprayed pan.
Mix together the soup, milk and salsa.
Dump over tortillas.
Sprinkle with some grated cheese.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 to 3/4 hour (cover with foil).

title: potato casserole
directions: Thaw steak fries enough so you can cut into 1-inch pieces. Mix all together.
Pour into a greased 9 x 13-inch baking pan. Bake at 350° about 40 minutes.
Top with 1 can onion rings, broken up.
Continue baking 10 to 15 minutes.
This makes a large casserole.

title: jerusalem artichoke relish
directions: Wash and scrape artichoke tubers.
Place in sterilized pint size jars.
Mix other ingredients in saucepan and bring to boil. Pour over artichokes.
Seal jars.
Allow to set one month before using.

title: vidalia onion casserole
directions: Melt margarine and cook onions until tender.
Butter a casserole dish and line with cracker crumbs.
(May substitute bread crumbs.)
Mix together soup and onions.
Pour mixture over crumbs.
Beat together eggs and milk.
Pour this over casserole. Sprinkle grated cheese and more cracker crumbs over top.
Bake at 350° until brown and bubbly.

title: black forest cake
directions: Combine in a large bowl all ingredients; stir by hand.
Pour into a greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 325° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Cook to toothpick "test."

title: low-fat vegie casserole
directions: Spray casserole bowl with vegetable spray.
Place equal parts of vegies in dish in layers. Salt and pepper to taste. Dot with low-fat margarine or spray.
Cover with lid.
Bake 1 1/2 hours at 350°.

title: cranberry refrigerator dessert
directions: Grind fresh cranberries. Combine banana and 1/2 cup sugar. Set aside.

title: drunken dogs
directions: Mix all together in saucepan.
Simmer over low heat 1 hour.
If it dries out, add a little more booze.
Transfer to a serving dish with toothpicks.
Enjoy!!

title: calico beans
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Bake in a 350° oven for 1 1/2 hours or simmer in a crock-pot at medium-low heat setting for several hours.

title: oven fried mullet
directions: Combine egg and
milk
and
beat
well.
Dip
mullet in batter and roll in bread crumbs.
Place on greased baking pan, skin side down.
Pour
cooking
oil over mullet.
Bake at 450° for 15 to 20 minutes or until brown.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix altogether.
Add a little oil in bottom of baking pan. Shape into loaf.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes, covered. Uncover and let top brown before removing from oven.

title: mexican wedding cake
directions: Mix together.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes in a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: pheasant a la orange
directions: 1. Clean and skin pheasant. Rub poultry seasoning, sage, salt, and pepper into the meat.
2. In a large casserole dish squeeze the orange over the
pheasant and place orange peels over the top of the
pheasant.
3. Add wine and place cover on dish. Place in hot oven for
50 minutes at 375°.

title: corn flake cookies
directions: Add 1/2 cup sugar gradually to the 2 egg whites.
Beat until sugar is dissolved.
Add vanilla.
Stir in pecans and corn flakes. Drop by spoon on to large cookie sheet lined with wax paper. Bake at 275° about 55 minutes.

title: buttermilk pound cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs and beat well.
Add 1/2 of flour, beat 1 minute.
Add rest of flour, then buttermilk last with flavoring and lemon juice.
Bake in large tube pan at 300° for about 1 hour, until top springs back to touch.
Cool slightly before removing from pan.

title: broccoli supreme
directions: Cook broccoli according to the directions on the package. Drain.
In a
saucepan, saute the onions, celery and green pepper in the butter until soft.
Add the remaining ingredients except the cheese and mix well. Salt and pepper to taste.
Transfer to a baking dish. Top with the cheese and bake at 350° for 20 minutes. Serves 8.

title: chicken bundles italian
directions: Skin, bone and coarsely chop chicken.
Cook with green onions in hot oil over medium heat until chicken is no longer pink and onions are tender.
In large bowl combine spinach, Ricotta and Parmesan cheeses, garlic, oregano, nutmeg and lemon.
Stir in chicken and onions, salt and pepper to taste.
Lightly grease 8 (10-ounce) custard cups with some melted butter.
Line each cup with egg roll wrappers, allow hangover.
Divide chicken mixture among 8 cups; fold ends over to cover mixture entirely.
Brush with butter.
Press seams to seal.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: skillet beans
directions: Dice up
three
strips
of
bacon
and fry.
When half done, add chopped onion.
When
the
onion
is slightly browned, pour off most of the grease
and
add
beans,
sugar, vinegar and catsup;
stir well and cover.
Let this simmer for at least 30 minutes.
The longer you let it simmer, the better
it is.
Or else bake slowly at 300° for a couple of hours.

title: roman apple cake(a rich delight)
directions: Heat
oven
to
325°.	Sift
the
flour.
Add	sugars, butter,
cinnamon and salt.
Use hands to crumble this mixture until
blended, but not oily.
Divide the crumbs into 2 parts. Stir
into	1/2
the crumbs the soda, buttermilk and egg, combined and beaten.
Place 1/2 of this batter in a deep greased ovenproof 9-inch pie plate.

title: scrumptious peanut butter pie(makes 2 pies)
directions: Mix cream cheese until fluffy.
Add peanut butter and Eagle Brand milk.
Beat until smooth.
Add lemon juice and vanilla. Fold in one container Cool Whip.
Spoon into pie shell and top with the remaining container of Cool Whip.
Sprinkle with chopped pecans and ground chocolate chips.
Chill 4 hours.

title: orange balls
directions: Mix all ingredients together except coconut.
Make into small balls (1-inch) and roll in flaked coconut.
Yields about 50 to 60.

title: chili con carne
directions: Cook bacon in heavy skillet or pan.
Remove and chop.
Saute onion in drippings, then add meat to brown until no longer pink. Add remaining ingredients.
Bring to a boil, stirring, then lower heat.
Cover and simmer for 20 minutes.
Adjust seasonings.
Serve over noodles or rice.

title: nancy's sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix ingredients together and pour into a casserole dish. Bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: mom's pecan pie
directions: Mix and bake at 350°.

title: pork chop bake
directions: Brown chops in shortening or spray pan with vegetable spray and brown both sides.
Drain chops on paper towels.
In buttered 2 to 3-quart oblong baking dish, arrange potatoes and onions and place browned pork chops on top.

title: scampi-style shrimp
directions: In a large skillet over medium-high heat, cook and stir green onion and garlic in margarine and oil for 1 minute.
Add shrimp. Cook and stir until shrimp are pink.
Add lemon juice and salt. Heat through. Garnish as desired.
Refrigerate leftovers.

title: key lime pie
directions: Beat egg whites until fluffy; continue beating and start adding the sugar.
Mix the Cool Whip and milk together.
Combine the 2 mixtures, then gradually mix in lime juice.
Pour into prepared crusts.
Cool overnight.

title: spinach meat loaf
directions: Preheat oven to 325°

title: apple pie
directions: Put half of apples in crust.
Mix sugar, flour and cinnamon. Add 1/2 cup of mix and 1/2 stick oleo.
Add apples and rest of mix. Top with crust and add oleo.
Bake 10 minutes at 450°.
Reduce heat to 350° and bake 30 minutes longer.

title: pumpkin crunch
directions: Mix together all ingredients, except cake mix and melted margarine.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch baking pan and cover with dry cake mix.
Sprinkle nuts over cake mix and drizzle with melted margarine.
Bake at 350° (325° if using glass pan) for 55 to 60 minutes.
Serve with whipped cream or plain.

title: cottage cheese dip
directions: Mix together and chill.

title: yum a set la
directions: Brown hamburger with salt, pepper, brown sugar and onion. Add tomato soup. Cook egg noodles as directed and drain. Add Cream of Chicken soup to egg noodles. Layer hamburger mixture and noodle mixture in casserole dish with cheese between layers. Bake at 350 degrees for 30 minutes.

title: lemon lush
directions: Mix and bake margarine, flour and pecans about 15 to 20 minutes at 275° to 300° until light golden color, not brown.
Let this cool.

title: best cake
directions: Mix the ingredients all together by hand and bake in 9 x 15-inch greased and floured oblong pan for about 30 to 35 minutes or until done at 350°.

title: cheese ball
directions: Finely chop the following:
ham, beef, olives and onion.
Mix together well with other ingredients. Roll in pecans and chill.

title: ranch potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Wash potatoes, and slice 1/4-inch thick. Place into a casserole dish.
Sprinkle with seasonings.
Drizzle with melted margarine.
Pour dressing over potatoes.
Toss to coat all sides well.
Cover; bake 50 to 60 minutes or until tender. Serves 8.

title: blueberry buttermilk biscuits
directions: Combine flour, baking powder, soda, salt, 1/2 cup sugar and orange rind in a medium bowl; cut in shortening with a pastry blender until mixture resembles coarse meal.
Combine egg and buttermilk.
Add to flour mixture, stirring just until dry ingredients are moistened.
Stir in blueberries.
Turn dough out onto a lightly floured surface,
knead 4 or 5 times.
Roll dough to 1/2-inch thickness.
Cut with a 2 1/2-inch biscuit cutter. Place on lightly greased baking sheet.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes or until golden brown.

title: anti-pasta salad
directions: Cook and drain noodles.
Drain gardenia and cut into small pieces.
Slice olives in half.
Combine all ingredients.
Add dressing to taste and chill.

title: greg's dream cheese cake
directions: Melt butter; add cracker crumbs and mix thoroughly.
Pat into 9-inch cake pan.
Cream the cheese.
Separate eggs.
Beat whites until foamy.
Gradually add cream of tartar, mixed with 3 tablespoons sugar.
Continue beating until egg whites form stiff peaks.
Set aside.
Beat egg yolks, flour, sugar and salt until creamy.
Beat in cream cheese and beat until smooth.
Fold in sour cream and vanilla.
Fold in egg whites.
Pour into cake pan and bake in a preheated 325° oven for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Turn off oven and leave cake in for 10 minutes.
When cool, put fresh fruit of your choice, or any canned pie filling, on top.

title: hash brown potato casserole
directions: Place thawed potatoes in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Mix together the next 6 ingredients and pour over potatoes.
Top with crushed cornflakes and drizzle melted margarine over all.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serves 12.

title: baked beans
directions: Brown meat, onion and pepper. Drain well. Drain beans. Combine remaining ingredients. Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: chicken soup(serves 1)
directions: In a saucepan, combine all ingredients.
Cook on medium heat until vegetables are tender.

title: irene's turkey curry
directions: Cook onion and apple in butter in double boiler until onion is golden.
Blend in flour and seasonings.
Add broth, milk and cream.
Cook over boiling water, stirring until thickened.
Cook additional 10 minutes, covered.
Add lemon juice and turkey.
Heat through.
Serve over hot rice.

title: holy cow cake
directions: Bake cake in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
While hot, poke holes in cake.
Pour milk and caramel over cake.
Sprinkle 1/2 Butterfinger over cake.
Chill overnight.
Mix sugar, cheese and Cool Whip. Spread over cake.
Top with more Butterfinger.

title: donna's meatballs
directions: Roll cracker crumbs until fine.
Mix with remaining ingredients.
Roll into medium sized meatballs.
Brown in oven at 350° for 15 minutes.
Remove meatballs from grease and put in casserole dish.

title: chicken pie
directions: Boil chicken until done, debone and chop in small pieces.
Put chopped chicken in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish or pan.
Mix soup and water and pour over chicken.
Mix flour, buttermilk and melted margarine and spoon over chicken.
Pour chicken broth over batter. Do not stir!
Bake at 350°
for 1 hour.
Crust will rise to top and be golden brown.

title: grits casserole
directions: Pour the grits into boiling water to which salt has been added.
Mix well cook until thickened. Add the butter, cheese, beaten eggs and milk.
Stir thoroughly and place in buttered casserole.
Bake in 350° oven for 40 minutes.

title: mandarin orange pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together, pour into graham cracker crusts and refrigerate until serving.

title: sue's gingersnaps
directions: Cream shortening, sugar, egg and molasses.
Add flour, baking soda, cinnamon, cloves and ginger.
Shape into small balls and roll into white sugar.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: plum cake
directions: Mix all ingredients, but do not beat.
Bake about one hour in a 350° oven in a greased and floured tube pan.

title: shrimp sandwich spread
directions: Soften cream cheese.
Mix all ingredients together. Refrigerate until ready to serve.
Good on party rye.

title: delta ribbon ambrosia
directions: Cook pudding according to directions on package using only 2 1/2 cups milk. Cool completely.

title: breakfast cookies("for kids on the go")
directions: Cream Crisco and sugars; add eggs, vanilla and milk and blend well.
Sift flour, baking soda and salt.
Add to mixture gradually and blend well.
Stir in Quaker oats and Raisin Nut Bran.
Mix well.
Drop by spoonfuls on ungreased cookie sheet and bake at 375° for 13 minutes.

title: apple dumplings
directions: Peel and core apples; quarter.
Roll one piece in each crescent roll.
Press to cover.
Heat together orange juice, sugar and margarine.
Bake on 300° oven until brown.

title: tart green beans with bacon
directions: Cook the beans.
Fry the bacon, cut into 1/2 inch pieces.
Add to the skillet the chopped onion, vinegar, water, sugar, salt and pepper.
Bring to a boil and pour this mixture over the drained beans.
Toss and serve.
Serves 4.

title: pretzel salad
directions: Mix crushed pretzels, butter and sugar.
Press into 9 x 11-inch pan.
Bake at 400° for 8 minutes.
Cool.

title: auntie lynette's meat loaf surprise
directions: In 3-quart saucepan, heat potatoes and enough water to cover to boiling over high heat. Reduce heat to low; cover and simmer 10 to 15 minutes until potatoes are fork-tender. Drain potatoes and return to saucepan. Add milk, margarine or butter, 1/2 teaspoon salt and 1/8 teaspoon pepper. With potato masher, mash potatoes until mixture is smooth; set aside.

title: kool kubes
directions: Mix together Kool-Aid, water and sugar. Then pour Kool-Aid into ice tray. Place ice tray in freezer until cubes are frozen. Place in drink or enjoy alone.

title: mustard sauce
directions: In a small frying pan, melt margarine.
Cook onion over medium heat for 7 minutes and blend in flour, salt and pepper. Add milk slowly, stirring until thickened.
Add mustard and cook for 1 minute over low heat.
Serve with fish steaks.

title: swedish meatballs
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients until well combined.
Form into balls.
Pour about 2 tablespoons of oil in skillet.
Brown slowly. Remove balls as soon as they are brown.
When all are brown, put back in pan.
Pour over 1 can of cream of mushroom soup, mixed with milk.
Simmer 1/2 hour.
Just before serving, stir in 8 ounces sour cream.
Keep warm.
Serve over hot noodles.

title: bread pudding
directions: Soak bread crumbs in milk.
Set aside until cool.
Add sugar, butter, eggs (slightly beaten), salt and flavoring.
Bake one hour in buttered pudding dish in slow oven.
Serve with vanilla sauce. In preparing bread crumbs, avoid using outside crusts.

title: cheese ball
directions: Chop chipped beef into small pieces.
Mix all ingredients with mixer.
Let set for approximately an hour before serving.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Cream sugar, spices and margarine until light and fluffy.
Add corn meal and Pet milk.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Blend in vanilla.
Pour into chilled unbaked pie crust.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: hot fudge pudding cake
directions: Scoop ice cream into 8 portions on chilled tray.
Freeze, uncovered, for 24 hours.
Combine flour, sugar, 2 tablespoons cocoa, baking powder and salt in ungreased 9 x 9-inch cake pan. Stir in milk, oil and vanilla with fork until smooth.
Stir in pecans.
Spread evenly.
Sprinkle with brown sugar and remaining 1/4 cup cocoa.
Pour hot water over top.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Let stand for 15 minutes.
Spoon into serving dishes, reserving sauce in pan.
Top pudding cake with ice cream portions. Drizzle with reserved sauce.
Yield:
8 servings.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Add red onion to broccoli flowerettes and stems.
Add crumbled bacon, cheese, and sunflower seeds.
Mix well.
Add dressing and mix well to serve.
Bon appetit!

title: orange-sour cream dip for fruit
directions: In medium bowl, combine concentrated orange juice and cold milk.
With electric mixer, beat in instant pudding on low speed for 2 minutes.
Stir in sour cream and chill 2 hours.

title: grated apple pie
directions: Combine sugar, flour, cinnamon and salt in a large bowl.
Add apples and toss gently.
Stir in egg and butter.
Spoon into pastry shell.
Sprinkle with pecans.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes; reduce oven to 350° and bake for 50 minutes.
Yields one 9-inch pie.

title: apricot pound cake
directions: Sift all dry ingredients together.
Beat sugar in oil.
Add eggs; mix in the dry ingredients.
Add the jars of apricot baby food.
Add the nuts.
Mix thoroughly.
Bake 1 hour at 350° in a greased Bundt or angel food pan.

title: sponge cake
directions: Mix eggs and water; add dry ingredients.
Mix well.
Spray a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pour batter into pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: baked chicken
directions: Dip chicken breasts or pieces into Italian dressing.
Roll in bread crumbs and Parmesan cheese.
Bake in a greased baking dish for 1 hour at 350°.
Can use pork chops or steak.

title: pilaf pie loaf
directions: Use a large pan.
Melt the margarine and brown noodles.
Be careful as noodles will burn quickly.
Add rice and pour chicken broth in.
Stir and cover.
Cook until broth is absorbed.
Try not to lift lid too often.

title: 3 bean casserole
directions: Mix beans altogether; add browned hamburger.
Add remaining ingredients and bake in a 350° oven for about 45 minutes.
Can be cooked in a crock-pot.

title: dieter's potatoes
directions: Mash hot potatoes and add chopped eggs.
Stir in onions and season to taste.
Serve hot.
Contains 175 calories per serving.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Blend first 4 ingredients in blender or mixer.
Beat at low speed until blended well.
Add mayonnaise and blend well again.

title: pumpkin roll
directions: Beat eggs on high for 4 minutes.
Gradually add sugar.
Add pumpkin and lemon juice.
Mix all dry ingredients (except powdered sugar) and fold into pumpkin mixture.
Spread onto greased and floured jelly roll pan.
Sprinkle nuts on top.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.

title: pork chops le grande
directions: Place chops in baking dish; cover with sliced onion and apple. Salt and pepper to taste.
Spoon soup over all.
Bake at 325° until tender, about 1 1/2 hours.

title: pistachio salad
directions: Combine the dry pudding mix with the crushed pineapple.
Mix well.
Add Cool Whip.
Mix well.
Add rest of ingredients and mix well.
Chill a few hours or overnight before serving.

title: blue cheese vinaigrette
directions: Whisk vinegar, salt and pepper.
Gradually add oil until thickened, then Blue cheese.

title: misery pie
directions: Mix pecans, chocolate chips, coconut and milk and pour into pie shell.
Bake at 350° until mixture starts bubbling and getting brown on top.
Cut into small pieces since this is very rich.

title: grandma kellers pineapple torte
directions: Put marshmallows and milk in double boiler.
When melted, cool. When cool, add drained pineapple.
Whip the whipping cream until stiff and fold into marshmallow mixture.
Line 8-inch spring-form pan with chocolate Nabisco wafers (crushed).
Take whole wafers and set around the sides of pan.
Fill with marshmallow mixture and sprinkle crushed wafers on top.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: creamy cauliflower soup
directions: Cook cauliflower in a small amount of water (cut up) with little salt 10 to 15 minutes or until tender.
Drain and coarsely chop.

title: blueberry muffins
directions: Put all ingredients, except blueberries in a mixing bowl.
Mix well by hand.
Fold in berries last.
Bake at 400° for 20-25 minutes.
Makes 12 medium muffins.

title: beef roast in mushroom gravy
directions: Blend mushroom soup, onion soup mix and water together. Pour over roast. Cover and cook in slow oven (250°) until tender. Delicious cooked in crock-pot for 7 to 8 hours. Serve gravy with rice or potatoes.

title: banana split cake
directions: Mix together cracker crumbs and melted margarine.
Press in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix together cream cheese, powdered sugar and vanilla; spread over crumbs.
Slice bananas lengthwise and lay on cream cheese mixture.
Spread pineapple on top.
Spread Cool Whip next and sprinkle with cherries and pecans.
Pour chocolate syrup sparingly over top, if desired.
Chill thoroughly.
Best if it sets overnight.

title: buttermilk pound cake
directions: Cream sugar, shortening and eggs.
Mix flour, salt and soda. Add to mixture alternately with buttermilk.
Pour into greased tube pan and bake at 400° (gas oven) or at 375° (electric oven) about 1 hour or more.

title: jewish apple cake
directions: Mix 5 tablespoons sugar and cinnamon together; set aside. Peel and slice thin apples.
Cream sugar and oil well.
Add eggs, one at a time; sift dry ingredients.
Add gradually; alternate with orange juice.
Add vanilla.
Grease Bundt pan.
Put part of batter in pan (thin layer); add apples and cinnamon sugar; repeat process with batter, apples and cinnamon and sugar.
Bake 1/2 hour at 375°, then 1 hour at 350°.
Cool when done.
Sprinkle with cinnamon sugar.

title: spinach dip with water chestnuts
directions: Process cottage cheese in food processor until blended.
Place in bowl and set aside.
Press spinach between paper towel until barely moist.
Add spinach and remaining ingredients to cheese mixture; stir well.
Cover and refrigerate about 3 hours.
Serve with fat-free crackers or raw vegetables.

title: egg gravy
directions: Scramble eggs in skillet.
Push to one side.
Mix flour, salt and pepper to oil or grease.
Stir until brown.
Mix milk to make gravy.
Mix all together in skillet.
Makes a lot to serve campers with only one skillet to wash.
Delicious!

title: cornflake macaroons
directions: Beat egg whites until stiff, gradually adding sugar and continue to beat until stiff.
Fold in coconut and cornflakes. Drop by teaspoon onto greased baking sheet.
Bake in moderate oven (350°) until lightly browned.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Cut broccoli flowerets into small bite-size pieces.
Peel upper stalks and cut into small pieces.
In small skillet, saute bacon until crisp.
Drain on paper towels.
Break into small pieces.
Slice onion into lengthwise julienne strips.

title: huckleberry delight
directions: Mix butter, nuts, flour and sugar; pat into 9 X 13 pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Cool.

title: raisin puffs
directions: Cook raisins in water over moderate heat until all the water is absorbed.
Set aside to cool.
Cream shortening, sugar and eggs until fluffy.
Sift flour with soda and salt.
Add to creamed mixture with raisins and vanilla.
Mix well.
Shape into small balls and roll in granulated sugar.
Bake on greased cookie sheet for 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: russian tea
directions: Mix all ingredients together and simmer.
Do not boil.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients. Mix brown sugar, 1/3 cup margarine, flour and chopped pecans. Mix well. Sprinkle on top of casserole 10 to 15 minutes before done. Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: date nut bread
directions: Put flour and 1 teaspoon baking powder and butter together. Pour hot water over dates and baking soda.
Add dry ingredients. Mix in nuts last.
Heat oven to 350°.
Bake 30 to 45 minutes.

title: ginger pickles
directions: Mix.
Heat for 1 hour and put in jars.
Seal while hot.

title: bourbon sweet potatoes
directions: Turn sweet potatoes, undrained, into large saucepan. Cook over medium heat, stirring, until heated through.

title: second prize baked cod fillets with piquant potato crust
directions: Mix oil, onions, potatoes, salt, pepper and dill.
Roll fillets in mix and place in pan.
Place chopped bacon, mustard and paprika in a small bowl and combine.
Spread on top of fillets. Bake.

title: cheese ball
directions: Chop onions and beef fine.
Mix well with electric mixer, using large bowl and dough hooks if you have them.
Shape into 1 large ball or 2 small balls and roll into finely chopped pecans. It handles better if it is chilled before making into balls. Serve with crackers or vegetables.

title: magic shrimp
directions: Makes 2 main dishes or 4 side dish servings.

title: irish cream coffee pound cake
directions: Beat butter at medium speed, about 2 minutes until soft and creamy.
Gradually add sugar, beating at medium speed for 5 to 7 minutes.
Add eggs one at a time; beat just until yellow disappears.
Dissolve coffee granules in boiling water.
Stir in liqueur.
Add flour to butter mixture alternately with coffee mixture, beginning with and ending with flour.
Mix at low speed. Stir in flavoring.
Pour batter into greased and floured Bundt pan. Bake at 300° for 1 hour and 40 minutes.
Cool in pan; let cool 30 minutes.
Brush with Irish Cream Glaze and sprinkle with toasted almonds.

title: baked pork chops
directions: Brown chops.
Remove chops and heat soups and water in that pan.
Prepare stuffing according to directions on box.
Arrange chops in 13 x 9-inch pan.
Put 1/2 cup stuffing on each chop.
Pat flat to cover chop.
Spoon soup over stuffing.
Cover and bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: strawberry rhubarb preserve
directions: Combine rhubarb and sugar and let stand overnight.
Next morning, cook about 15 minutes.
While hot, add strawberry Jell-O. Stir until Jell-O is dissolved.
Fill jelly jars or containers. Cover and let stand overnight.
Keep refrigerated.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Slice cookies and place on pizza pan.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes, until light brown.
Mix remaining ingredients and spread on cooled cookies.
Add fruit of your choice: strawberries, kiwi, peaches, pineapple, bananas, blueberries, etc.

title: creamed potatoes
directions: Brown bacon and onion.
Stir in milk.
Bring to a boil, stirring constantly, for 1 to 2 minutes.
Add cooked potatoes. Make thickening of flour and a little bit of milk.
Stir into milk and bacon mixture.
Cook until thickened, stirring constantly. Stir in parsley flakes.

title: lemon chess pie
directions: Melt margarine over low heat.
Add eggs, sugar, lemon extract and vinegar.
Mix well.
Pour in an unbaked pie shell and bake slowly until done at 350°.

title: meat spaghetti
directions: Cook together ground round or ground chuck and onions (stir enough to keep granular) until onions are clear and meat is brown. Add salt, black pepper, oregano, chili powder, tomatoes, Ro-Tel chilies and tomatoes and tomato sauce.
Cook vermicelli or thin spaghetti until done.

title: chocolate grasshopper
directions: Thoroughly blend melted chocolate, boiling water and 1/4 cup sugar; cool.
In large bowl, sift together flour, 1 1/2 cups of sugar, baking powder and salt.
Make a well in center of dry ingredients and add oil, egg yolks, cold water and vanilla in order given.
Beat until very smooth.
Stir chocolate mixture into egg yolk mixture.
Beat egg whites with cream of tartar until very stiff peaks form.
Pour chocolate batter in thin stream over entire surface of egg whites, gently folding to blend.

title: microwave apple crisp
directions: Arrange sliced	apples	in
1 1/2 quart round microwave dish. Sprinkle
with
lemon
juice.
In
a mixing bowl combine flour, rolled
oats,
brown
sugar,
cinnamon and cloves.	Cut butter into
mixture until crumbly.
Sprinkle mixture over top of apples. Microwave	12
minutes on High or until apples are tender.

title: lemon chicken and peppers(easy food for college students designed to impress your
directions: Juice lemon in shallow baking dish.
Pound chicken and place in dish.
Sprinkle chicken on one side with garlic and pepper.
In large skillet, melt butter.
Brown chicken over medium heat, until almost cooked.
Toss in vegetables and finish cooking.
When vegetables are crisp-tender, remove meat from skillet and drain liquid from vegetables.
Serve with saffron rice.

title: crock-pot chili
directions: Place cooked meat in crock-pot. Add beans, tomatoes, chili mix and spaghetti. Stir and mix together. Add 1 to 2 cups of tomato juice. Cook on high for 1 hour, then turn on low 3 to 4 hours.

title: pumpkin cookies
directions: Combine flour, oats, soda, cinnamon and salt.
Cream butter and sugars, add the egg and vanilla, add pumpkin.
Stir in chocolate chips or raisins.
Drop by spoonfuls on a lightly greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: cherry yum-yum(very quick and easy)
directions: Make pudding as directed on the box, add cream cheese and 1/2 container of Cool Whip.
Beat on medium speed until smooth.
Pour into pie shells.
Chill 1 hour before serving.
Before serving, top with Cool Whip and cherries.

title: quick date nut ring
directions: In warm water, stir in dates.
Add oil, eggs and vanilla. Stir in flour, sugar, salt and soda.
Blend well.
Stir in nuts. Makes 2 loaves.
Or turn into a greased 10-inch tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.
Grease loaf pans.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix ingredients together and roll into balls.
Bake 35 minutes at 325°.

title: mexican pot roast
directions: Place all ingredients in a large pot and cook for 4 to 5 hours, stirring often.
Serve over Mexican rice or crushed Fritos.

title: crock-pot chicken-n-dressing
directions: Boil chicken (put margarine in water).	Debone chicken.
Cook cornbread.	In large bowl, crumble cornbread; tear buns into pieces.
Beat eggs really well and add to cornbread and buns. Stir in onions, celery, sage, pepper and chicken.
Pour in crock-pot.	Pour cream of chicken soup on top.
Cook on high for 1 hour.
Stir if dressing is bubbling.
Turn on low and cook about 3 to 5 hours, stirring occasionally.

title: kuchen
directions: Combine all ingredients except pie filling.
In greased and floured 13 x 9-inch pan, spread 2/3 of batter.
Add pie filling and top with remaining batter.
Bake in 350° oven for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: southern potato casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together and bake 1 hour at 400°.
Save a little grated cheese to sprinkle on top before baking.

title: cheese and vegetable chowder
directions: In hot butter, cook vegetables, covered, stirring occasionally for 20 minutes or until tender.
Remove from heat; stir in flour. Mix well.
Cook 1 minute, stirring occasionally.
Add broth and bring to a boil.
Gradually stir in cheese.
Cook over medium heat, stirring until cheese is melted.
Gradually add milk. Season with salt and pepper.

title: mahogany pound cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Bake 1 hour and 30 minutes.

title: french dressing
directions: Mix ingredients thoroughly.
Add cream and beat vigorously.

title: shrimp louis dip
directions: Stir all ingredients until well mixed.
Chill for 2 hours. Serve with crackers.

title: fried cabbage
directions: Shred cabbage.
Fry onion.
Brown hamburger; drain.
Mix with cabbage and onion.
Add can of tomato sauce and simmer.

title: buttermilk salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into 8 x 12-inch pan. Freeze and keep frozen until ready to serve.
Will keep for several weeks.
You may add other fruit if desired.

title: cinnamon float
directions: Blend egg, corn syrup and milk in a blender.
Place ice cream in a tall glass.
Pour in milk mixture and sprinkle with cinnamon.

title: mermain salad
directions: Mix all ingredients; chill and serve on crisp lettuce leaves or use as a stuffing for tomatoes, avocados, etc.

title: easy-as-pie eclair cake
directions: Prepare pudding as directed on box.
When set, add Cool Whip and
beat
with
mixer.
Line
bottom
of
pan with whole crackers; pour 1/2 of pudding over this.
Put another layer of crackers and
the
rest
of
the
pudding.	Put a 3rd layer of crackers
and
refrigerate a few hours before covering the top layer of crackers with chocolate icing.

title: spinach salad with honey dressing
directions: In a large bowl, combine the first seven (7) ingredients.
In a small bowl, stir mayonnaise, honey, and lemon juice until smooth.
Pour over the salad and toss to coat.
Serve immediately. Makes 8-10 servings.

title: jo ann's punch
directions: Mix all ingredients (except ice cream) and chill until ready to serve.
Spoon ice cream into liquid when ready to serve.

title: cinnamon crunches
directions: Put butter in a medium size casserole and microwave on High for 1 minute or until melted.
Combine sugar and cinnamon in small bowl.
Add cereal to melted butter and stir until coated.
Then sprinkle the cinnamon sugar over cereal and stir again carefully. Microwave on High for 3 to 4 minutes.
Stir in the raisins and apples.
Let cool.

title: cashew chicken
directions: Saute celery and onion in butter.
Add chicken, soup and water.
Heat thoroughly.
Add 1/2 can of Chinese noodles and cashews and heat.
Pour into serving bowl and top with remaining Chinese noodles.

title: apple pound cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Butter and flour 10-cup tube pan.
Mix flour, baking powder and baking soda.
In a large bowl with electric mixer, beat sugar, butter and buttermilk until pale in color.
Beat eggs in a small bowl and add egg alternately with flour mixture.
Beat until well blended and fluffy.
With a wooden spoon, stir in apples and vanilla.
Pour batter in pan.
Bake 1 hour or until a toothpick comes out clean.
Cool in pan on wire rack 10 minutes.
Turn cake out on wire rack and cool completely. Makes 10 servings.

title: beef tater tot casserole
directions: Stir soup and cheese into meat mixture.
Layer Tots on top of meat and soup mixture.
Bake at 400° for 25 minutes.

title: stuffed bacon roll-ups
directions: Combine bread crumbs, chopped apple, onion and parsley.
Add salt, pepper and milk; mix well.
Cut each slice of bacon in half. Place 1 tablespoon mixture in center of bacon.
Roll up; secure with toothpicks.
Place on wire rack inside baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Makes 20 to 22 roll-ups.

title: wild rice stuffing
directions: Cook rice in salted water (3 cups water and 3/4 teaspoon salt).
Bring to boil, then simmer, covered, until kernels open, approximately 45 minutes.
Melt butter in large skillet; saute onion and celery until onion is tender.
Stir in rice, bread cubes, parsley, poultry seasoning, salt and pepper.
Gently stir in broth and egg.
Spoon into buttered 1 1/2-quart casserole. Bake, covered, in preheated 350° oven for 20 minutes; uncover and bake 10 minutes longer.
Makes 5 to 6 servings.

title: mints
directions: Mix all ingredients and knead as for pie dough. Roll into marble size balls. Either press into candy molds or flatten with tines of fork after rolling in small amount of sugar.
If using molds, unmold at once onto waxed paper.
Makes 6 dozen.

title: spinach balls
directions: Mix ingredients together. Cover and let sit in refrigerator overnight. Roll into balls the size of walnuts and bake on ungreased cookie sheet at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: calico carrot chop-chop
directions: Put carrots, green and red peppers and onions through food chopper, using a coarse blade.
(There should be about 14 cups.) Place in a kettle; add boiling water to cover.
Let stand 5 minutes, then drain well.
Return vegetables to kettle.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Heat, stirring several times, to boiling, then simmer, stirring once or twice for 5 minutes.
Ladle into hot sterilized jars; seal following manufacturer's directions.
Cool jars, label and date.

title: buttermilk puffs
directions: Sift together flour, sugar, baking powder, baking soda, and nutmeg.
Stir buttermilk, oil and egg with fork.
Combine and beat until smooth.
Drop by teaspoonful into hot oil and fry.
Remove from oil when done and sprinkle with powdered sugar.
Light and delicious!

title: apple cake
directions: Cream Crisco and sugar, then add eggs.
Mix in flour, cinnamon and baking soda.
Beat in apples.
Mix well.
Grease and flour a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Pears can be added with apples to total 6 cups.
Tastes best if allowed to age 1 day.

title: easy milk chocolate fudge
directions: In heavy saucepan on low heat, melt chocolate chips with milk and salt.
Remove from heat and add nuts and vanilla.
Spread in 8 or 9-inch pan, greased.
Chill 2 hours or until firm.
Makes about 2 pounds.

title: lemon sponge pie
directions: Beat egg whites and set aside.
Blend sugar, egg yolks and butter.
Add milk, flour and lemon juice.
Fold in beaten egg whites.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: pineapple banana cake
directions: Do not use mixer.
Bake in a greased Bundt pan at 350° for 1 hour and 5 minutes.

title: molasses cookies
directions: Mix together sugar, butter and shortening; add molasses, eggs and vanilla and mix.
Sift together flour, baking soda, cloves, cinnamon and baking powder; add to dough until dough is "stiff." Add raisins.
Bake at 325° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: These cookies are fun to make and very delicious!

title: peanut patties
directions: Cook the first 4 ingredients to soft ball stage at 230°, then add the remaining three.
Drop by spoonfuls on waxed paper.

title: applesauce chocolate chip cake
directions: Cream shortening, sugar and egg together.
Dissolve soda in applesauce and add dry ingredients.
Add soda and applesauce; mix well, then add the chocolate chips.
Pour into a well-greased Bundt pan and bake at 350° for 35 minutes or until done.

title: crab rangoon
directions: In a medium bowl, combine cream cheese, crab meat, salt, pepper, green onion, garlic, ginger, bread crumbs and sesame oil; mix well.
Refrigerate for 30 minutes.

title: fruit tea punch
directions: Pour boiling water over tea leaves and let stand.
Make a syrup by boiling the sugar and water until clear.
Add other ingredients.
Pour over ice and serve.
Grape juice may be used instead of the grapefruit juice.
Serves 25 people.

title: pork chops with apple stuffing
directions: Combine stuffing mix, 1/2 cup apple juice, margarine and apple in large bowl.
Saut pork chops in 10-inch skillet over medium heat until brown on both sides.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Mound 1/4 of stuffing on each chop.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Add 1/4 cup apple juice to skillet.
Heat to boiling; reduce heat.
Cover and simmer 10 to 15 minutes or until pork is done, 170° on meat thermometer.

title: fruit salad
directions: Mix ingredients together and serve.

title: taco dip
directions: Spread cream cheese on the bottom of a Corning Ware casserole. Top with chili, black olives, then the green chilies.
Last, top with the cheese.
Bake at 325° for 20 minutes or microwave until heated throughout.
You can add a layer of hot salsa if you like it hot.
Serve hot with tortilla chips.

title: hot tamale pie
directions: Brown meat with onions and garlic.
Cook slowly, stirring occasionally.
Remove excess fat.
Add salt, pepper and chili powder; stir well.
Add tomato paste and 2 cups water; continue to simmer.
In 7 cups boiling, salted water, slowly add the corn meal, stirring constantly with wire whisk.
Cook until very thick.
Place meat mixture and meal by layers in a greased casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.
Brown on top.

title: layer refried beans
directions: Put all ingredients in order into a large casserole dish. Refrigerate before serving.

title: apple nut pudding
directions: Mix apples and sugar together.
Let stand 15 minutes.
Then mix the rest of your ingredients into that.
Put your mixture into a baking dish and bake at 350° for 50 minutes.
Let cool and serve.

title: strawberry-orange sherbet
directions: Put all in a food processor or a powerful blender; puree. Serve immediately or store in freezer.
(If frozen hard, put in refrigerator 30 minutes to soften.)

title: new hampshire company casserole
directions: Cook noodles according to package instructions.
Meanwhile, cut greens from scallions into small pieces with scissors (wash scissors afterwards or your coupons will smell like onions!).
If using bar cream cheese, cut into cubes (about 16 chunks).

title: pace six layer dip
directions: Mash avocados in a bowl; add lemon juice, salt and pepper. Use another bowl to combine sour cream and mayonnaise.
Layer in an oblong dish:
bean dip, top with avocado mix, then sour cream mix.
Sprinkle with onions, tomatoes and olives.
Cover with cheese, top with Pace picante sauce.

title: date nut roll
directions: Combine sugar, milk and butter in heavy 2-quart saucepan. Blend thoroughly.
Place over low heat; stir until sugar is dissolved and mixture is boiling moderately.
Cover, cook 3 minutes.
Remove cover.
Use silver knife blade wrapped in damp cloth to remove any crystals that form on side of pan.
Stir occasionally.
Cook to soft ball stage (234°).
Add dates; mix well.
Again, cook to soft ball stage.
Remove from heat; add vanilla.
Cool without stirring to lukewarm (116°).
Beat until very thick.
Add finely chopped nuts.

title: chinese beef oriental
directions: Combine soy sauce, water, cornstarch and sugar in bowl.
Add thin sliced cut beef.
Stir to coat and marinate 5 minutes.
Heat oil in skillet and add beef (including marinade); stir-fry for 3 to 4 minutes over medium heat.
Add frozen vegetables.
Cover and cook 5 minutes over medium heat.
Remove cover and simmer 2 minutes, while stirring gently.
Serve with rice.

title: dinky's carrot cake
directions: Cream sugar and oil.
Beat in eggs.
Add dry ingredients. Fold in carrots, pineapple and nuts.
Pour in a 13 x 9-inch greased and floured pan.
Bake 25 to 40 minutes at 350°.

title: poor man's chop suey
directions: Brown hamburger, onions and celery.
When browned, add water and bouillon cubes.
Cook rice separately, then add to hamburg, stir well.
Add soy sauce to taste.
Top with chow mein noodles. Another way to use hamburger and it's delicious!

title: chicken salad
directions: In a large mixing bowl, mix together all ingredients.
Yields about 2 1/2 pounds.

title: innie's egg nog
directions: Beat
yolks and whites of eggs separately.
Add 1/2 cup sugar to	yolks
while
beating.	Add 1/4 cup sugar to whites after they have been beaten very stiff.
Mix whites and yolks gently together.
Add whipping cream and half and half.
Stir thoroughly. Serve
very cold with dollop of whipped cream and sprinkle of nutmeg.

title: chocolate rolle
directions: Mix egg yolks, sugar, flour, baking powder, chocolate and vanilla.
Beat egg whites until stiff.
Fold in gently.
Beat cream, sugar and vanilla until stiff.
Reserve.
Put dough on waxed-papered cookie sheet.
Bake at 325° for 10 minutes.
Cool. Put more waxed paper down and flip from cookie sheet onto the waxed paper.
Roll tightly.
Cool.
Unroll; spread with cream mixture.
Roll again.
Frost with chocolate frosting.
Top with cherries and nuts.

title: amber apple bake
directions: Separate dough into 10 biscuits. Place on bottom of greased 8-inch square or 2-quart round baking dish. Arrange apples over top of biscuits.

title: chocolate crinkles
directions: Cream shortening, granulated sugar and vanilla thoroughly. Beat in eggs, then chocolate.
Sift dry ingredients together.
Add to the creamed mixture alternately with milk, blending well after each addition.
Stir in nuts.
Chill 2 to 3 hours.
Form in 1-inch balls.
Roll in confectioners sugar.
Place on a greased cookie sheet 2 to 3 inches apart.
Bake in a 350° oven about 15 minutes. Yield:
4 dozen.

title: cold grape pops
directions: Buy grapes while in season or on sale.
Wash and dry completely.
Put in freezer bags (small or large) and freeze. Grapes will be a little crunchy like a popsicle.
Great while watching TV or grabbing a handful to go out and play.
Cold and healthy.

title: cabbage soup(weight watchers)
directions: Mix and cook until vegetables are tender.
Freezes well.

title: vanilla butter frosting
directions: Blend butter and sugar.
Stir in vanilla and milk.
Beat until frosting is smooth and of spreading consistency.
