title: cherry cobbler
directions: For cherry filling, in a medium saucepan, combine cherries, the 3/4 cup granulated sugar, tapioca and 1/3 cup water.
Let stand 5 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Cook and stir until slightly thickened and bubbly.
Add the 1 tablespoon butter or margarine.
Set aside; keep warm.

title: chicken livers - chopped
directions: Combine all ingredients except eggs and mayonnaise, in non-stick skillet.
Cover and simmer over moderate heat until onions are tender.
Uncover and continue cooking until liquid evaporates.
The livers and vegetables will begin to brown in the remaining fat; stir frequently.
When the livers are done, remove and drain any excess liquid.
Chop liver mixture very fine in a food processor.
Combine the liver mixture and chopped eggs with just enough mayonnaise to hold together.
Press mixture into mold. Chill several hours.
Unmold onto lettuce.
Serve with crackers.

title: hominy casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients in a 9 x 9-inch baking dish. Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes until it bubbles and browns on top. Serves 6.

title: fudgy brownies
directions: Melt chocolate and butter together over hot water.
(If using cocoa, mix with flour and sugar.)
Beat eggs until foamy.
Add sugar, beating thoroughly after each addition.
Blend in chocolate mixture, then stir in sifted flour.
Add vanilla and nuts.
Spread in greased 9 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 325° for about 40 minutes. Cool in pan; cut into squares or bars.

title: caramel icing
directions: Mix brown sugar and milk.
Add butter and simmer on low heat until melts.
Turn up to medium heat to boil until forms a soft ball.
Take off stove and beat until it cools.

title: chicken herb casserole
directions: Mix well.
Put into a buttered casserole.

title: cauliflower-radish salad
directions: Place on a platter small, individual lettuce leaves.
On the edge, ring in alternate selections of chunks of jello and small pieces of fruit.
In the middle put scoops of cottage cheese and either sherbet or yogurt.
Surprisingly tasty!

title: pickling pig cake
directions: Mix all together and beat with electric mixer.
Pour into 3 layer pans.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes, no longer.
Cool.

title: grandma bliss chocolate cake
directions: Mix chocolate and butter over low heat.
Combine in large bowl the sugar, milk, eggs, vanilla and flour (sifted with baking powder). Do not stir until all ingredients are mixed in. Beat hard until smooth.
Bake in two 8-inch round pans, greased.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes or tested.

title: old fashioned bread pudding
directions: Slice bread into 3/4-inch pieces and place in shallow buttered 1-quart baking dish. Set aside.

title: broccoli rice casserole
directions: Cook broccoli and rice separately. Drain broccoli, mix broccoli and rice together. Put the broccoli and rice in a 9 x 13 inch pan. Add cheese and soup; mix well. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: rum cake
directions: Mix all ingredients.
In a Bundt pan, greased and floured, put nuts, then the batter.
Bake at 350° for 55 to 60 minutes.

title: bleu cheese salad dressing
directions: Mix well.
Put in glass containers with lids and refrigerate. Let set at least 3 days before using.
Will keep in fridge, but if left too long, water will form on the bottom, which is the buttermilk separating.
Use as soon as possible after shaking it up.
Makes 5 plus quarts.
Bon appetit!

title: salisbury steak
directions: Combine meat, egg, oats, ketchup, 2 tablespoons water, Worcestershire, onion, salt and pepper.
Form into 6 large patties.
Pat lightly in flour.
Brown in butter; pour off grease. Combine soup and 1 can water; pour over patties.
Simmer, covered, 45 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: deep dish pumpkin pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In medium bowl, combine flour and sugars; cut in butter until crumbly.
Reserving 1 cup crumb mixture, press remainder firmly on bottom and halfway up sides of 12 x 7-inch baking dish.
Stir nuts into reserved crumb mixture; set aside.
In large mixer bowl, combine remaining ingredients except crumb mixture; mix well.
Pour into prepared crust.
Top with crumb mixture.
Bake 55 minutes, until golden brown.
Cool and garnish as desired.
Refrigerate leftovers.

title: chocolate sheet cake
directions: Combine sugar and flour in a bowl.
Set aside.
In a saucepan, combine margarine, water, cocoa and oil.
Bring to a boil.
Pour over flour sugar mixture.
Add eggs, cinnamon, vanilla, salt, buttermilk and soda.
Pour in greased sheet pan.
Bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: canadian cheese soup
directions: Melt butter in 3-quart glass casserole.
Add onions, carrots and celery.
Cover and cook with microwave 12 minutes or until vegetables are tender, stirring every 2 minutes.
Add flour and cornstarch.
Cook 1 1/2 minutes or until bubbly.
Add stock and milk.
Stir until smooth.
Cook 18 minutes, stirring after 12 minutes.
Add soda, cheese and salt.
Cook 3 minutes.
Sprinkle parsley on top to serve.
Recipe yields 8 to 10 servings.

title: spinach artichoke dip
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix all ingredients and spoon into 9-inch pie plate.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes.
Sprinkle with sliced green onions.
Serve with tortilla chips.
Makes 2 cups.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Mix flour, sugar and cocoa.
Add a little milk, egg yolks and vanilla.
Mix well, then add the rest of the milk.
Cook until thickens.
Beat egg whites until stiff.
Add vanilla and 1/4 cup sugar.
Beat until real stiff.

title: fruit punch
directions: Combine pineapple, lemon, orange and lime juices, sugar and 1/2 of crushed mint leaves.
Chill.
Just before serving, add ginger ale, soda water, whole mint leaves and quartered strawberries.
Pour over large cake of ice in punch bowl.
Yields 75 cups.

title: edwin's spaghetti
directions: Cut oysters and saute with shrimp, shallots, garlic and butter in a skillet on medium heat for 10 minutes, constantly stirring.

title: tenderizer marinade(for steak or roast beef)
directions: Combine in glass jar and store in refrigerator.
Pour over your meat roast overnight; steak 4 hours.

title: fudgy cocoa brownies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease an 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan.
In medium saucepan melt shortening over low heat (or melt in microwave) in one quart container.
Remove melted shortening from heat; add cocoa and stir until well blended.
Add sugar and mix well.
Add eggs, one at a time, and beat well.
Stir in vanilla, flour and salt.
Do not overbeat.
Fold in nuts.
Spread in prepared pan and bake 25 to 30 minutes.
Frost as desired.

title: roasted vegetables
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
Cut 3/4-inch off top of garlic bulb, cutting through tip of each clove; discard top portion.
Wrap securely with foil.

title: squash casserole
directions: Wash and dice squash.
Simmer with chopped onion until tender. Drain.
Mix soups with sour cream until well blended.
Add squash and onion to soup mixture and lightly mix.
Place 1/2 the cornbread stuffing in the bottom of a 13 x 9-inch baking dish. Spoon 1/2 the squash mixture over stuffing.
Sprinkle 1/2 the cheese over soup.
Spoon remaining soup over cheese, then sprinkle remaining stuffing and cheese on top.
Bake at 375° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: frogmore stew(low country - south carolina)
directions: Place beer and bay leaves in large kettle or pot.
Cook sausage 1 1/2 hours at medium heat.
Add shrimp, corn-on-the-cob and clams.
Cook for additional 30 minutes.
Serve in bowls.

title: orange julius
directions: Place all ingredients, except ice, into blender.
Blend well, adding ice cubes one at a time, until blended thoroughly.
Yields 6 cups.

title: berry cream coffee cake
directions: Cut cream cheese and butter into biscuit mix until crumbly. Blend in 1/3 cup milk.
Turn onto floured surface; knead 8 to 10 strokes.
On waxed paper, roll dough to 12 x 8-inch rectangle. Turn onto greased baking sheet; remove paper.
Spread preserves down center of dough.
Make 2 1/2-inch cuts at 1-inch intervals on long sides.
Fold strips over filling (braid).
Bake in 425° oven for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: salted peanut bars
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pat into ungreased cookie sheet. Beat egg whites and 1/2 cup brown sugar. Spread on top of cookie mixture.
Sprinkle with salted peanuts and 1 cup chocolate chips. Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: blueberry salad
directions: Mix together and refrigerate until set.

title: squash casserole
directions: Mix squash, margarine, and cheese together.
Put stuffing mix in squash mixture and mix.
Add some milk to liquify.
Put in dish and sprinkle a little stuffing mix on top.
Bake at 325° for 15-20 minutes.

title: tuna fritters
directions: Combine flour, baking powder and salt.
Break up contents of tuna.
Add egg and milk.
Combine tuna mixture with dry ingredients.
Mix thoroughly.
Heat about 3/4-inch fat in large skillet and drop by heaping teaspoonfuls.
Cook 5 to 7 minutes until browned on all sides.
Drain on paper towel.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: First Layer:
Combine cream cheese, 1/4 cup sugar, vanilla and egg; mix well.
Spread on bottom of pie crust.

title: diet banana shake
directions: Process all ingredients in blender until smooth.
Serve immediately.
Makes 4 servings.

title: cheese biscuits
directions: Sift dry ingredients.
Add cheese.
Cut in shortening and milk to make a soft dough.
Place on a floured board and roll 1/2 inch thick.
Cut out biscuits.
Place on cookie sheet and bake 12 minutes at 450°.
Makes 14 biscuits.
Be sure and serve a little side dish with 1/4 cup melted hot garlic butter.
Just put them on the dish and smother them with butter and have plenty of napkins handy.

title: cheesy macaroni bake
directions: Cut Cheddar and Mozzarella cheese into cubes.
Cook macaroni until done; add fresh broccoli flowerets until done.
Drain. Return macaroni and broccoli to pan.
Add Cheddar cheese and Mozzarella cheese, bacon bits, mustard and salt.
Spoon mixture into a baking dish.
Pour milk evenly over top and bake until bubbly or golden, 18 to 21 minutes at 450°.

title: roast beef hash
directions: Make hash.
In medium bowl, toss roast beef with potatoes, green pepper, onion, salt, pepper, Worcestershire and bouillon until well combined.
Slowly heat butter in a heavy 10-inch skillet.
Spread hash in skillet.
Cook over medium heat, about 10 minutes or until hash is heated through and most of the liquid is absorbed.
Turn hash over occasionally with pancake turner, scraping bottom of skillet to remove brown bits, then spread evenly.
Reduce heat, cook uncovered, without stirring, about 40 minutes or until hash is very brown and crusty on the underside. Occasionally lift edge of hash with turner to test for brownness.

title: cranapple compote
directions: Combine 1 cup sugar and 1 cup water.
Bring to boil, add cranberries and reduce heat.
Cook until skins pop open.
Set aside.
Peel and slice apples.
Combine sugar and 1/3 cup water, add cinnamon and bring to a boil, stir to mix well.
Reduce heat. Add apples and cook until just tender.
Remove from heat.
Cool. Pour apples into bowl and add cranberry mixture on top.
Do not stir until next day.
Can be made ahead.
Will keep up to 3 weeks in refrigerator.

title: pecan treats
directions: Beat egg white and water until frothy, but not stiff.
Add pecans and mix until well coated.
Mix sugar, salt and cinnamon in a bowl.
Add coated nut mixture and stir.
Spread on buttered cookie sheet and bake 1 hour at 225°, stirring every 15 minutes. Cool.

title: zucchini stew
directions: Brown sausage, drain.
Add celery and simmer for 10 minutes. Add rest of ingredients, except green peppers.
Simmer 10 minutes. Last add green peppers.
Simmer 10 more minutes.

title: "big apple" pancakes
directions: Combine all dry ingredients.
Mix egg, milk and oil.
Add liquid to dry ingredients.
Add 1 cup chopped apples.
Fry in melted shortening or oil.
Serve with cinnamon and sugar on top. Yields 4 very large pancakes.

title: skillet italiano
directions: Brown beef with onion, garlic, oregano and salt in skillet. Add soup, water and vinegar; heat.
Stir in noodles and cheese; heat.

title: saturday night beans
directions: Put beans in a pot with a small amount of water.
Add mushrooms, red wine and garlic salt.
Bring to a boil and cover. Cook for about 20 minutes.

title: russian chicken
directions: Mix jelly, Russian dressing and soup mix.
Dip chicken into mixture.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes, until done.

title: egg drop soup
directions: Bring chicken broth to a boil.
While broth is heating, dissolve the cornstarch in water.
Slice the scallion (the white and edible green parts).
Beat the egg with the oil.
When the broth reaches the boiling point, stir cornstarch mixture and add it slowly to the broth.
Season with salt and pepper and add scallions.
Turn off heat and immediately add beaten egg in a steady stream, stirring broth constantly so egg breaks up into floaty bits.
Serves 4.

title: pasta salad
directions: Cook pasta and drain; mix all ingredients together.
Chill and it's ready to eat.

title: corn bread
directions: And as they were eating, Jesus took bread and gave it to the Disciples and said, "Take, eat; for this is my body."
And he took the cup and gave thanks and gave it to them saying, "Drink ye all of it; for this is my blood of the New Testament, which is shed for many for the remission of sins."
Matthew 26:

title: traditional sweet roll dough
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Stir in milk, sugar, eggs, shortening and 2 1/2 cups of the flour.
Beat until smooth.
Mix in enough remaining flour to make dough easy to handle.
Turn dough onto lightly floured board; knead until smooth and elastic, about 5 minutes.
Place in greased bowl, turn greased side up. (At this point, dough can be refrigerated 3 to 4 days.)
Cover and let rise in warm place until double, about 1 1/2 hours.
Dough is ready if impression remains when touched.
Punch down dough. Shape dough into desired rolls.
Cover and let rise until double, about 30 minutes.
Heat oven to 375°.
Bake as directed.

title: fresh peach frozen pie
directions: Blend peaches.
Combine all ingredients and place into two graham cracker crusts.
Freeze for four hours.
Take out five minutes before serving.

title: microwave baked apples
directions: Cut apples in half; core.
Melt butter in microwave in a small dish.
Add sugar, flour and cinnamon.
Spoon mixture evenly over apple halves.
Cover with plastic wrap, leaving a "vent". Microwave on High 5 minutes or until apples are tender.
Let set 5 minutes.
Sprinkle with miniature marshmallows.
Microwave just long enough to melt.

title: beef tips in oven
directions: Mix mushroom soup with 1/2 can of water.
Add all but a little of onion soup mix.
Sprinkle meat with seasoned salt, garlic salt and regular salt and pepper.
Put in mixture.
Bake in dish, covered with aluminum foil, for 3 hours at 300°.

title: strawberry-cheese delight
directions: Combine crumbs, 1/4 cup sugar and butter.
Press firmly in bottom of a 13 x 9-inch pan. Chill 15 minutes.

title: bell family punch
directions: *Can substitute different juice.

title: 90-minute rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in lukewarm water.
Add shortening, sugar, salt and enough flour to make a stiff dough.
Cover and let rise in a warm place about 50 minutes.
Turn out on a floured board.
Make into rolls.
Place in greased pan and allow to rise 20 minutes. Bake at 375° for 20 minutes.

title: pumpkin pudding
directions: Mix milk and pudding.
Fold in pumpkin pie filling.
Pour into cups or little tart shells.
Refrigerate for 5 minutes.

title: dirt cake
directions: Whip cream cheese; mix with pudding, sugar and Cool Whip. Slowly add 3 1/2 cups of milk.

title: rhubarb pie
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into a 9-inch pie crust.
Bake at 400° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: sweet potato salad
directions: Boil potatoes in water with a pinch of salt until just tender.
Drain and remove to a bowl.
Toss with lemon juice.
Add pecans, celery and dates.
In a small bowl, combine mayonnaise, orange peel, orange juice, honey, ginger, salt and nutmeg.
Pour dressing over warm potato mixture, stirring to coat well.
Cover and chill before serving.

title: peanut brittle
directions: In a large heavy boiler, put sugar, Karo and water.
Bring to a full rolling boil, then add peanuts.
Cook continually, stirring slow.
Listen for popping peanuts.
Cook until peanuts are lightly brown.
Add wax and melt it.
Add soda.
Stir fast.
Dump on board immediately and spread fast.
(Board should be 2 feet by 2 feet, covered with aluminum foil.)
Cool, then break in pieces. Seal in Ziploc bags or can be poured into 8 x 10-inch lightly buttered aluminum pans.

title: chicken and rice with almonds
directions: Rinse chicken with cold water and pat dry.
Place chicken in baking dish; sprinkle with salt, pepper and paprika.
Melt butter in saucepan.
Stir in remaining ingredients, except rice.
Pour over chicken.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until done.
Serve with rice.

title: hot taco dip
directions: Mix together all ingredients, except chips.
Put in crock-pot and cook 3 to 4 hours.
Serve with Doritos or taco chips.

title: chocolate cake
directions: Sift together first 5 ingredients.
Make 3 holes and put oil in one, vanilla in one and vinegar in last hole.
Pour water over all and mix well.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: hot dog chili
directions: While beans are cooking, in a separate pot combine margarine, beef, onions, garlic and vinegar; cook on high temperature to brown meat and onions.
When beans are tender, drain and add all ingredients together.
Cook awhile on low temperature.
Serve with a 16 ounce Double cola.

title: people puppy chow
directions: Melt peanut butter, chocolate chips and butter together.
Add cereal and stir.
Make sure all cereal is coated with chocolate mixture.
Then put in refrigerator for 10 to 15 minutes.
Put confectioners sugar in a clean trash bag.
Dump chocolate mixture in and mix until all is covered and white.
Then eat.

title: fish batter
directions: Add water to make desired thickness of batter.

title: cranberry sweet potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Drain sweet potatoes; chop into smaller chunks and place into a large casserole dish.
Stir in cranberry sauce.
In separate bowl, combine remaining ingredients and mix to make a crumble mixture.
Stir half of the crumble mixture into the sweet potato and cranberry sauce mixture.
Reserve the other half of the crumble mixture to sprinkle on top of the dish.
Bake for 30 minutes, uncovered.

title: sausage balls
directions: Combine ingredients with hands.
Shape into small balls (pecan size).
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Remove from pan onto paper towels until cool.
Makes approximately 100.

title: hamburger salami
directions: Mix all together.
Use your hands & work spices in really well.
Shape into 5 rolls & wrap in foil.
Bake in pan with sides on it because this loses grease while it's baking.	Bake at 325° for 1 1/4 hours.

title: fruit salad with honey ginger dressing
directions: Mix the sour cream, honey, ginger and cinnamon together in a small bowl.
Makes 1 cup.
Pour over fresh, cut up fruit.

title: rockport red sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients well and chill.
Makes approximately 1 cup sauce.
Contains approximately 13 calories per tablespoon.

title: mom's dumplings(yields 10 servings)
directions: Put flour in a large bowl.
Cut in shortening.
Stir in pepper.
Add egg and liquid.
Blend until all flour is moist. Roll out dough on floured board.
Roll dough to about 1/4-inch thick.
Cut rolled dough into small pieces (2 x 3-inch).
Set aside.
Bring stock to a boil and drop dumplings in, one at a time, until all is added.
Drop heat to simmer and cook for about 30 minutes.

title: quick stew
directions: Brown ground beef in a large saucepan over medium heat.
Add rest of ingredients.
Stir and heat until bubbly, about 20 minutes.

title: chip stuffed eggs
directions: Fry bacon crisp and crumble into small pieces.
Cut eggs in half lengthwise and remove yolks.
Mix mashed yolks with bacon, mayonnaise, parsley and chips.
Fill the egg halves and sprinkle with paprika for color.

title: jello cake
directions: Sift cake mix and Jell-O together.
Add milk and oil alternately.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each one. Stir in flavor.
Pour into Bundt pan and bake in preheated oven (350°) about 45 minutes or until done.

title: cream of broccoli soup
directions: Combine first 8 ingredients in large saucepan. Bring to a boil, stirring constantly for 1 minute. Add broccoli, milk, cheese and margarine. Cook on low heat until cheese melts and mixture is thoroughly heated. Garnish with cheese. This recipe is easily doubled.

title: sausage-cheese balls(excellent appetizers!)
directions: Mix together thoroughly.
Makes very stiff dough so you may have to use your hands to mix.
Roll into one-inch balls.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet and bake at 400°.
Makes about 6 dozen.

title: autumn apples
directions: Arrange sliced apples in pie crust.
(Pierce crust several times with fork to release air bubbles as it cooks.) Combine topping ingredients and sprinkle evenly over apples.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes until apples are tender.

title: frozen strawberry daiquiri
directions: Thaw strawberries enough to cut in chunks.
Place in blender. Add mix and rum.
Cover and blend.
While blender is running, add ice cubes, a few at a time, blending until ice is melted.
Pour into trays or 1/2 gallon plastic container.
Cover and freeze several hours or overnight.
It will not freeze firm.
Spoon into cocktail or sherbet glasses.
Garnish with fresh strawberries. Store, covered, in freezer to use as needed.
Makes 5 cups.

title: butter pecan white chocolate truffles
directions: Melt chocolate, butter and water in the top of a double boiler over hot water, stirring constantly until smooth.
Pour mixture into mixing bowl; add egg yolk and beat with electric mixer until fluffy and cooled to warm temperature (about 5 minutes).
Place mixture on flat baking pan and cool in the refrigerator.
Scrape a spoon across the surface of the mixture and quickly press into small balls.
Roll balls into nuts and place in a paper candy cup.
Keep refrigerated until ready to serve.
Wrap in several thicknesses of aluminum foil to store.

title: judy mundy's orange sauce
directions: In a small saucepan mix cornstarch, brown sugar, nutmeg, orange juice, margarine and parsley.
Cook until thick and pour over cooked cauliflower.

title: tortilla wedges
directions: Mix cream cheese, sour cream and onions.
Spread on top of tortilla.
Top with another spread mixture, and so on, until you have 5 tortillas layered high.
Wrap in plastic wrap and refrigerate for 3 hours or overnight.
Cut stacks into wedges. Serve with warm salsa for dipping.
Very spicy!
Makes 30 to 40 wedges.

title: 1930 lettuce soup
directions: Chop lettuce very fine.
Chop celery, onion and green pepper any size you like.
I use a food processor.
Cook until vegetables are tender in canned chicken stock.
I use broth that is 1/3 less salt.
You can add pasta or noodles, also.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: Saute onion and celery in butter.
Add chicken and chilies. Spread on tortillas.
Mix 1 cup sour cream and soup.
Cover with mixture and cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: yummy angel food cherry delight
directions: In a 9 x 13-inch pan, alternate layers of bite size pieces of angel food cake, lite cherry pie filling and lite Cool Whip. Chill several hours before serving.
Best when chilled overnight. Yields 15 servings.
"Enjoy."

title: green temple creamed tofu sauce(this recipe makes about 1 gallon of sauce.)
directions: Blend all ingredients together until smooth and creamy, then add dried parsley flakes or chopped fresh parsley.

title: hummingbird cake
directions: Sift all dry ingredients.
Set aside.
Beat eggs.
Add oil and vanilla.
Blend in dry ingredients.
Beat about 2 minutes.
Fold in bananas, pineapple and nuts.
Bake at 350° for about 50 minutes.
Cool and then frost.

title: round steak parmesan
directions: Cut
meat
into
serving
pieces;
salt
and	pepper. Combine Parmesan
cheese
and bread crumbs.
Dip meat into egg and then
coat with cheese mixture.
Heat oil in a skillet and fry meat
pieces
until
brown.
In
another pan, fry onion in butter until soft; add remaining ingredients except Mozzarella cheese. Boil
a
few
minutes.
In a casserole, layer half of sauce with meat, then add all the Mozzarella cheese.
Top with rest of
sauce and
bake,
uncovered, at 350° for 30 minutes. Serves 6.
My favorite!

title: salsa sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients together in large cooking pan and simmer several hours until thick.
Pour into sterilized pint jars and seal.

title: four layer dessert
directions: Mix and pat in bottom of oblong pan.
Bake 15 minutes at 350° or until light brown.
Cool.

title: salmon patties
directions: Mix all ingredients in a bowl.
Round into patties.
Heat vegetable oil and fry until golden brown.
Makes 6 to 7 patties.

title: baked spaghetti
directions: Cook spaghetti and drain.
Cook hamburger and drain, then add spaghetti sauce and tomato sauce to cooked hamburger.
In a baking dish, put a layer of spaghetti, then hamburger and sauce.
Then add some cheese.
Layer spaghetti sauce.
Top with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: auntie millie's lasagna
directions: In a large pot, brown hamburger in olive oil. Remove sausage from casing, crumble and brown with hamburger.
Crush garlic and saute with meat. Add tomato paste, tomatoes with liquid, water and seasonings. Simmer slowly for 4 hours.
Should have a nice thick consistency.
Grate all cheeses.
In lasagna pan, coated with sauce, layer as follows:
noodles (cooked al dente per package directions), edges overlapped, sauce, cheeses (drop Ricotta by teaspoonful);
make 3 layers, ending with cheese.
Bake, covered, 1 hour in a 350° oven. Remove cover the last 20 minutes to brown.

title: cranberry jello mold
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in a bowl of water.
Add juice and cranberries.
Chill until slightly thickened.
Add walnuts and apples; stir in.
Pour in a mold.

title: margaret bailey's sour cream pound cake
directions: Sift together the flour, salt, soda and baking powder. Separate eggs.
Cream the butter.
Add sugar.
Cream well in a large bowl until light, then add egg yolks and beat again.
Add flour alternately with sour cream.
Beat egg whites until stiff. Fold into the mixture by hand.
Add flavorings.
Bake at 300° for about 1 hour and 45 minutes if using a tube pan (greased and floured).
May be baked in 2 loaf pans.
It is better not to cut until the next day after baking.
(The cake becomes moist as it ripens.) Freezes well.

title: mexican cheesecake
directions: Preheat oven to 350.
Combine chips and butter.
Press mixture into bottom of a greased 9-inch spring form pan.
Bake 10 minutes.
Combine cream cheese and jack cheese in a food processor.
Add eggs and 1/2 cup sour ream and pulse to combine. Add green chilies and picante sauce.
Pulse again to thoroughly combine.
Pour cheese mixture over crust and spread evenly.
Place pan on a baking sheet and bake 40 minutes.
Spread remaining 1/2 cup sour cream on hot cheesecake.
Cool to room temperature and chill.

title: chocolate chess pie
directions: Mix cocoa and sugar.
Add eggs and mix.
Add margarine and mix well.
Add milk and vanilla.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake for 35 to 45 minutes at 350°.

title: spicy sausage dip
directions: Brown pork sausage; drain. Add Ro-Tel tomatoes and cream cheese. Heat through. Serve with chips or crackers.

title: spinach salad and dressing
directions: Mix onion, oil, vinegar, sugar, yellow mustard and celery salt together.
Let this mixture refrigerate for 1 or more hours. Serve over spinach salad and top with other toppings.

title: richer biscuits
directions: Sift together flour, baking powder and salt.
Cut in shortening.
It should look like meal.
Add milk and mix.
Drop with tablespoon on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 450° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Makes 10 (2-inch) biscuits.

title: oatmeal carmelitas
directions: Melt caramels in evaporated milk in heavy saucepan.
Cool slightly.
Combine remaining ingredients except butterscotch bits and nuts in large mixing bowl.
Press half of crumbs into bottom of greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Remove from oven.
Sprinkle with butterscotch bits and nuts.
Spread carefully with caramel mixture.
Sprinkle with remaining crumb mixture.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes longer or until golden brown.
Chill 1 to 2 hours before cutting into bars.

title: better than chocolate cake
directions: Mix cake mix, vanilla pudding, water and oil. Add eggs and beat well after each addition. Add sour cream, nuts, chocolate bar and coconut. Put in tube pan (greased). Bake 50 to 55 minutes at 350°.

title: tv snacks
directions: Mix well.
Bake in a 300° oven about 1 hour.
Turn or stir often, about every 15 minutes.

title: hungarian-style goulash
directions: About 2 1/2 hours before serving, in 5-quart Dutch oven, over medium-high heat, in hot margarine or butter, cook onions until lightly browned.
Add meat, paprika and salt.
Reduce heat to low. Cover and simmer 1 1/2 to 2 hours until meat is fork-tender.

title: vinegar pie
directions: Melt margarine.
Add sugar, then add beaten eggs, vinegar, milk, flour and vanilla and bake at 350° in preheated oven until done.

title: chris' favorite baked beans
directions: Mix all ingredients, except bacon.
Pour into baking dish. Top with bacon slices.
Bake at 400° for about 45 minutes. Serves 6.

title: cucumber dip
directions: Blend all together, adding enough mayonnaise to make dipable.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Divide into 2 graham cracker crusts and freeze.
Serve frozen.

title: twinkie cake
directions: Slice 5 Twinkies lengthwise.
Place, cream side up, in dish. Add sliced bananas.
Add crushed pineapple, drained.
Add Cool Whip.
Dot with cherries.
Chill 2 hours before serving.

title: microwave hot bean dip
directions: Using scissors, snip bacon into small pieces into a 2-quart casserole. Microwave at High (10) for 3 to 4 minutes. Remove bacon and drain well.

title: squash medley
directions: Parboil squash (zucchini for three minutes, yellow crooknecks or small white pattypans for five minutes).
If you use frozen squash, do not parboil.

title: salmon croquettes
directions: Beat eggs. Add salmon and onion. Add salt and pepper. Stir in enough crumbs to mold firmly. Fry in hot grease until brown on both sides.

title: lemon delight
directions: Mix first 2 ingredients until crumbly.
Add nuts.
Pat in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 15 minutes at 400°.
Take out.
Crumble up and repack in pan.
Cool in refrigerator.
Whip cream cheese, powdered sugar and 1/2 cup Cool Whip.
Put on cool crust bottom.
Add 1 1/2 to 2 cans lemon pudding on pie filling on top of cream cheese mixture.
Add rest of Cool Whip on top of pudding.
Sprinkle with crushed nuts.

title: filling balls
directions: Mix the bread cubes, beaten eggs, butter, salt, pepper, celery and onion together.
Add enough milk to make mixture wet.
Grease pan.
Take filling and put loosely into loaf cake dish.
Mix the chicken gravy and same amount (1 can) of milk.
Pour over filling. Take a fork and punch holes in filling so the gravy will go all through the filling.
Bake at 325° until done, about 1 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: apple cider biscuits
directions: Heat oven to 450°.
Combine dry ingredients; add butter with pastry blender until it resembles coarse crumbs.
Stir in cider just until soft dough forms that leaves the side of the bowl. Knead into a ball and pat out to 1/2-inch thickness.
Cut biscuits with 2 1/2-inch biscuit cutter.
Place biscuits 1 inch apart on cookie sheet (ungreased); sprinkle with cinnamon.
Pierce top with fork.
Bake 12 to 15 minutes, or until golden brown.
Makes 8.

title: chicken marsala
directions: Shake chicken and flour in bag until coated.
In 10 x 10 x 2-inch pan, place coated chicken.
Sprinkle onion and mushrooms over top of chicken.
Add seasonings.
Pour wine over mixture. Pour tomato sauce over.
Put in 350° oven for 1 1/2 hours, turning periodically, until golden brown.
Serves 6.

title: eggs tetrazzini
directions: Cook spaghetti according to package directions.
Drain thoroughly.
Heat oil in skillet.
Add onion, celery and green pepper.
Cook slowly for 5 minutes.
Blend in flour and seasonings.
Add milk and stir until thickened.
Dice two of the eggs into the sauce.
Pile spaghetti on hot platter.
Top with hot sauce.
Slice remaining eggs over sauce.

title: baked apples
directions: Peel and core apples.
Slice thin.
Bring sugars and water to a boil; thicken with cornstarch. Add vanilla and a little red food coloring.
Pour over apples at 350 degrees for 25 minutes uncovered or at a lower temperature 1 hour.

title: india relish
directions: Choose firm green cucumbers 6-inches long and 1 1/4-inches in diameter and tomatoes that have whitish color just before ripening. Wash vegetables.
Quarter tomatoes and cucumbers and put through food chopper, using the coarse blade.
Put into glass or enamel bowl, add salt and let stand overnight.
Place in colander, press out and discard liquid.
Add next 4 vegetables and remaining ingredients.
Simmer 10 minutes.
Stir occasionally.
Pour into jars and seal.
Makes 4 1/2 pints.

title: old-fashioned oatmeal cookies
directions: Simmer raisins and water over medium heat until raisins are plump, about 15 minutes.
Drain raisins, reserving the liquid. Add enough water to reserved liquid to measure 1/2 cup.
Heat oven to 400°.
Mix thoroughly shortening, sugar, eggs and vanilla. Stir in reserved liquid.
Blend in remaining ingredients.
Drop dough by rounded teaspoonfuls about 2 inches apart onto ungreased baking sheet.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes or until light brown.
Makes about 3 dozen.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix together. Let stand overnight. Form into a ball and roll in pecans.

title: old-fashioned lemonade
directions: Boil sugar and water in a small saucepan for 5 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Remove from heat and stir in lemon juice. Cool, then pour into jar and refrigerate.
To serve, stir 2 tablespoons syrup into three-fourths cup water.
Add ice.
Makes enough for 20 servings.

title: three cheese enchiladas
directions: Combine 1 cup Monterey Jack cheese, 1 cup Cheddar cheese, cream cheese, 1/4 cup picante sauce, chilies and cumin; mix well. Spoon cheese mixture down the center of each tortilla.
Roll and place, seam side down, in a 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Spoon remaining picante sauce evenly over enchiladas.
Cover with the remaining cheeses.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes, or until hot. Top with lettuce, tomato and black olives.
Yields 5 servings.

title: chicken dumplings
directions: Mix eggs, water, salt, flour and oil well and roll out very thin.
Cut into 2-inch squares.
Drop into boiling broth and add pepper to taste.
Cover pan and cook for 15 minutes over low heat. Do not remove cover until time is up.
Add chicken and heat, if needed.

title: rice and black-eyed pea casserole
directions: Cook pork or bulk sausage, onion and bell pepper for 30 minutes on low heat.
Add ham, green onion and garlic; cook 30 minutes.

title: sweet-sour chicken
directions: Place chicken pieces in shallow baking dish.
Mix dressing with soup mix and preserves in small amount of water.
Pour over chicken and bake 1 1/2 hours in 350° oven or until chicken is tender.
Good with cooked rice and green vegetable.
Serves 4.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Mix together sugar, butter and milk.
Bring to a boil; remove from the heat.
Add oatmeal, peanut butter, cocoa and vanilla. Mix together.
Drop by spoonfuls onto waxed paper.
Let set at least 30 minutes.

title: cheese ball
directions: Beat in mixer.
Form into a ball and roll in finely chopped nuts.

title: food pyramid party mix
directions: Mix well in bowl.
Serves 3 people (1 cup each).

title: squash casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients, except small amount of cheese and bread crumbs.
Pour in greased casserole dish.
Sprinkle with the extra cheese and bread crumbs.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 30 minutes or until slightly brown on top.

title: chicken and wild rice salad
directions: Toss chopped, cooked chicken with the cooked wild rice.
Add any of the optional ingredients, then mix in the mayonnaise, mustard and vinegar.
Chill.

title: pizza casserole
directions: Cook noodles, brown hamburger with oregano, onions and drain in large bowl.
Add soups, pizza sauce and mushrooms to noodles and hamburger in large casserole pan (greased).
Put layer of pepperoni, then noodles.
Repeat; add cheese, then put the 1 pound shredded Mozzarella cheese on top.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Add graham cracker crumbs and peanut butter to melted butter. Add salt and vanilla.
Blend in 10x sugar.
Mix well and press into 13 x 9-inch pan.
Cool, but do not refrigerate.
Melt chocolate chips and spread over top.
Cool at room temperature and cut into 1-inch squares.

title: taco pie
directions: Spread rolls over bottom and sides of a 9 x 13-inch pan. Brown ground beef with taco seasoning.
Layer chips and meat. Spread sour cream over meat; add cheese and rest of chips.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Serve with chopped lettuce and tomatoes.

title: cranberry fruit-nut bread
directions: Mix together flour, sugar, baking powder and soda.
Cut in shortening until mixture resembles coarse corn meal.
Combine orange juice and grated orange rind with well beaten egg.
Pour all at once into dry ingredients.
Mix until smooth.
Fold in chopped nuts and cranberries.

title: dream cake
directions: Boil the sugar and pineapple together for 5 minutes.
Pour over hot cake and let cool.
Make up the vanilla pudding as directed on box. Slice the bananas thin and add to the pudding. Spread over pineapple layer.
Spread Cool Whip over the pudding layer. Sprinkle coconut and chopped nuts over top.
Keep leftovers in refrigerator.

title: grape butter
directions: Wash and crush grapes.
Separate hulls and pulp.
Heat pulp with juice and put through a colander to remove seeds; grind hulls in a food chopper using fine blade.
Combine deseeded pulp, juice and hulls.
Cook until hulls are tender.
Add sugar and spices. Cook very slowly, stirring repeatedly until the mixture is very thick and has a jelly-like consistency.
Pack in hot, sterilized jars and seal.
Yield:
about 8 pints.

title: freezer pickles(makes 6 packages)
directions: Slice cucumbers and onions real thin.
Place in a large bowl, covered with ice water, 2 tablespoons salt and 1/4 teaspoon alum. Let stand in refrigerator overnight.
Heat sugar and vinegar until sugar is dissolved.
Cool.
Drain cucumbers and onions.
Cover with vinegar solution.
Fill Ziploc bags and freeze.

title: red jello
directions: Do not drain anything.
Combine Jell-O and water, then add frozen berries when slightly cool, to thaw.
Then add marshmallows and last, rest of ingredients after cool.

title: tropical coolers
directions: In blender container, combine all ingredients.
Cover; blend 30 to 60 seconds or until smooth.
Serve immediately.

title: super bubbles
directions: The glycerine makes these bubbles so super.
With the 4 parts glycerine, these bubbles can be used in a hula hoop, etc. to make truly, huge, long lasting bubbles.
Store in a tightly covered jar and enjoy all summer.

title: carbanara
directions: Cook spaghetti.
Mix alfredo, cream cheese, bacon bits and water.
Put cooked spaghetti in oblong dish, 13 x 9.
Pour mixture over the spaghetti and mix slightly.
Add shredded Mozzarella or Provolone cheese on top and bake until starts to brown.

title: coconut cake
directions: Combine cake mix, water, eggs and oil in a large mixing bowl. Blend.
Beat at medium speed for 4 minutes.
Stir in coconut and nuts.
Pour into greased and floured 10-inch tube pan.
Bake at 325° for 60 minutes or until done.
Cool 15 minutes.
Remove from pan and cool on rack.

title: pecan pie dessert bars
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients.
Press in greased pan. Bake 15 to 20 minutes at 350°.
Use a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: punch
directions: Put cherries and bananas in blender and grind to fine pulp. Pour into gallon jar.
Add gelatin (dissolved in boiling water), juices, sugar and water. Chill.
Just before serving, add ginger ale and sherbet.
Will serve about 50 punch cups.
Another 46-ounce can of orange juice and quart of ginger ale may be added to serve more people without impairing flavor.

title: it
directions: Mix rice, soup, soup mix, mushrooms and water together.
Pour into a 9 x 12-inch baking pan.
Set aside.
Brown chicken in margarine.
Place chicken on top of rice mixture.
Pour remaining margarine over the chicken.
Cover with foil.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour 15 minutes.

title: chocolate leaves
directions: To decorate cake, gather 20 to 30 rose leaves from garden. Wash thoroughly and dry leaves.
Melt an 8 ounce milk chocolate candy bar in double boiler.
Lay waxed paper on cookie sheet.
Hold leaf in hand; put chocolate on the underneath side with knife or paint brush.
Put in refrigerator.
When chocolate has hardened, peel off rose leaves.
Place chocolate leaves in storage container in refrigerator until needed for decorating.

title: shake and bake
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Can be used for baked chicken, pork chops, etc.

title: pork chop casserole
directions: Line
pan
with pork chops.
Add cut up vegetables (cut up like
you would for a roast).
Pour mushroom soup on top of all vegetables	and chops.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes, until vegetables	are
done.
Makes
pork
chops fall off the bone.

title: baked whitefish and spinach(makes 4 servings at 142 calories each and 3.4 grams fat)
directions: *Hint:
Don't forget about soaking in buttermilk for 4 to 6 hours or overnight to improve flavor.

title: texas brownies
directions: Boil margarine, cocoa and milk.
Add sugar, nuts and vanilla.

title: cherry chocolate cake
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour into 9 x 13 greased pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Test for doneness. Cool.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Heat water to a boil.
Add lemon jello and tomato soup.
Whip smooth.
Add cream cheese and whip smooth.
Add remaining items. Whip until smooth.
Chill until ready to serve.
You can put in hawaiian bread and serve.

title: aunt dee's rolls
directions: Scald milk; add shortening and melt.
Let cool.
Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Sprinkle 1 tablespoon sugar over yeast mixture.
Beat eggs and add to milk.
Add 1/2 cup sugar and salt. Add this to yeast mixture.
Blend in flour.
Let rise until double.
Punch down and shape.
Let rise until double again.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Makes 2 pans of rolls anyway you want.

title: strawberry fluff
directions: For crust, in bottom of 8 x 10-inch cake pan, mix flour, brown sugar, nuts and oleo.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until brown, stirring occasionally, to make crumbs.
Reserve a few for top.

title: coconut ice cream
directions: Finely chop flaked coconut.
In large bowl, with wire whisk or fork, beat coconut, cream of coconut, half and half, light corn syrup and 2 cups of water until smooth.
Pour coconut mixture into 9 x 9-inch metal baking pan.
Cover pan with foil or plastic wrap. Freeze until partially frozen, about 3 hours, stirring occasionally.
Spoon mixture into chilled large bowl; with mixer and chilled beaters, at medium speed, beat mixture until smooth but still frozen.
Return mixture to pan; cover and freeze until firm, about 3 hours.
To serve, let frozen cream stand at room temperature for 10 to 15 minutes to soften slightly for easier scooping.
Garnish with coconut ruffles and mint sprigs.
Makes 5 cups or 8 servings.

title: crustless quiche
directions: Spray quiche pan with cooking spray. Spread cheese over bottom of pan.
Sprinkle
meat and vegetables over the cheese. Put remaining ingredients
into
blender
for
1 minute.
Pour over cheese mixture in
pan.
Bake at 350° about 35 minutes or until set.
Serves 6.

title: sausage snacks
directions: In a large bowl, mix ingredients by hand; roll into small balls and bake in 9 x 13-inch pan at about 350° (+/-) for 10 to 15 minutes or until brown.
Makes about 3 dozen.

title: old fashioned hot chocolate
directions: Combine chocolate, sugar, salt and water in saucepan.
Cook over low heat, stirring constantly, 5 minutes, or until chocolate is melted.
Stir in milk slowly; heat just until piping hot. Serve with whipped cream or marshmallows.

title: chicken salad
directions: Mix together and cool.

title: turkey casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients, except chow mein noodles and slivered almonds,
and place in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Cover with the chow mein noodles and almonds.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 1 hour.
(If frozen, bake, uncovered, at 400° for 70 minutes. Serves 12.

title: hot seafood salad
directions: Set crab and shrimp aside.
Combine remaining ingredients. Fold in seafood.
Spoon into lightly greased casserole.
Toss bread crumbs with butter.
Sprinkle over casserole.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes or until browned.

title: cheese cookies
directions: Mix margarine and cheese.
Add flour, a little at a time. Stir in Rice Krispies and form into small balls.
Place on cookie sheet and press with fork that has been dipped in flour.
Bake at 325° to 350° for 20 minutes.

title: spinach bread dip
directions: Combine all ingredients and let stand at least 4 hours.
Place in hollowed out round bread on a plate with cut pieces of bread placed around it.

title: imperial crab casserole
directions: Mix well.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Place beans in 3-quart casserole.
Microwave on High 15 minutes; drain.
Add soup and milk; mix well.
Now, add onion rings.
Microwave on High 15 minutes.

title: onion casserole
directions: Stir and saute onions in 1/2 cup butter.
Place in greased 9 x 13 baking dish.
Place over onions:
1/2 lb baby Swiss cheese, sliced or grated, 1 can undiluted cream of chicken soup.
Butter slices of French bread and place on top.
Bake until bread browns and casserole bubbles.
Bake at 350° for 25-30 minutes.

title: potato casserole
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Brown hamburger with 2 tablespoons minced onion.
Put the potatoes from the boxes in a large pan.
Add remaining minced onion, butter and cheese mixes from box of potatoes.
Add the 8 cups of boiling water, milk and sour cream. Stir until well mixed.
Bake for 50 minutes until golden brown on top.
This makes enough for a large group of people.

title: zucchini and tomatoes
directions: Slice zucchini in thin-medium slices.
Layer ingredients in microwave-safe dish in this order:
zucchini (2 layers), Parmesan (sprinkle), tomato (1 layer) and dollops of butter or margarine. Repeat layers until desired quantity.
Microwave at High for 10 to 20 minutes.
Serves 4 to 8.
So simply, it's hard to believe how delicious this dish is!

title: arlene's fruit cake
directions: Grease pan and dust with flour.
Mix all ingredients.
Bake at 250° for 1 hour and 20 minutes.

title: chocolate pound cake
directions: Cream together batter and shortening. Add sugar and mix well. Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each. Add vanilla. Combine dry ingredients; add alternately with milk to creamed mixture. Bake in greased 10-inch tube pan at 325° for 80 minutes.

title: creamy onion dip
directions: Thoroughly combine sour cream, mayo, onion mix and parsley. Cover and chill until serving time.
Serve with chips or crackers.

title: easy banana pudding
directions: Mix lemon juice and eagle brand milk.
Mix puddings and milk until thickened.
When milk has thickened, mix into pudding mixture.
Mix in cool whip.
In large bowl, layer in this order: graham crackers, sliced bananas, pudding mix.
Should make 3 layers.

title: steamed christmas pudding
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Beat in eggs and vanilla; stir in carrots, fruit and nuts.
Sift flour, soda and salt; stir into creamed mixture.
Add crumbs; mix well.
Spoon into well-oiled 1 1/2-quart mold.
Cover securely with mold lid or several thicknesses of waxed paper tied in place with string.
Place mold on a rack in covered kettle of boiling water (water should come halfway up on the mold).
Steam for 3 hours.
Unmold pudding onto serving plate.

title: chocolate oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients to a rolling boil.
Add remaining ingredients.
Drop by teaspoon on wax paper or buttered cookie sheet. Makes 2 dozen.

title: buttermilk fudge
directions: Put buttermilk and soda in kettle.
Let stand 3 minutes.
Add sugar, cocoa and butter and cook to soft ball stage.
Remove; beat until creamy.
Add vanilla and nuts.
Stir until mixed.
Pour into buttered pan.

title: potato salad
directions: Boil potatoes in water until soft; drain and mash.
Add chopped eggs, sweet pickles, onion, salt, mustard and mayonnaise. Mix well.
What you want is a rich consistency with a pale yellow color.
Add some pickle juice if more liquid is needed.
To fancy it up, save an egg or two, slice and arrange neatly on top. Sprinkle with paprika or dill seeds.
Sliced pickles look good too.
You can make more or less just by varying the amounts of the ingredients used.

title: mexican cheese dip
directions: Melt cheese; chop other ingredients and mix in.
If less hot dip is wanted, wash seeds out of jalapeno pepper.
Cook in crock-pot on low.

title: biscuits
directions: Melt oleo in pan.
Add all ingredients together. Don't knead too much. Roll out desired thickness.
Place biscuits in pan with melted oleo.
Bake at 375°.
When baked, brush with melted oleo.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli until tender; drain. Add remaining ingredients, except crackers. Mix well and pour in casserole dish. Sprinkle crackers over top and bake in 350° oven for 30 to 35 minutes or microwave on High approximately 20 minutes.

title: jerome cookies
directions: Line a 9 x 13-inch pan with whole graham crackers.
Melt the butter.
Combine the egg, sugar and condensed milk with the butter.
Bring this mixture to a rolling boil, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat and add the nuts, coconut and graham cracker crumbs.
Spread this over the graham crackers in the pan. Cover with whole graham crackers.

title: chicken spaghetti casserole
directions: Cook the spaghetti.
Saute the mushrooms, onion, green pepper, celery and garlic.
Add the tomatoes and olives.
Add the chicken and cooked spaghetti.
Turn into shallow baking dish.
Cover with grated cheese; heat for 20 to 30 minutes.
Can be made a day ahead.
Tastes even better if it sets awhile before heating.

title: sugarless apple pie
directions: Mix cornstarch, salt and cinnamon with apple juice.
Slice butter over top of sliced apples in a 9 x 13-inch glass dish. Pour juice mixture over apples and microwave for 15 minutes, until fork-tender.
Cool for 20 to 30 minutes.
Then add to shell. Refrigerate before serving.
Top with Cool Whip or ice cream, if desired.

title: apple and yam casserole
directions: Slice apples and yams.
Place a layer of apples first in a buttered 9 x 13-inch casserole dish.
Place small dots of butter in each apple slice.
Season each layer by sprinkling spices over each.
Layer apples and yams with brown sugar until all ingredients are used.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: cranberry sauce
directions: Pick over and wash cranberries and place in saucepan together with sugar, orange rind and juice and spices.
Bring to a boil, stir, cover and boil just until the cranberries burst, 4 to 5 minutes.
Sauce jells when cold.
Makes about 2 quarts.

title: raisin cookies
directions: Cook raisins in water until water is nearly absorbed.
Cool. Add baking soda.
Cream sugar and shortening and add to raisins. Add eggs and dry ingredients which have been sifted together. Drop by greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes. Makes 75 cookies.

title: corn salad
directions: Combine corn, cucumbers, onion and tomatoes in salad bowl. Blend sour cream with mayonnaise.
Add remaining ingredients.
Add sour cream mixture to corn mixture. Toss gently to coat vegetables.
Chill thoroughly.

title: brownies
directions: Melt butter and pour over all ingredients except chips.
Mix well until smooth and add chocolate chips.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes in a 13 x 9-inch greased pan.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix all and pour in greased casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until done.

title: cabbage burger bake
directions: Shred cabbage.
Spread half in buttered dish or pan.
Fry bacon until crisp.
Drain on paper towels.
Stir onion and rice into bacon drippings.
Cook over medium heat until onion is soft and rice is brown.
Spoon over cabbage.
Brown meat.
Spoon over rice.
Season with salt and pepper.
Top with remaining cabbage. Pour spaghetti sauce slowly over cabbage.
Top with bacon slices. Cover.
Bake at 400°
for 50 minutes.
Uncover and bake 10 minutes longer.
Makes 6 servings.

title: beef and macaroni casserole
directions: Prepare dinner to package directions.
Cook meat until lightly browned.
Add onions and green pepper.
Cook until tender.
Add tomato paste, water and macaroni.
Pour into 2-quart casserole. Top with cheese.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes or until bubbly hot and cheese melts.
Serves 8.

title: concordia hamburger cheese bake
directions: Cook noodles according to package directions.
Mix together first 6 ingredients.
Layer into 9 x 9-inch glass baking pan the noodles, cheese and meat mixture (like lasagna).
Sprinkle cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes (if you use a larger pan, it will be less thick).

title: rice and bacon dish
directions: Place all ingredients in heavy saucepan with tight fitting lid; bring to full boil.
Stir; reduce heat.
Simmer for 20 minutes; remove from heat.
Let set for 5 to 10 minutes.

title: steak potage
directions: In a heavy 3 or 4-quart pan, brown hamburger, stirring to crumble.
Add onions, carrots, canned tomatoes, water, bouillon cubes, pepper, salt and mixed veggies.
Bring to a boil; cook for 1 to 2 hours.
At the end, melt oleo and mix in the flour. Thicken the soup with the mixture, stirring until thickened. Serve with biscuits or rolls.

title: golden syrup walnut pie
directions: Mix all ingredients except walnuts.
Stir in walnuts. Pour into 9-inch unbaked pastry shell.
Bake in 400° oven 15 minutes. Reduce heat to 350° and bake 30 to 35 minutes longer.
Filling should be slightly less set in center than around the edges.

title: ham hot dish
directions: Cook noodles in boiling, salted water. Add cheese to hot white sauce. Add onions celery and mushrooms (browned in butter). Add noodles, ham, salt and pepper to taste. Turn into greased baking dish and cover with buttered crumbs. Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix cream of chicken soup and sour cream together.
Add chunked chicken breasts.
Cover with crushed crackers and dot with oleo.
Bake 45 minutes.

title: pinto bean casserole
directions: Heat oven to 325°.
Brown ground beef; drain and set aside.
In a casserole dish, pour in pinto beans (don't drain).
Pour in Hunt's tomato sauce.
Add package of cheese; mix well together. Prepare cornbread mix following directions on back of package.
Mix cornbread using just a little more milk than package calls for, making the batter a little thinner.
Pour cornbread mix on top of beans and bake in oven until bread is brown on top.
Ovens vary so cooking time will vary.

title: my mom's zuppa(hearty vegetable soup)
directions: Put all ingredients (raw) in large kettle, except kidney beans. Take 1 1/2 cans kidney beans and puree in food processor. Add remaining beans whole.
Add drippings.
Cook until all veggies are cooked to your taste.

title: chocolate brownies
directions: Brownies:
Cream butter and sugar. Add chocolate syrup.
Mix well.
Add eggs, one at a time, then flour and nuts; mix well. Put in large jelly roll pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: spring pea soup
directions: Mix all ingredients except sour cream and mint in large saucepan. Bring to a boil on medium-high heat. Reduce heat to medium-low and simmer 15 minutes or until vegetables are tender. Transfer potato mixture to blender container in small batches. Cover. Blend until smooth. Repeat until entire mixture is blended. Stir in sour cream. Serve warm garnished with chopped fresh mint. Makes 7 (1 cup) servings.

title: sauerkraut balls
directions: Brown sausage and drain.
Put sauerkraut in blender and chop up fine and drain.
Put all ingredients in skillet.
Add cheese to melt; mix well.
Refrigerate 24 hours.
Make into small balls. Dip in flour, egg and bread crumbs.
Deep fry until golden brown in color.

title: chicken cashew casserole
directions: Cook
the
first
3 ingredients in 3 tablespoons butter until soft.
Mix	all
together,	put into casserole dish and cover with chow mein noodles.
Bake 20 to 30 minutes or until bubbly. Bake in a 375° oven.

title: razzle dazzle
directions: Cook the last 5 ingredients to a soft ball stage and pour over mixture of first 5 ingredients.
Turn out on buttered cookie sheet.

title: fudge cake (brownies)
directions: Melt butter in saucepan (or in microwavable bowl).
Add all other ingredients in order listed.
Bake at 300° for 35 minutes. Do not overbake.
Chocolate icing may be spread on top before cutting into squares or bars.

title: italian cream cake and icing
directions: Cream sugar, butter and Crisco.
Add beaten egg yolks, one at a time.
Mix soda with milk.
Then add milk alternately with flour to creamed mixture.
Add coconut and pecans.
Fold in stiffly beaten egg whites.
Makes 3 layers.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes or until tested with a toothpick and it does not stick.

title: beef whirligigs
directions: Get in your car and drive it to town.
Go through the drive through at KFC and ask for "One bucket of Original Recipe."

title: poppy seed pound cake
directions: Bake in greased and floured tube pan at 350° for 60 to 65 minutes.
Cover lightly with foil the last 20 minutes of baking time.
Test with toothpick.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Drain vegetables well.
Add celery, onions, mayonnaise and soup.
Mix well.
Pour melted margarine over crushed crackers and place over top of mixture that has been poured into buttered casserole.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: yummy refrigerator muffins
directions: Pour boiling water over wheat bran and let stand until cool. Cream the sugar and shortening.
Add eggs.
Sift dry ingredients together and add alternately with buttermilk.
Beat until smooth. Add cooled bran, bran cereal and raisins.
Put in container and refrigerate.
Batter keeps 4 to 5 weeks.

title: liz's eggplant pie
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Peel and slice eggplant.
Soak in salted water 20 minutes.
Drain and pat dry.
Brown eggplant slices in a little oil and transfer to a 10-inch pie plate. Sprinkle with salt, pepper, half of the parsley and thyme.
Cover the eggplant with the sliced tomato and sprinkle with salt and pepper, the remaining parsley, thyme and the onion and green pepper.
Cover with slices of cheese.
Beat eggs and milk together and pour over the vegetables.
Bake 30 minutes or until custard is firm.
Cut into wedges and sprinkle with Parmesan cheese when serving.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: cheddar cheese sticks
directions: Cream butter.
Add flour, crumbs, cheese and seasonings.
Mix thoroughly.
Add milk.
Roll and cut in strips 1/4 x 6-inches. Bake at 325° until brown.

title: sunset salad
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
When thoroughly dissolved, add pineapple juice, salt, pineapple and carrot.
Pour into a jello mold pan.
When set, serve on a platter covered with lettuce.
Serves 8.

title: al's easy bread
directions: Mix all dry ingredients by hand in a large bowl.
Add wet, except for 1 cup water.
Dissolve yeast in water; add to mix.
Pour 1/4 cup vegetable oil over bread and turn bread at once.
Cover dough with a cloth.
Let sit in warm place, 8 to 12 hours.
Punch bread down with fist three times.
Divide into three parts and knead each part 10 to 12 times.
Put each into greased loaf pan. Cover with a cloth and let sit for 8 to 12 hours.
Bake at 325° for 30 to 35 minutes on lowest rack in oven.

title: cottage cheese salad
directions: Mix dry jello into cottage cheese.
Add all the rest of the ingredients at once; mix until completely blended together.
Chill 1 hour.

title: peanut butter cookies (no flour)
directions: Mix well. Roll into walnut size balls. Roll in sugar. Put onto ungreased cookie sheet. Press down with finger. Bake 14 minutes at 350 degrees. Take out of oven. Put Hershey kiss on top while still hot.

title: vinegar pie
directions: Mix well and pour into unbaked pie crust.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until set.

title: ham and swiss crescent braid
directions: Heat oven to 375°. In 2-quart bowl, combine ham, chopped broccoli, cheese, mayonnaise and mustard; mix well. Unroll both cans crescent rolls. Place dough with long sides together on greased cookie sheet. Form a 12 to 15-inch rectangle by pressing the dough to seal perforations and edges. Spoon the ham mixture down the middle of the dough in a 6-inch strip. With sharp knife, make slits 1 1/2-inches apart on both long sides of the dough. Alternately cross strips over filling, tucking the ends up over the filling. Bake at 375° for 30 minutes or until deep golden brown. Cool 5 minutes before slicing.

title: blueberry-banana pie
directions: Cream the sugar and cream cheese.
Add flavoring.
Fold in Cool
Whip
and berries.
Slice and cover bottom of crusts with bananas.
Add
layer
of
cream cheese mixture, bananas, then cream cheese mixture.
Refrigerate.
Makes 2 pies.

title: mincemeat bars
directions: Mix the first 5 ingredients.
Place 1/2 of the mixture on bottom of 7 1/2 x 11-inch pan; spread mincemeat, then cover with remaining crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: fruit cake
directions: Cook cake as directed. Let cool. Crumble into pieces. Mix frosting mix as directed. Add all ingredients together. Mix in large pan. Mix real good. Pack in a dish or pan. Refrigerate. Slice when cool.

title: broccoli corn bread
directions: Mix together.
Melt 1 stick of butter in a 9 x 13-inch pan. Add mixture.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: quick smothered hamburger patties
directions: Fry the patties in skillet with 2 tablespoons oil.
When done, remove from pan and saute the onions in remaining oil.
When onions are no longer crunchy, return cooked patties to pan.
Add the soup.
Add about 1/2 can of water.
Cover and simmer until soup is thick and bubbly.
Season as desired.
Excellent served over cooked egg noodles!

title: cottage cheese mold
directions: Dissolve gelatin and salt in boiling water.
Stir in orange juice.
Chill until partially set.
Beat cottage cheese on high speed of mixer until almost smooth.
Stir in sour cream.
Fold cheese mixture into gelatin.
Pour into oiled 6 1/2-cup mold. Chill until firm.
Unmold on platter and surround with sliced fruit, as desired.
Makes 12 servings.

title: pumpkin bars
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into a greased jelly roll pan and bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: cookie and cream layer cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. In a large bowl, combine cake mix, sour cream, milk, egg whites and oil. Beat on low speed to blend, then on medium for 2 to 3 minutes. Stir 1 1/2 cups crushed cookies into batter. Divide batter between 2 greased and floured round cake pans. Bake for 30 to 35 minutes or until cake tester comes out clean. Cool and frost with White Frosting, then sprinkle remaining 1/2 cup of crushed cookies on top of cake for decoration.

title: shepherd's pie
directions: Brown meat; drain grease.
Boil potatoes or use prepared mashed potatoes.
Layer meat in bottom of 2-quart baking dish. Top with half of the cheese; cover with potatoes.
Top with remaining cheese.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until cheese is melted and bubbly.

title: chicken goulash
directions: Split chicken; skin, debone and cut into strips.
Sprinkle chicken with salt and pepper.
Coat with flour and brown in oil. Pour off all oil except 3 tablespoons of the drippings.
Add onion and garlic.
Cook until onion is tender.
Add remaining ingredients except sour cream.
Cover and simmer 20 to 25 minutes. Uncover; remove from heat after 5 minutes.
Stir about 1/4 cup of the sauce into sour cream.
Add slowly to mixture in skillet, stirring constantly until sour cream is thoroughly blended.
Heat through (do not boil).
Serve over noodles or rice.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: kraut
directions: Use 2 level teaspoons of salt (canning or pickling salt) to each quart of shredded cabbage.
Fill jars to almost full with cold or hot water and let stand while preparing cabbage.
(Empty prior to filling with shredded cabbage.)

title: seven-layer salad
directions: Mix mayonnaise and sugar.
Layer rest of ingredients in a large bowl; spread dressing over top, sealing edges.
Chill, tightly covered, for 6 hours or overnight.

title: zucchini cake
directions: Cream together the eggs, sugar and oil.
Add the remaining ingredients.
Pour into greased and floured 9 x 12-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for approximately 50 minutes.

title: hamburger mushroom noodle casserole
directions: Brown and drain ground beef.
Add mushrooms, soup, milk and cooked wide egg noodles.
Pour into baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Serves 12.

title: beef stew
directions: In a plastic bag, combine flour and 1 teaspoon salt.
Add meat cubes a few at a time, shaking to coat.
In hot oil, brown all sides of the meat cubes.
Add onion, garlic and thyme.
Stir in the vegetable juice, bouillon, hot pepper sauce and 1 cup of water.
Bring to boiling.
Reduce heat.
Cover and simmer until nearly tender.
Stir in potatoes, celery and carrots.
Continue cooking until tender.
If you prefer, use your crock-pot.

title: potato soup
directions: Saute onion and garlic in butter; add chicken broth, diced potatoes, salt and pepper.
Cook until potatoes are tender.
With hand masher, mash up some potatoes.
Add milk.

title: cocoa mix (hot chocolate)
directions: Mix well.
Store in a covered container.
Add 2 teaspoons or desired amount of mix to a cup of boiling water.
Top with marshmallows, if desired.

title: coconut pie
directions: Grease pie tin. Put all ingredients in blender for 2 to 3 minutes.
Pour in pie shell.
Bake in 350° oven for 45 minutes.

title: parmesan wings
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cut wings into drumsticks.
Combine parmesan cheese, parsley, oregano, paprika, salt and pepper in a bowl.
Line a cookie sheet with foil.
DO NOT omit this step or you'll be scrubbing the pan a week later.
The new no-stick foil is great for this!

title: cheesy potatoes
directions: Melt margarine in 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Spread potatoes on top of margarine.
Mix remaining ingredients.
Spread on top of potatoes.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Top with bacon bits; bake 15 minutes more.

title: meat loaf
directions: Chop onion, celery and pepper small.
Fry bacon in large skillet until crisp; remove to paper towel.
With about 2 tablespoons of drippings, add chopped vegetables, spices, tomatoes and baking soda.
Cook for about 5 or 6 minutes breaking up the tomato as you stir it.
Let cool.
Put in bowl and add eggs, and Worcestershire sauce.
Mix.
Add meat and crumbled bacon.
Mix well.
Add bread and make 2 even size loaves.
Place on rack in pan and bake at 350° for 1 hour or until brown.

title: salt substitute
directions: Mix ingredients and shake them.
Makes 1 cupful.

title: deviled baked potatoes
directions: Scrub the potatoes and pierce with a fork.
Place on a piece of paper toweling in the microwave oven or on a microsafe plate. Microwave on High power for about 12 minutes, until the potatoes yield to gentle pressure.
Let stand 3 to 5 minutes.
Cut a thin lid off the top of each potato.
With a melon baller, scoop out the flesh, leaving a 1/4-inch shell inside the potato skin.

title: chicken a la dinner
directions: Melt butter in skillet over medium-high heat.
Add oregano and chicken; cook until chicken is browned.
Add wine, garlic, rosemary, salt and pepper.
Simmer 1 hour or until wine is reduced 1/4 cup.
Serve with rice or pasta.

title: pea and mushroom casserole(serves 4)
directions: Cook peas until bright green and season with seasoned salt. Saute mushrooms and onion in butter until tender.
Add rice and mix.
Place in casserole dish.
Cover mixture with the peas.
Bake in 300° oven for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: banana bread
directions: Sift flour, baking powder, soda and salt.
Cream shortening; add sugar and beat.
Add eggs and beat again.
Add flour mixture and banana alternately.
Bake in a loaf pan that has been floured and greased lightly.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Bake for approximately 60 minutes.
Cool on wire rack.

title: oatmeal cake
directions: Combine oats and boiling water; let stand for 20 minutes.
Mix all ingredients.
Grease and flour 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: chicken chili
directions: Cal. 222 kc, fat 2 gm, chol. 24 mg, fib. 6 gm, carb. 33 gm, sodium 300 mg.

title: hot swiss cheese spread
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Place in small casserole and heat at 350° until cheese melts.
Serve with crackers.

title: pheasant aloha
directions: Place pheasant pieces in slow cooker.
Combine soy sauce, ginger, salt, onion, orange and pineapple juice.
Pour over pheasant.
Cover and cook on low setting for 6 to 8 hours.
Remove meat and set aside.

title: spicy pumpkin pie
directions: Combine butter, pumpkin, ginger, cloves, mace and cinnamon. Beat eggs until frothy; add flour, both sugars, salt and milk; mix gently.

Mix egg mixture and pumpkin mixture with a gentle hand. Pour into unbaked pie shell and bake at 450° for 15 minutes. Reduce oven to 375° and bake 45 minutes longer or until knife tip inserted in center comes out clean.

title: stuffed peppers ala mike
directions: Clean peppers.
Remove seeds and white membrane.
Blanch in salted boiling water for five minutes.
Drain and place in greased ovenware dish.
Peel and dice onion and pepper lids.

title: pear salad
directions: Drain juice and save.
Mash pears.
Heat juice and add jello. When cool, add pears.
Blend cream cheese, cream and Miracle Whip. Slowly blend in Cool Whip and pear mixture.
Pour into mold and chill.

title: forgotten cookies
directions: Beat egg whites.
Gradually add sugar and vanilla.
Fold in nuts and chocolate chips.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Drop cookies by teaspoons on ungreased foil.
When you start to put in oven, turn oven off and leave overnight.

title: white chip chocolate cookies
directions: Combine flour, cocoa, baking soda and salt in small bowl. Beat margarine, granulated sugar, brown sugar and vanilla in large mixer bowl until creamy.
Beat in eggs.
Gradually beat in flour mixture.
Stir in morsels.
Drop by well rounded teaspoonfuls onto ungreased baking sheets.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 9 to 11 minutes.
Let stand for 2 minutes; remove to wire racks to cool completely.
Makes about 5 dozen cookies.

title: dirt cake
directions: Grind cookies in food processor.
Mix butter, cream cheese and confectioners sugar together.
In separate bowl, mix milk, pudding and whipped topping.
Fold mixtures together.
Layer in an 8-inch flowerpot.
Start and end with ground cookies.
Decorate with flowers.

title: spicy pork balls(appetizer)
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Stir together last 6 ingredients in shallow baking dish.
Trim roots and wilted ends from onions.
Cut into 3 or 4 pieces.
Trim any fat from pork.
Slice into 20 slices.
Flatten meat slices with knife.
Roll each meat slice around one onion piece.
Place pork rolls in mixture and turn to coat.
Bake 10 to 15 minutes until no longer pink.
Yields about 20.

title: cantaloupe salad
directions: Cut cantaloupe into balls or chunks.
Combine sugar, mustard and lime and orange juices in a saucepan and bring to a boil. Cook until sugar is dissolved, then cool.
To combine, pour salad oil over melon balls, grapes and then pour over cooled dressing. Mix well.
Chill thoroughly at least 3 to 4 hours.

title: spinach quiche
directions: Layer half the spinach and half the Swiss cheese in the pie shell; repeat.
Combine rest of ingredients and pour over layered mixture.
Bake at 450° for 10 minutes.
Lower heat to 325° and bake until knife comes out clean, 24 to 45 minutes.

title: no-bake pumpkin pie
directions: For crust, you can use graham cracker Ready-Crust or bake Pet Ritz crust.
(Or make your own, they have to be baked).
In heavy medium saucepan, combine unflavored gelatine, spices and salt; stir in sweetened condensed milk and eggs.
Mix well.
Let stand for 1 minute.
Over low heat, cook and stir constantly until gelatine dissolves and mixture thickens slightly, about 10 minutes.
Remove from heat, stir in pumpkin, mix well.
Pour into prepared pie crust.
Chill for 3 hours or until set.
Garnish with whipped cream.
Makes 2 pies.

title: lazy day lasagna
directions: In a large bowl, mix cottage cheese, Mozzarella cheese, eggs, parsley, onion powder, basil and pepper until well blended; set aside.
In a medium bowl, mix together spaghetti sauce and cooked ground beef/turkey.

title: fruit salad
directions: Drain fruit but reserve 1/2 of liquid from each.
Pour over fruit.
Add pudding mix and stir well.
Add 2 to 3 bananas before serving.

title: no bake fudgies
directions: Bring sugar, oleo, milk and cocoa to a boil.
Now mix in the following to hot mixture:
peanut butter, vanilla and oats.
Drop by teaspoon on waxed paper and cool.

title: fudge brownies
directions: Melt margarine in 8 or 9-inch square pan. Mix all other ingredients together and pour in pan. Bake at 300° for 45 minutes.

title: crescent chicken squares
directions: Blend cream cheese, milk and 2 tablespoons butter.
Add rest of ingredients and mix.
Squeeze and pinch together crescents to make 4 squares.
Use 2 triangular crescents pinched together to make 1 square.
Put 1/2 cup of mixture into crescent square.
Pull up and pinch sides together.
Brush with remaining melted butter; sprinkle with bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° on ungreased sheet for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Pour melted butter into a shallow 2-quart baking dish; set aside.
Drain peaches, reserving 1/4 cup juice.
In a saucepan, bring peaches and juice just to a boil.
Meanwhile, in mixing bowl, combine 1 cup sugar, flour, milk, baking powder and salt; mix well.
Pour over butter in baking dish.
Spoon hot peaches over batter.
Sprinkle with remaining sugar.
Bake at 400° for 25 minutes or until cake tests done.
Serve warm.
Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: squash bake
directions: Combine vegetables and basil in 1 3/4 quart casserole sprayed with vegetable cooking spray; toss lightly.
Sprinkle with cheese. Cover and bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.
Contains about 35 calories per serving.

title: simple hollandaise
directions: Break egg in saucepan and stir slightly.
Add butter and lemon juice.
Place over burner, stirring constantly until desired thickness obtained.

title: marshmallow salad
directions: Combine marshmallows, orange juice and grapes.
Fold in whipped cream.
Chill in 2-quart casserole.
Sprinkle chopped nuts on top just before serving.

title: mama den's breakfast type thickened chocolate
directions: Mix thoroughly sugar, flour and cocoa (leave no lumps).
Mix together completely.
Then add milk.
Cook at medium heat until thick!

title: lotsa cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add eggs.
Beat; add flour mixture to butter, sugar and eggs.
Add remaining ingredients.
Spoon on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Recipe may be halved.
This recipe makes just what it says, Lotsa Cookies!

title: yogurt sesame chicken
directions: Cut up chicken into pieces.
Combine honey and yogurt.
In another bowl, combine corn flake crumbs, sesame seed, salt, ginger, paprika and pepper.
Dip chicken pieces in yogurt mixture and roll in crumb mixture until well coated.
Place in single layer on a greased baking pan.
Melt margarine and drizzle on chicken.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until chicken is tender.
Do not cover or turn chicken during baking.

title: blueberry crisp
directions: Put blueberries in buttered 8-inch square baking dish. Sprinkle with sugar and lemon juice.
In medium bowl, mix together butter, brown sugar, flour, cinnamon and salt until mixture is crumbly.
Stir in rolled oats.
Sprinkle mixture evenly over blueberries.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes at 375° until topping is nicely browned.
Serve warm with whipped cream or ice cream. Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: burritos
directions: Wrap tortillas in foil.
Heat in a 350° oven for 10 minutes to soften.

title: cheese bread
directions: Beat Bisquick mix, egg and milk with electric mixer, then stir in the rest.
Top with 1/2 cup cheese and 2 tablespoons melted butter.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: batter for french fried onion rings, shrimp, scallops, fish, etc.
directions: Combine the ingredients and refrigerate one hour before using. This batter may be used for onion rings, fried shrimp, scallops, fish or any fried food needing a good batter.

title: gloobly glop
directions: Make pudding following directions; refrigerate until set. Drain all canned fruit and mix all fruit in.
Fold in whipped cream.
Chill several hours.

title: liendsertart
directions: Mix all the ingredients by hand.
Knead the dough. Refrigerate the dough for 6 hours or overnight.
Place chilled dough on a lightly floured board.
Place a piece of wax paper over the dough and using a rolling pin, stretch the dough to fit a 10-inch pan.
Spread the jam on top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes. Can be made ahead.

title: sliced baked potatoes
directions: Peel potatoes and cut into thin slices but not all the way through. Use handle of spoon to prevent knife from going all the way through.
Put potatoes in a baking dish and fan slightly. Sprinkle with salt and drizzle with butter.
Sprinkle with herbs. Bake at 425° for 50 minutes. Remove from oven and sprinkle with cheese.
Bake for another 10 to 15 minutes or until lightly browned.

title: chop suey cake
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well.
Bake in greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan for 35 minutes at 350°.
Prepare frosting while cake is baking.

title: karo pecan pie
directions: Mix together all ingredients, adding nuts last.
Pour into unbaked crust.
Bake in a 450° oven for 10 minutes, then reduce heat to 350°.
Bake until a silver knife blade inserted into filling comes out clean, about 30 minutes.
Do not overbake.

title: maple syrup
directions: Combine sugar and water together in a small sauce pan. Bring to a boil, stirring constantly until sugar dissolves. Remove from heat and add maple flavoring. Makes about 1 1/3 cups.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Beat butter, shortening, sugars, vanilla, water and eggs until light and fluffy.
Mix flour with soda and salt; blend into butter mixture.
Stir in chips.
Drop 2 inches apart from teaspoon onto ungreased baking sheet.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes or until golden brown.
Makes about 8 dozen.

title: chewy oatmeal cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Lightly grease baking sheet.
Combine shortening, brown sugar, egg, milk and vanilla in large bowl.
Beat at medium speed until well blended.
Combine oats, flour, baking soda, salt and cinnamon.
Mix into creamed mixture at low speed. Stir in raisins and nuts.
Drop rounded tablespoonfuls of dough 2 inches apart onto baking sheet.
Bake for 10 to 12 minutes or until lightly browned.

title: veggie pizza (appetizer)
directions: Spread crescent roll dough on baking sheet, pressing seams together.
Bake until light brown, about 10 minutes.
Combine cream cheese, mayonnaise and dressing mix; spread over cooled, baked, crust.
Sprinkle veggies on top.
Cut into small squares or triangles.

title: spicy corn pudding
directions: Combine all ingredients and pour into 3-quart casserole.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
It should have a "set" consistency.
