May be prepared ahead and bake just before serving.
Serves 10.

title: pumpkin cake
directions: Remove 1 cup cake mix; set aside. To the rest of the cake mix, add 1 stick melted butter and 1 beaten egg. Mix with fork. Let set for 10 minutes and then press in bottom of 9 1/2 x 11 pan. Combine pumpkin, 1/2 cup brown sugar, 3/4 cup white sugar, cinnamon, milk and 3 beaten eggs. Mix together and spread over cake pan. Sprinkle with the following crumb mixture.

title: cream cheese pie with cherry topping
directions: Beat softened cream cheese until fluffy.
Beat in sweetened condensed milk.
Add lemon juice and vanilla.
Pour into graham cracker crust.
Chill until firm, until 3 hours.
Top with canned cherry pie filling.

title: aline's hot tomato ketchup
directions: Cook mixture of vinegar, sugar and cinnamon and add to rest of mixture.
Cook until it thickens, keeping it stirred.
Makes 7 pints.
This is very good on chitterlings.

title: creamy spinach dip
directions: Drain spinach, reserving 2 Tbsp. liquid.
Combine reserved liquid, sour cream, mayonnaise and soup mix.
Stir in spinach and red pepper.
Refrigerate several hours or overnight.
Serve with vegetables, bread or crackers.

title: custard pie
directions: Beat eggs, add sugar, vanilla and milk.
Pour in pie shell, sprinkle top with nutmeg. Bake in 450° oven for 30 minutes or 425° oven for 30 minutes.

title: rhubarb preserves
directions: Cut rhubarb into small pieces. Grate oranges, peeling and all. Cook down to preserves (until thick).

title: onion rings
directions: Sift flour and salt into mixing bowl. Mix milk, melted fat, and egg white; add to flour all at once. Beat until smooth. Add enough water to make a medium-thin batter. Separate onion rings and carefully dip in batter so each ring is covered. Drop a few at a time in 375° oil and fry until golden brown. Drain on absorbent paper. Sprinkle with salt. Serve hot.

title: sugar-free pumpkin pie
directions: Beat eggs.
Add pumpkin, sweeteners, spices and salt.
Add milk last.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 450° for 15 minutes, then at 325° for 45 minutes.

title: go foo
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Simmer for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: chicken bake
directions: Wrap each piece of chicken with dried beef slices.
Secure with bacon slices and toothpicks.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Cook noodles and/or rice according to package directions and place on each side of 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Cover with chicken.
Pour soup over all.
Bake, covered, 30 minutes at 350°.

title: texas sheet cake
directions: Icing: Bring margarine, milk and cocoa to a boil 2 minutes. Remove from heat and add sugar to right spreading consistency. Add vanilla and nuts. Spread on hot cake. Cool and cut into squares.

title: picante dip
directions: In a medium size bowl, mix all of the ingredients.
(Add spices and jalapeno peppers to season to taste.)
This dip is best if allowed to chill.

title: chicken almond spread
directions: Several hours or the day before serving, mix softened cream cheese, celery salt, onion salt, Worcestershire sauce, Tabasco sauce, parsley and sour cream.
Stir in chicken, mushrooms and almonds, all finely chopped.
Place in a dish that will mold the spread.
Refrigerate until chilled.
This allows all flavors to blend.
Unmold spread and sprinkle with paprika.
Serve with assorted crackers.

title: pasta with carbonara sauce
directions: Let eggs, butter and cream stand at room temperature for 2 to 3 hours.
Cook bacon until done; drain and cut up.
Heat an ovenproof serving dish in a 300° oven.

title: blueberry dessert
directions: Combine 20 graham crackers (make crumbs) with 1/3 cup melted butter.
Cook marshmallows and milk until smooth, stirring constantly.
Put aside to cool.

title: bread pudding
directions: Tear or cut bread into small pieces; mix together well all ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: cheese roll
directions: Mix the first 6 ingredients all together.
Shape into long rolls and roll in the paprika and chili powder.
Wrap roll in waxed paper.
Place in a Baggie and refrigerate.

title: southern sweet potato pie
directions: Boil yams in skins for 1 hour.
Cool and peel.
Place in mixing bowl with sugar, butter and milk.
Mash well or put in blender for about 3 minutes.
Add vanilla, egg, nutmeg and cinnamon.
Mix well.
Pour into uncooked pie shell and bake 45 minutes in
preheated 350° oven.

title: pull-apart herb bread
directions: In a skillet, saute garlic in butter; set aside. Separate biscuits, place half in an even layer in a greased 9 inch spring form pan. Brush with butter mixture; sprinkle with half of the cheese and herbs. Repeat. Place the pan on a baking sheet. Bake at 375 for 20-25 minutes or until golden brown. Remove from pan, serve warm. 8 servings.

title: aunt carolyn's chocolate pie
directions: Mix sugar, cocoa and flour.
Add milk and cook until thick, stirring constantly.
Add beaten egg yolks and softened butter. Cook one minute more.
Add vanilla.
Cool slightly and pour in baked pie shell.
Beat egg whites with 3 tablespoons sugar.
Brown at 350°.

title: phyllis' dessert
directions: Layer crackers and pudding.
Chill.
Cut into squares to serve.

title: 1-2-3 yellow cake (grammy cake)(use easy caramel frosting recipe)
directions: This is a favorite recipe in our family for 3 generations. Grammy Smucker made this cake and sold it at City Market years ago. "If too much is eaten, you will soon have a change of waist line."

title: cherry pie
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Prepare pastry.
Mix the sugar and flour.
Stir in cherries.
Pour in crust.
Sprinkle with almond extract and dot with margarine.
Cover with top crust and cut slits.
Seal and flute.
Cover edge with 2 to 3-inch strips of aluminum.
Remove foil last 15 minutes of baking.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes.

title: heavenly cherry cake
directions: Bake cake according to directions.
Cool.
Mix pudding with only half the recommended milk.
Chill.
Pour cherry filling over cake evenly.
Mix Cool Whip and pudding together gently and spread over cake and cherries.
Chill and serve.

title: yams and apples
directions: Saute apples and onion in margarine until soft.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Heat thoroughly.

title: cranberry crunch
directions: Mix oatmeal, brown sugar, flour and coconut.
Work in oleo. Spread half in 8 x 8-inch greased pan.
Spread with cranberry sauce and lemon juice. Add remaining crumb mixture.
Bake 40 minutes at 350°.

title: yogurt pie
directions: Mix yogurt and Cool Whip.
Pour into graham cracker crust. Freeze.

title: mississippi mud cake
directions: Cream sugar and Crisco.
Add eggs, one at a time; beat well. Add flour, salt and cocoa; mix well.
Add nuts, vanilla and coconut.
Pour into a well-greased sheet pan.
Bake for 40 minutes in a slow oven (300°).
While cake is still hot, pour the marshmallows on top of it.

title: broccoli corn bread
directions: In mixing bowl, combine melted oleo, onion, salt, cheese, broccoli and beaten eggs; blend.
Stir in muffin mix.
Pour into a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes. Cut into serving size squares.
Yields 18 servings.

title: meat loaf
directions: Saute onion, celery and bell pepper.
Season beef with salt and pepper.
Add sauteed onion, celery and bell pepper.
Beat eggs with a fork, briskly, and put in meat mixture.
Add the Bull's-Eye barbecue sauce, Worcestershire sauce, bread crumbs and milk.
Make 2 pones of meat loaf; dredge in flour.
Place in greased loaf pan and bake 40 minutes in a 350° oven.
Serves 8.

title: larry day's grandma's snickerdoodles
directions: Heat oven to 400°. Combine all ingredients. Roll into balls. Roll each ball into 2 tablespoons sugar and 2 teaspoons cinnamon. Bake on ungreased cookie sheet for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Put rice in bottom of pan with soup, soup mix and water.
Put fryers on top.
Cover and bake 2 1/2 hours at 275°.

title: stove top "baked beans"
directions: Cut bacon into cubes.
Finely chop onion.
Fry bacon pieces with onion in bean pot.
When browned, lightly add brown sugar and pork and beans to bacon and onion mix. Cook on low heat until beans are tender and brown sugar has melted.
Serves 12 children and 2 adults.

title: plain frosting
directions: Add vanilla to sugar.
Add cream gradually until frosting is of right consistency for cake.

title: blizzard ice cream
directions: Mix all ingredients together and add 1 pound of 1 of the following:
Oreos, Reese's Pieces, Butterfinger chips or Heath bars. Mix together and freeze.

title: martha's christmas pumpkin pie
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Stir in ingredients in the order given. Bake 15 minutes at 425°.
Reduce temperature to 350°; bake an additional 45 to 50 minutes or until done.

title: baked mock lobster
directions: Place fillet in a greased dish after rubbing with butter. Sprinkle rest of stuff on, cornflakes last.
Bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: all american dinner
directions: Brown beef in oil in Dutch oven.
Add water and seasonings. Cover; simmer 1 1/2 hours.
Add vegetables; cover and simmer 20 minutes.
Serve pan drippings with roast.
Serves 6.

title: breadsticks
directions: Mix all ingredients, except butter.
Knead 10 to 15 times. Roll out 1-inch thick and cut into 1/2-inch wide sticks.
Melt butter in baking dish.
Place sticks in melted butter; turn over once to coat before baking.
Bake at 450° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: fruit salad a la maria
directions: Mix all the fruit together. Serve and enjoy!
Serves 2 to 4.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Spray or grease one loaf pan.
Mix bananas, eggs and honey; stir in sugar.
Combine flour and baking soda in a separate bowl; stir into banana mixture.
Add chopped nuts and stir well.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Clean and chop into bite sizes the broccoli and cauliflower. Cook and crumble crisp bacon.

title: dump cake
directions: Mix cake mix per instructions.
Stir in peaches.
Melt 1 block of butter.
Pour on top.
Bake 15 minutes or until cake mix is baked.

title: icebox pickles
directions: Mix sugar, vinegar, salt and celery salt together.
Pour over the cucumbers, onions and peppers.
No need to cook at all.
Place in glass jars and keep in refrigerator.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Add sugar, vegetable oil and vanilla to beaten eggs.
Beat mixture until thick and lemon colored.
Stir in zucchini.
Add rest of ingredients to nuts.
Pour into 2 greased bread pans and bake at 350°
for 1 hour.

title: corn and macaroni bake
directions: Mix
all
ingredients together in casserole dish.
Bake in 350° oven 1 hour.
Stir once during baking.

title: pineapple casserole
directions: Drain pineapple well.
Toss pineapple with flour and sugar. Pour pineapple into greased casserole dish.
Top with Cheddar cheese, then Velveeta cheese, then Ritz cracker crumbs and the melted butter.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: cherry tarts
directions: Blend sugar, cheese and eggs; mix well.
Stir in peanut butter chips.
Drop by teaspoon onto vanilla wafers placed in baking cups.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until set.
Cool.
Top with cherry pie filling.

title: pork tenders with orange glaze
directions: In refrigerator, marinate pork overnight in Worcestershire sauce in sealed plastic bag.

title: chocolate chews
directions: In double boiler over simmering water, melt chocolate chips; set aside.
In large bowl, beat butter and 1 cup sugar until creamy.
Beat in eggs and chocolate.
Mix dry ingredients in small bowl, then add gradually to butter mixture.
Place remaining sugar in small bowl.
Roll dough in 1-inch balls and roll in sugar. Place 2-inches apart on greased baking sheet.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 14 minutes or until tops appear dry.
Cool one minute, then transfer to rack.
Store airtight.
Makes 3 1/2 dozen.

title: strawberry cream jello
directions: Prepare jello and set aside.
Mix soft cheese and Cool Whip. When jello is set, mix on low speed until fluffy.
Fold in cream cheese and whipped cream.
Fold in strawberry pie filling until smooth.
Chill 3 hours in 9 x 13-inch dish or pan and serve.

title: beef stick
directions: Fry the meat in oil until done.
Add the onions and cook until they are clear.
Season with salt and pepper to taste.
Add desired amount of water to make a broth.
Heat thoroughly.
Serve over rice.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Boil macaroni 10-12 minutes. Drain.
Beat eggs and milk together.
Add salt and pepper.
Alternate layers of macaroni, egg mixture and cheese.
Bake at 350 degrees 45 - 60 minutes.
Makes 10 servings.

title: chocolate cream cheese frosting
directions: Heat chocolate with water in small saucepan over very low heat, stirring constantly until melted and mixture is smooth.
Remove from heat; cool until lukewarm.
Add cream cheese; beat until mixture is well blended.
Gradually stir in sugar; add salt and vanilla.
Let stand a few minutes until frosting is of the right consistency for spreading.
Makes 1 cup or enough for tops of two 8 or 9-inch layers or tops of 20 cupcakes.

title: easy lasagne
directions: Brown ground beef in large skillet.
Drain.
Add both jars of sauce, mushrooms, minced onions and garlic salt.
Simmer while you boil lasagne noodles with 1 teaspoon oil until al dente.
Combine Ricotta, oregano and Parmesan cheese.
Set aside.
When noodles are done, spray bottom of 9 x 13-inch glass dish with Pam.
Lay noodles to cover bottom.
Layer Ricotta mixture, then meat sauce mixture and then Mozzarella.
Add more noodles and repeat until all ingredients are gone.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or cheese is lightly brown.

title: chicken bake
directions: Prepare stuffing according to package directions (use both). Place dressing in buttered 9 x 13-inch pan.
Add chicken (cut up) over stuffing.
Place cheese strips on top.
Mix broth and soup together.
Pour over all.
Cover and bake at 350° for 45 minutes. Remove cover last 5 minutes.

title: seven layer salad
directions: Place lettuce in bottom of salad bowl. Add layer of chopped celery, chopped green pepper and chopped green onion combined. Add layer of frozen peas. Spread mayonnaise mixed with sugar over the frozen peas like frosting. Layer with grated cheese. Cook bacon until crisp; then crumble over the cheese. Cover tightly and refrigerate for 24 hours. Do not toss.

title: butter bean casserole
directions: Brown ground beef and onions.
Add bacon, fried crisp, and broken in pieces, butter beans, brown sugar, tomato soup, salt and pepper.
Mix well.
Bake at 350°
for 1 hour in 9 x 13-inch pan. Delicious!

title: peanut brittle
directions: Cook sugar, white syrup, water and salt until it almost spins a thin thread.
Add raw peanuts.
Add butter when it spins a thread.
Cook until ready, then remove from heat.
Add soda and blend.
Pour on a butter slab or a couple of cookie sheets, turn over and spread as thin as possible.

title: homestyle baked beans and wieners
directions: Fry bacon until crisp and remove from pan.
Brown onion in bacon fat, combine onion, bacon, wieners and beans in a bowl.
Add molasses and spices.
Pour into covered baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Serves 4.

title: broccoli cauliflower salad
directions: Place bacon in a large, deep skillet.
Cook over medium high heat until evenly brown.
Crumble and set aside.
In a medium sized salad bowl, layer in order the
broccoli, cauliflower, eggs and bacon.
Prepare the dressing by whisking together the mayonnaise, sugar and vinegar.
Drizzle dressing over top and serve.

title: mexican cornbread #2
directions: Mix eggs, sour cream, chili peppers and onion. Mix dry ingredients. Combine the mixtures. Grease and heat skillet in 350° oven. Pour 1/2 mixture into skillet. Add shredded cheese. Add remaining mixture. Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: fat free banana bread
directions: Mix nonfat margarine, Egg Beaters and sugar together.
Add bananas and sour cream, blend well.
Then add flour gradually, baking soda and vanilla.
Stir.
Bake in a slightly greased loaf pan at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: grandma's orange jello
directions: Dissolve jello in hot water completely.
Fold in sherbet right away.
Fold in Cool Whip and orange sections.
Now, it is ready to serve.

title: debbie's crab dip
directions: Let the cream cheese soften. Add Worcestershire sauce, onions and garlic. Mix together until creamy. Spread on platter and cover with chili sauce. Rinse crab meat and squeeze out all water (watch out for shells) and spread on top of cheese and sauce mixture. Sprinkle with parsley flakes.

title: quick chicken soup
directions: Combine chicken broth, celery, onion, carrot, a dash of Mrs. Dash, uncooked rice and salt to taste.
Cook slowly until rice
is done and vegetables are tender.
Add can of cream of chicken soup
and can of chicken or turkey.
Continue cooking for 30 minutes, adding water as necessary.
Serves 4.

title: chocolate chip blonde brownies
directions: Mix flour, baking powder, soda and salt.
Add nuts and mix well.
Melt margarine in pan.
Remove from heat; add sugar and mix well.
Cool.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Add flour mixture, a small amount at a time, mixing well after each addition.
Turn into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle chocolate chips over top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes (approximately).
Cool in pan.

title: dill bread
directions: Mix in separate bowl to dissolve the yeast, water, ginger and 1 tablespoon of sugar.

title: jungle soup
directions: Place peas in a large saucepan without a lid and add the cold water.
Bring to boiling point.
Allow to simmer until the water cooks down and the peas are cooked to a soft, wet paste.
(Be careful not to let them burn.)
Add the 2 cans of soup; stir and allow to simmer for a few minutes.
Season to taste, if necessary, after all ingredients are added.
If the soup is thicker than you prefer, add a little water.

title: creamy chicken enchiladas
directions: Cook onion in oleo until tender.
Stir in chicken, 1/4 cup picante sauce, cream cheese and cumin; heat through.
Remove from heat.
Stir in 1/2 cup of shredded cheese.
Heat about 1/2 inch oil in small skillet; quickly fry each tortilla in oil to soften (about 2 seconds on each side).
Drain on paper towel.
Spoon 1/3 cup chicken mixture down center of each tortilla; roll and place seam side down in 12 x 7-inch baking dish.
Spoon remaining picante sauce over enchiladas; cover with remaining cheese.
Bake at 350° about 15 minutes or until hot.
Sprinkle with the green onion and serve with additional picante sauce.

title: sausage cake
directions: Combine raw sausage and brown sugar.
Add 2 cups flour and spices.
Dissolve soda in hot coffee and add to mixture.
Dredge raisins and nuts in flour.
Add to batter, mixing well.
Pour into Bundt pan and bake at 325° for 90 minutes or until cake tester comes out clean.

title: roasted pecans
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Put pecans in large baking pan.
Place stick of butter in middle of pan.
Place in oven.
Roast for 30 to 40 minutes.
Stir at least twice.
Drain nuts on paper towel. Add salt, turning nuts to make sure salt covers both sides.
Let nuts cool and enjoy!

title: egg casserole
directions: Combine chilies, eggs, milk, flour, salt and 1/2 cheese in 1 quart shallow pan.
Sprinkle remainder of cheese on top.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour or 1 1/2 hours.
May add cooked bacon, ham, etc. Makes 8 servings.

title: calico beans
directions: Cook together hamburger, bacon and onion; drain.
Combine all ingredients and bake 40 minutes in a 350° oven.
Or you can put it in a crock-pot.
I make and cook mine as I would chili.

title: apple bread
directions: Beat sugar and eggs together.
Add oil and vanilla.
Beat well.
Add sifted dry ingredients and apples.
Add the remainder of the ingredients and mix well.
Pour into greased and floured loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.
Yield: 3 loaves.

title: light and heavenly salad
directions: Mix first two ingredients and then fold in the rest of the ingredients.
Chill 4 to 6 hours.

title: my kid's favorite giant shells
directions: Cook the noodles as directed on the box.
Cook the turkey meat in a bowl in the microwave.
Cover bowl with a piece of waxed paper and cook 5 minutes.
Remove and stir.
Return to the microwave and cook about 3 to 4 more minutes.
Drain turkey meat in a colander. In a large bowl, pour in the spaghetti sauce.
Add the turkey to the tomato sauce.
In a medium bowl, blend together the Ricotta cheese, Egg Beaters and Parmesan cheese.
Spray 2 casserole dishes with Pam spray (9-inch square size).
This recipe makes two casseroles.
You can serve one now and freeze one for a busy day when you don't have time to cook.
Pour a little of the turkey-tomato sauce mixture in the bottom of each of the casserole dishes.
Spread the Ricotta cheese mixture over this layer in each dish.
Next place the noodles on top of the Ricotta cheese mixture. Sprinkle half of the cheese on top of each dish.
Repeat layers with sauce, giant shells and end up with Mozzarella cheese sprinkled on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
You can also cook this for 10 minutes in the microwave and place in oven about 5 minutes to brown.
Yields 2 (9-inch) square casseroles.
Serves 18 to 20.

title: homemade rolls
directions: Heat milk; add Crisco, sugar and salt.
Dissolve well.
Let cool to lukewarm temperature.
Add yeast.
Sift and add flour. Mix well.
Form into ball in bowl; cover and let rise at least 1 hour or until double in size.

title: orange cookie chip
directions: Combine flour, baking soda and salt in small bowl.
Beat butter, granulated sugar and brown sugar in large mixer bowl until creamy.
Beat in egg and orange peel.
Gradually beat in flour mixture; stir in morsels.
Drop dough by rounded tablespoon onto ungreased baking sheets.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 10 to 12 minutes or until edges are light golden brown.
Let stand for 2 minutes; remove to racks to cool completely.
Makes 40 cookies.

title: quick and yummy tato
directions: Put potatoes in 9 x 13-inch pan with onion.
Melt Cheez Whiz, mushroom soup and sour cream in microwave.
Pour over potatoes and bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.
Can be mixed up ahead for a hurry up bake.

title: italian vegetable soup
directions: Cook and stir sausage and enjoy the aroma as you add the onion.
Cook until sausage is light brown and onions are limp. Drain.
Stir in tomatoes with liquid, beans, broth, water, zucchini and basil.
Break up tomatoes with fork.
Heat to boiling.
Reduce heat and cover.
Simmer until zucchini is tender, about 5 minutes.
Sprinkle with cheese.

title: cranberry-apple glazed ham
directions: In a 2-cup measuring microwave cup, stir together the brown sugar, cornstarch and allspice.
Stir in the cranberry juice.
Add the chopped apple and cranberries.
Mix well.
Microcook, uncovered, on 100% power (High) for 3 to 5 minutes or until thickened and bubbly, stirring every minute.
Set fruit mixture aside, covered.
Arrange ham slices in baking dish.
Cover. Microcook on High for 3 to 4 minutes.
Spoon fruit mixture over ham and serve.

title: tuna garden salad
directions: Combine mayonnaise,
dressing and mustard.
Add rest of the ingredients and refrigerate.

title: penne with asparagus and porcini cream(prep time: 20 minutes; cook: 20 minutes; serves 4)
directions: Combine the porcini and water in a small saucepan; heat to boiling.
Simmer, covered, for 5 minutes.
Let stand off heat for 10 minutes.
Strain the liquid through a fine sieve; reserve the liquid.
Finely chop mushrooms and set aside.

title: sharon's barbecue sauce
directions: Mix ingredients together and refrigerate.

title: witch's brew
directions: Put the tea bags in 2 cups water.
Boil and steep for 4 hours. Add 7 cups water and 2 cups sugar; bring to a rapid boil.
Remove from heat; add all liquid together.
Freeze.
The longer it has set in the freezer, the better, at least 2 days.
To use, put one "ice cream scoop" of the Brew to a glass and fill with Sprite or 7-Up. It will be slushy.

title: pickled mushrooms
directions: Mix all ingredients; add 2 (6 ounce) cans mushroom crowns, drained.
Simmer 5 to 6 minutes.
Chill in covered dish several hours; drain before serving.

title: cranberry slush punch
directions: In a bowl, combine the cranberry sauce concentrates, water, cinnamon and allspice. Cover and freeze for 8 hours or overnight. Remove from freezer 45 minutes before serving.

title: country style pot roast
directions: Brown the meat in a small amount of the tomato liquid and drain, if necessary, to remove excess fat.	Add
tomatoes and seasonings.
Cover and simmer 1 1/2 hours; then add potatoes, carrots, celery and onions.
Cover and simmer about 1 hour until vegetables are crisp-tender.
Add mushrooms and simmer 15 minutes. Delicious! (Sometimes I add a couple of drops of Tabasco sauce to spice it up since we cut down on the salt.)

title: cranapple relish
directions: Boil cranberries until popped.
Add sugar and raisins and boil 5 minutes.
Take pan off heat and combine with all remaining ingredients.
Chill.
Serve with meat, poultry or game.

title: mom's hot cocoa mix
directions: Mix all ingredients together. Use as any other powdered cocoa mix, but much better.

title: oven beef stroganoff
directions: Cook the meat in 1 tablespoon butter until it loses its red color.
Add onion; cook for four minutes or until the onion is barely tender.
Pour into 1 1/2-quart greased casserole.
Melt 1 tablespoon butter in saucepan; blend in the flour.
Add bouillon cubes, hot water, hot pepper sauce, salt, pepper, mustard, Worcestershire sauce and ketchup.
Cook until thickened.
Blend in the dairy sour cream; pour the mixture over the meat and cover. Bake the beef in a preheated moderate oven (350°) for 45 minutes or until tender.
Makes four servings.
Can be prepared ahead; refrigerate until cooking time.

title: turkey jambalaya
directions: In heavy skillet, fry bacon until crisp.
Add butter and melt over medium heat.
Saute ham and turkey 4 minutes.
Remove meat from skillet.
Add onion, bell pepper, celery and garlic.
Saute until onion is lightly brown, about 5 to 7 minutes.
Add rice and mushrooms and saute 3 minutes.
Return meat to skillet and saute for 1 minute.
Add chicken broth, seasoning mix and Tabasco sauce. Cook, uncovered, 25 to 30 minutes or until rice is tender.
Add parsley and green onions and mix well.
Cover and cook over very low heat for 5 minutes.

title: green mashed potatoes
directions: Fold spinach into potatoes.
Add all the remaining ingredients and mix.
Put in greased casserole.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes. Serves 6 to 8.

title: 5-cup salad
directions: Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: almond chicken
directions: In a large skillet, heat oil.
Add chicken. Brown well.
Drain fat.
In a small bowl, combine tomato sauce, preserves, onion, soy sauce and ginger. Blend well.
Pour sauce over chicken. Cover and simmer 1 hour or until chicken is tender, turning once.
Place chicken on a serving platter. Spoon sauce over chicken. Garnish with toasted almonds.

title: tex mex
directions: In medium bowl, mix together refried beans, green chilies and taco seasoning mix.
Spread mixture on a 12-inch round platter. Spread on taco sauce.
Mix together the avocado dip and sour cream.
Spread on top of taco sauce.
Add layer of cheese, jalapeno, tomatoes, onions and black olives.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: broccoli cheese ball
directions: Mix the cream cheese, chopped green onions and shredded broccoli tops together.
Mold into ball; set in refrigerator until time to serve.
Serve on a bed of lettuce, with crackers.

title: new england boiled dinner for 4 people
directions: Boil ham about 1 hour.
Add potatoes, onions, turnips, cabbage and carrots (cut up).
Cook until vegetables are tender.
Add 1 tablespoon butter; let set until medium warm.
Serve with corn bread.
Tastes better next day.

title: easy-n-delicious spinach casserole
directions: Cook spinach according to package directions.
Combine sour cream, soup mix and cheese; add to drained spinach.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch Pyrex dish and top with bread crumbs.
Bake, covered, at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes (until heated through).
Easily halved. Serves 12 generously.

title: peanut brittle candy
directions: Combine sugar, water and syrup in saucepan.
Cook to 250° on candy thermometer.
Pour in peanuts; stir and cook to 300°. Remove from heat and add butter immediately.
Then add baking soda and stir briskly.
Will foam over if not stirred after mixing soda.
Pour hot candy onto a smooth well buttered surface.
Cool slightly, then stretch to your liking.

title: stuffed green peppers(microwave)
directions: Remove the pepper's tops and seed them.
Combine remaining ingredients and fill peppers.
(At this time, you can package well and freeze in airtight containers.)
Bake in microwave oven for 10 to 11 minutes on High until peppers are done.
When dish is frozen, place in microwave for 15 to 20 minutes on High until peppers are done.

title: easy and best sugar cookies
directions: Beat butter and sugar; add eggs and beat well.
Add vanilla; mix well.
Stir in baking soda and 1 cup flour at a time.
Chill overnight.
Roll out and cut with cookie cutters.
(Note: Best if dough 1/4 inch thick.)
Bake at 350° for 8 to 12 minutes.

title: chocolate mint pie
directions: Stir crushed cookies and melted margarine together until well blended.
Press into a spring-form pan or a 13 x 9-inch pan; for one hour, freeze.
Spread frozen crust with softened ice cream and freeze for one hour.
Top with layer of whipped topping.
Freeze 24 hours before serving.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Butter a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Combine soups, rice and milk in casserole; place chicken pieces on top.
Season chicken with salt and pepper.
Sprinkle with onion soup mix.
Cover tightly with aluminum foil and bake in preheated oven at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.
Serves six.

title: deep dark chocolate cake
directions: Combine dry ingredients in a large bowl.
Add eggs, milk, oil and vanilla.
Beat 2 minutes at medium speed.
Stir in boiling water.
(Batter should be thin.)
Pour into a greased and floured 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan and bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Frost as desired.

title: fudge icing
directions: Mix sugar and cocoa; add margarine and milk.
Cook over low heat, stirring, until margarine is melted.
(Cook without stirring until it forms a soft ball when dropped into cold water.)
Remove from heat; add vanilla and beat until it thickens enough to spread.
Covers 2 layers.

title: easy chicken pot pie
directions: Prepare stuffing mix as directed on box.
Mix soup and milk in 2-quart casserole.
Stir in chicken, mixed vegetables and thyme. Spoon stuffing over chicken mixture.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until hot and bubbly.
Serves 6.

title: copper penny salad
directions: Cook carrots for 25 minutes; drain and cool.
Add bell pepper and onion.
Mix soup, sugar, vinegar, salad oil and seasonings; pour over vegetables.
Refrigerate for at least 12 hours before serving.
Will keep at least 2 weeks in refrigerator.

title: butter pound cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add butter flavoring.
Mix 1 tablespoon less than 2 cups flour and dry pudding in another bowl by hand.
Pour into greased and floured tube pan.
Bake at 325° for 40 minutes.

title: vegetable sandwich mix
directions: Chop all fine (do not blend in blender).
Stir the mayonnaise with the vegetables. Salt and pepper to taste.
Soften the unflavored gelatin in the hot water.
Stir in the gelatin mixture, stirring as you pour.
Let set up in refrigerator for 24 hours or overnight.
Spreads 3 loaves of bread or use on crackers. Cut off crusts.
Makes great tea sandwiches or snacks.

title: gingerbread
directions: Cream together first 5 ingredients. Sift rest of the ingredients together and add alternately to cream mixture.
Turn into greased and floured 9 x 9 x 2-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: aunt cele's cornbread
directions: Mix ingredients together (except bacon grease).
Melt bacon grease in iron skillet; now add some to bread mixture and bake at 500° for about 15 minutes or until brown.

title: potatoes romanoff
directions: Cook potatoes. Combine, saving half cheese to go on top. Bake, uncovered, for 40 minutes at 350°.

title: banana split cake
directions: 1st layer:
In a 3-quart glass dish, mix graham cracker crumbs, margarine and sugar. Press in dish.

title: garlic bread
directions: Cut French bread into thick slices.
Put remaining ingredients in a small saucepan and melt over medium heat.
Brush margarine mixture on bread slices.
Arrange on baking sheet.
Broil until desired crispness.

title: marzetti
directions: Brown meat, onion and pepper.
Pour off grease.
Add soups and seasonings; simmer for 30 minutes.
Cook noodles according to directions and drain.
Combine meat mixture.
Add noodles and pour into Pyrex pan.
Top with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until cheese is brown.

title: pizza casserole
directions: Cook and stir the first 6 ingredients together.
Cook the noodles according to directions; drain.
In casserole dish, layer meat, noodles and Mozzarella cheese.
Layer until all are used, ending with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour, or until cheese melts.

title: nana's banana bread
directions: Cream together first 3 ingredients.
Add soda, flour and nuts; mix.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: summer noodles
directions: In a large pot of boiling water, cook the noodles until just tender.
Drain and put into a large bowl.
Add the sour cream, cottage cheese, salt and pepper and toss lightly to coat.

title: spanish rice
directions: Brown hamburger in skillet.
Cook rice.
Add cooked rice to meat in skillet.
Also add tomato sauce, salt, pepper, curry powder and paprika.
Stir all together and cook for 5 minutes. Can be made in 30 minutes, start to finish.
Good with bread and butter and salad.

title: banana crunch salad(kids cookery fruit salad)
directions: Wash, core and slice the apples.
Quickly dip them into the lemon juice and let drain.
Peel and slice bananas.
Quickly dip them into the lemon juice and drain.

title: chocolate pecan pralines
directions: Note:
Instead of chocolate squares, you can use 3 tablespoons of Hershey's cocoa and 1 tablespoon of oil to equal 1 square. Double this to make the 2 squares.

title: little man's favorite dish
directions: Boil rice until done (tender).
Meanwhile, be frying sausage; after both are done, add together into same skillet.
Let fry on low for 5 minutes.
Add salt and pepper for taste.

title: heavenly chicken
directions: Place one package of chicken cutlets or more (cut up or whole) in one egg batter or egg white.
Instead of the egg, you can cover the chicken with mayonnaise.
Season with garlic powder and basil leaves (salt and pepper is optional).
Then, cover the chicken with bread crumbs.
Place in oven on lightly greased pan or foil on middle rack at 350° for about 20 minutes or until it looks done.
Enjoy!
Peace be with you.

title: chopped apple cake
directions: Mix thoroughly the sugar, eggs, Wesson oil and vanilla.
Sift together and add to first mixture the dry ingredients.
Fold in chopped apples and nuts.
Bake 45 to 50 minutes at 350° in ungreased pan.
Bake in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cut in squares.

title: hot cheese dip
directions: Mix ingredients together and bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Serve hot.

title: black cuban beans
directions: Soak beans in their double amount of water overnight; rinse well before.
In a pressure cooker, put 1/2 cup of the olive oil. Cut green peppers, onion and garlic in large pieces and at medium heat, saute with bay leaf and finely cut tomato.

When tender, put the beans with the same water they have been soaked in plus about 4 cups more water into pressure cooker and cook for 1/2 hour. Uncover and let simmer at medium heat for 1/2 hour, smashing with spoon a few of the beans to help thicken the sauce.
When proper thickness is achieved, remove from heat and mix the sugar, vinegar and rest of olive oil into the sauce.
They even taste better the next day.

title: lemon chess pie
directions: Melt margarine.
Add sugar.
Add eggs.
Beat only until mixed. Add juice from lemons and then rind.
Pour into frozen 2 pie shells.
Bake at 425° for 10 minutes.
Reduce temperature to 350° and bake 45 minutes.

title: noodles and cheese bake
directions: Cook noodles; drain.
Return to pot and toss gently, but thoroughly, with 2 tablespoons of butter or margarine.
Place eggs in mixing bowl; beat slightly.
Add cheeses and salt, if desired, and blend well.
Divide into 2 equal parts.
Mix parsley into 1 part.

title: sour cream chocolate cake
directions: Sift together flour, sugar, soda and salt.
In large pan bring first 3 ingredients to boil; remove from heat.
Add eggs and sour cream (mix by hand, do not use mixer).
Combine and gradually add flour mixture.
Mix well.
Bake in greased 9 x 13-inch pan at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Frost while still warm.

title: banana foster
directions: Melt in skillet or chafing dish butter; add sugar and cinnamon.
Cook slowly until bubbly (3 to 4 minutes).
Add bananas to syrup, basting continually.
Cook until heated.
In small pan, heat liqueur and rum together.
Pour rum over the bananas; ignite with long match.
Baste with syrup until flame dies down.
Put ice cream into serving dishes; garnish with banana and syrup.
Serve immediately.
Serves 8 or more.

title: fresh tomato tart(6 servings)
directions: Line a 10-inch tart pan with pie pastry.
Prick crust well and bake according to package directions.
Cool.
Slice tomatoes and place in layers in tart pan.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper (I use "Old George's" original seasoning; it's good) and basil.
In a small bowl, combine mayonnaise, Parmesan cheese and garlic powder. Spread mixture over tomato slices.
Mixture will not completely cover tomatoes.
Sprinkle with cracker crumbs.
Bake Tomato Tart at 400° for 15 minutes.

title: white chocolate snack mix
directions: Melt white almond bark and oil.
Mix rest of ingredients in large bowl.
Drizzle chocolate mixture over and mix well to coat. Spread mixture out on waxed paper covered cookie sheet to cool. Store in airtight container.

title: dump cake
directions: Butter baking pan (2-inches deep) and spread crushed pineapple (include juice). Spoon pie filling, spreading evenly. Sprinkle dry cake mix over top and spread evenly. Pour melted oleo over cake mix. Scatter nuts on top and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: chunky salsa
directions: Cover and chill at least two hours.

title: pittsburg potatoes and white sauce
directions: Cook potato cubes and onions in boiling salted water for 5 minutes.
Add pimiento and cook 7 minutes.
Drain.
Put in a buttered baking dish and pour White Sauce over all, mixed with cheese and salt.
Bake in a moderate oven until potatoes are soft.

title: cheese ball
directions: Combine ingredients.
Form into a ball.
Roll in crushed nuts.

title: wine-herring pate with caviar
directions: Melt butter; pour into blender.
Add tuna and herring, 1/4 at a time.
Blend until smooth.
Mix in onion and garlic powder.
Pack into a 2-cup mold.
Refrigerate 2 hours or more.
Unmold.
Spread black caviar on sides or place on ring of sour cream surrounding mold.
Top with red caviar.
Serve with crackers.
Serves 20 to 30 people.

title: monkey bread
directions: Combine sugar and 1 teaspoon of cinnamon in a bag.
Add biscuits and shake.
Drop biscuit pieces into greased tube pan or round cake pan and sprinkle with nuts.
Combine brown sugar, 1 teaspoon of cinnamon and butter.
Bring to a boil over medium heat.
Pour over cake.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Turn out and serve while warm.

title: reese cup squares
directions: Combine first four ingredients and press into a large 9 x 13-inch pan.
Melt chocolate chips over low heat and pour over mixture.

title: german hot potato salad
directions: Cook potatoes until tender; drain well.
Cool slightly.

title: apricot salad
directions: Save the fruit juice.
Dissolve jello and 1 tablespoon sugar in 2 cups of hot water and add 1 cup of juice.
Add fruit and 2 cups miniature marshmallows.
Let set up.

title: mexican dish
directions: Cook ground meat with onion until done.
Warm tortillas in sauce.
Add mixture of ground meat, tortillas and cheese in layers in baking dish.
Bake at 350° until cheese is melted.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Brown meat, drain and set aside.
Mix corn, cornmeal, oil, eggs, onion, milk and 3/4 of the cheese.
Add meat and peppers. Mix well.
Pour into a greased baking dish and use leftover cheese to put on top.
Bake at 375° to 400° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Can be wrapped in foil and put in freezer.

title: three-bean bake(microwave)
directions: In
a
2-quart microwave-safe casserole, arrange bacon; cover. Cook
on
power
(High)
4 to 7 minutes or until crisp. Remove
bacon,
reserving
tablespoon of drippings. Drain and crumble and set aside.
Add onion rings to drippings in casserole; cover.
Cook,
covered,
on High 3 to 5 minutes or
until tender, stirring once.
Drain.
Combine all ingredients in microwave dish. Cook, uncovered, on High for 11 to 13 minutes, stirring once. Makes 6 servings.

title: jack's spaghetti sauce
directions: Brown beef in 2 or 3-quart saucepan in 2 tablespoons olive oil. Stir in garlic and mushrooms.
Add tomato sauce and paste, oregano and cayenne pepper.
Heat thoroughly.
Spoon over cooked pasta. Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: no bake oatmeal cookies
directions: Combine peanut butter and honey in a large bowl.
Mix in oats and dry milk.
Stir until completely mixed.
Roll into balls the size of walnuts.
Put on cookie sheets.
Yield: about 2 dozen.

title: cherry cake
directions: Make
cake
and bake according to directions in 12-inch Dutch oven
for
45 minutes.
Cool cake.	Mix jello with 1 cup boiling water
and 1/2 cup cold water.
At 1/2-inch intervals poke holes deep
into	top
of cake.
Pour jello mix on cake. Chill for
4 hours.
Put
on Cool Whip.	Spoon pie filling on top and serve.

title: apple potato pancakes
directions: In a blender, mix the eggs, flour, milk and salt.
Blend until smooth.
Let the batter stand about 1 hour.
Sprinkle the juice of one half a lemon over the apples.
In a heavy skillet, heat 2 teaspoons of butter.
When the butter is bubbly, add the batter with apples slices and bake in 350° oven for 15 minutes.

title: cherry salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together and refrigerate.

title: fruited chicken salad
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Fold in whipped cream.
Chill, covered, for at least 3 hours.
When ready to serve, line plate with lettuce.
Place cantaloupe ring on top.
Fill center with large scoop of chicken salad.
Decorate with seasonal fruit.
Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: pineapple beets
directions: Heat the pineapple, vinegar and flavoring to boil.
Combine sugar and cornstarch.
Stir into boiling mixture.
Cook until thick.
Combine beets, oleo, salt and pepper.
Add to mixture. Let stand one hour or more.
Reheat to serve.

title: 60-second blueberry pie
directions: Fold blueberries into blueberry pie filling.
Add almond extract, lemon juice and rind.
Pour into pie shell and chill until ready to serve.
Garnish with whipped topping.

title: waldorf salad
directions: Combine apples and lemon juice; toss gently.
Add celery, grapes, walnuts and raisins.
Toss gently.
Set aside.
Combine salad dressing, sugar and lemon juice in a medium bowl.
Stir well. Set aside.
Beat whipping cream at high speed until soft peaks form.
Gently fold whipping cream in salad dressing mixture.
Add to apple mixture.
Stir gently.
Stir in coconut and marshmallows. Cover and chill.

title: kraft treats
directions: Melt caramels in top of double boiler with milk.
In a large mixing bowl, put Rice Chex and pecan halves.
Pour caramel over cereal and nuts.
With buttered hands, make into balls and drop on wax paper.
Makes about 3 dozen.

title: broccoli and rice
directions: Simmer onions in margarine.
Add soup, cheese and melt together.
Add cooked broccoli; mix well.
Then add cooked rice. Mix again. Turn into casserole dish and cover mixture with cracker or potato chip crumbs.
Bake at 350° covered for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: tuna wonton soup
directions: Combine tuna, celery, lemon peel and green onion in small mixing bowl.
Mix well.
Lightly dampen edges of each wonton wrapper with water.
Place 1 teaspoon filling in center of each wonton.
Fold in half to top edge to form rectangle.
Fold again to within 1/8-inch of top edge.
Press sides to seal in filling. Dampen ends with water.
Lay rectangles on flat surface and form into a horseshoe shape.
Overlap ends and press to seal.
Heat chicken broth and water in large saucepan.
Bring to a boil.
Add wontons and simmer gently, about 6 minutes, stirring occasionally. Reduce heat.
Add zucchini, mushrooms and carrot.
Simmer 4 to 5 minutes longer, adding lemon slices for last 2 minutes.
Add soy sauce.

title: rolled dumplings
directions: Cut
shortening
into dry ingredients.	Stir in lightly the beaten egg	and milk.
Pat into a ball.
On floured board, roll out
to 1/4 to
1/8-inch
thick.
Cut
into
1/2-inch squares. Drop into boiling
broth.
Cover and cook slowly for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: tomato gratin
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Spray a shallow 2-quart baking dish with cooking spray.
Arrange 4 slices of bread over bottom of baking dish, tearing to fit.
Top with half of the tomato slices.
Spread garlic over tomatoes, then sprinkle with half the chives.
Season with salt and pepper.
Crumble Cheddar cheese over chives and drizzle with half the oil.
Top with remaining bread slices, pressing firmly to fit.
Arrange remaining tomato slices on top, then sprinkle with remaining chives, Parmesan cheese and additional pepper to taste.
Drizzle with remaining 1 1/2 teaspoons oil.
(If making ahead, cover and refrigerate, then proceed.)
Bake for 40 to 45 minutes, or until cheese on top is golden and tomatoes are soft. Serve immediately.

title: potluck
directions: Brown onion in 1 tablespoon of oil.
Add ground beef and sear; pour off excess grease.
Add tomato sauce and cook over low heat for 15 minutes.
Add beans, macaroni, salt and pepper to meat mixture.
Pour in 2-quart greased casserole dish.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes.

title: superb strawberry dessert
directions: Meanwhile, cream the cream cheese, Eagle Brand milk and Cool Whip.
Mix jello with hot water and plain gelatin.
Let cool to egg white consistency.
Mix into strawberries, then fold into cream cheese mixture.
Let mixture chill a little while before putting on top of crust.
Spread top with Cool Whip or Dream Whip.

title: spiced chicken
directions: Combine spices.
Wash chicken thoroughly and dry.
Sprinkle spice mixture over entire surface of chicken.
Refrigerate at least one hour.

title: pancit
directions: Boil chicken and pork in a pot until 3/4 done.
Remove from pot and slice into 1/4 to 3/8 inch strips.
Save the water that the chicken and pork were boiled in.
Slightly brown the garlic in the vegetable oil.
Add the celery, onions, greenbeans and cabbage. Add a little broth from the water that the chicken and pork were boiled in, if the wok gets to dry.
When they are slightly cooked, add the meat.
Once that is stirred and mixed thoroughly, add the pan cit noodles.
Stir thoroughly.
Add enough soy sauce to brown the noodles slightly.
Add the broth as necessary to keep all of the ingredients moist.
When the noodles are soft, serve with rice.

title: mini cheesecakes
directions: You will need 2-inch mini cupcake papers.

title: gram's kris kringle cookies
directions: Cream butter thoroughly; add sugar, a little at a time, and cream well.
Add eggs, vanilla and milk.
Sift flour, soda, cream of tartar and salt; mix well.
Add flour to make dough that can be rolled out.
Cut with cookie cutters.
Bake at 450° for about 7 minutes.
Enjoy!

title: no-knead rolls
directions: Combine first four ingredients.
Dissolve yeast in 1/4 cup lukewarm water.
Add egg and yeast to flour mixture.
Mix thoroughly.
Shape dough into rolls.
Place on greased baking pans.
Brush tops with melted fat or oil.
Cover with cloth or wax paper.
Set in warm place for about 45 minutes.
Bake at 400°.

title: italian beef stew
directions: Slowly brown meat and onion in shortening.
Add remaining ingredients, except spaghetti.
Cover and simmer 1 1/2 hours. Serve over spaghetti.

title: homemade ice cream
directions: In a small bowl, put 1/2 cup milk and Knox gelatine (set aside).

title: fudge frosting
directions: Combine all ingredients in a heavy saucepan.
Bring to a boil. Cook 1 minute, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat and continue to beat until thickened to spreading consistency.
This is a great hot fudge sauce over ice cream when served hot.

title: popcorn balls
directions: Cook to soft ball.
Add 1 teaspoon vanilla when syrup is cooked.
Pour syrup over popcorn.
Roll into balls.

title: molasses sugar cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add all other ingredients and mix until well blended.
Using your hands, form dough into small balls about the size of walnuts.
Roll each ball into sugar and place on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Yields approximately 3 1/2 dozen.

title: potato salad(may be made 3 days ahead.)
directions: Put potatoes in a pot with cold water to cover.
Bring to a boil, reduce heat and boil gently 10 to 15 minutes until just tender when pierced.
Drain.
Meanwhile mix vinegar, sugar, mustard, salt, pepper and garlic in a large bowl.
Add sliced onion.
When potatoes are cool enough to handle, cut in 1/4-inch thick slices.
Add to dressing and turn gently with a rubber spatula to mix and coat.
Let stand at least 15 minutes for potatoes to absorb some dressing.
Mix mayonnaise and milk.
Pour over potatoes.
Toss gently to mix and coat.
Cover and refrigerate al least 2 hours or until chilled.
Sprinkle with parsley.
Yields 8 cups.

title: samoset's caesar salad
directions: Break up garlic and rub in bowl.
Paste anchovies, Worcestershire sauce, vinegar and lemon juice.
Add just egg yolk; mix.
Add mustard; mix again.
Add olive oil; blend at the same time.
Add romaine; toss.
Add croutons and Parmesan cheese; toss again.
Add fresh pepper to taste.

title: "paska" - ukrainian easter bread
directions: Beat egg yolks, vanilla and sugar well.
Pour in scalded milk and mix until thick.
When cooled off slightly, add flour, yeast and salt.
Mix 1/2 hour.
Add melted butter, beaten egg whites and raisins; mix until bubbles appear and the dough stops clinging.

title: snowball
directions: Mix jello with water, juice, sugar and salt until dissolved. Let set in refrigerator until shivery.
Mix with 1 cup Cool Whip. Break cake into pieces and alternate cake with jello mixture. Pour into mold or dish.
Let set overnight.
Unmold or leave in dish.
Cover with Cool Whip.
Sprinkle coconut over top, if desired.
(Large Tupperware mold is perfect.)

title: peanut butter pie(sugar-free)
directions: Whip cream cheese, peanut butter and 8 packets of Equal; set aside.
Whip whipping cream and 7 packets of Equal until very stiff.
Fold whipped cream into cream cheese mixture.
Fill crust and store in refrigerator.

title: chunky applesauce
directions: Combine all ingredients in heavy saucepan.
Cover and cook over medium-low heat until apples are tender, stirring occasionally, about 45 minutes.

title: chocolate dessert wraps
directions: Spread 2 tablespoons of peanut butter on each tortilla. Sprinkle 1/4 cup marshmallows and 2 tablespoons chocolate chips on half of each tortilla.
Roll up beginning with the topping side. Wrap each tortilla in heavy-duty foil; seal tightly.
Grill, covered, over low heat for 5 to 10 minutes or until heated through. Unwrap tortillas; place on dessert plates.
Serve with ice cream. Garnish with chocolate shavings if desired.
Yield:
4 servings.

title: healthy gelled pick-me-ups
directions: In a medium size bowl, sprinkle the gelatin over cold juice and allow to stand 1 minute.
Add hot juice and stir until gelatin is dissolved.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch pan and chill until set. Cut into squares or use cookie cutters to make fun shapes.

title: chicken pie
directions: Take chicken from bone and place in large baking dish.
Cover with eggs.
Mix chicken broth and soup together.
Pour over chicken.
Mix flour, salt, pepper and milk.
Pour over other ingredients.
Do not stir.
This makes the crust.
Dab butter over this for a richer crust.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: old-fashioned butter roll
directions: Mix enough milk with flour to make a medium stiff dough. Separate dough into 4-inch balls.
Roll each ball out as thin as possible.
When rolled out, place pats of butter across middle. Spoon sugar across butter.
Roll pastry to cover butter and sugar. Continue until each ball is made into roll.
Place rolls into a pan 3 inches deep.

title: peaches 'n cream
directions: Layer 1:
Beat together pudding, flour, milk, egg and margarine.
Spread in 8-inch square pan.

title: carrots au gratin
directions: Melt 2 tablespoons of margarine in small pan.
Remove from heat and mix in crumbs.
Set aside.
Melt 3 tablespoons in large pan.
Add onion and cook until tender.
Stir in flour, salt and pepper.
Remove from heat; add milk, gradually stirring until smooth.
Return to medium heat and cook until thickened, stirring constantly.
Add cheese; stir until blended.
Remove from heat. Stir in carrots and parsley.
Spread in an 8-inch square greased baking dish and sprinkle crumbs evenly over top.
Bake at 350° for about 20 minutes until heated and bubbly.
Remove from oven.
Let stand 5 minutes before serving.
Serves 8.

title: asparagus-pea casserole
directions: Heat peas and drain.
Add mushroom soup to the drained peas and heat.
Alternate the peas, water chestnuts and soup mixture with asparagus in casserole.
Combine butter and crackers. Sprinkle this over top of casserole.
Bake 15 minutes at 350°. Yield: 8 servings.

title: king ranch casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients except tortillas together.
Tear 5 tortillas into small pieces and cover the bottom of a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Layer with half the chicken mixture.
Repeat and bake for 30 to 35 minutes at 350°.

title: rhubarb torte
directions: Combine graham crackers, 2 tablespoons sugar and melted butter.
Reserve 2 tablespoons of this mixture and pat remainder in 9 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes and cool.

title: lima bean casserole
directions: Cook beans until done.
Add 2 tablespoons butter.
Combine all ingredients except crumbs.
Sprinkle crumbs evenly over mixture. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: chili-cheese dip
directions: Soften cream cheese; spread in 9 x 13-inch dish.
Pour chili over cream cheese.
Pour salsa over chili; top with shredded cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: crab canapes
directions: Mix cheese, crab, butter, mayonnaise and seasonings.
Spread on muffins.
Cut each into quarters and broil five minutes or until crisp.

title: instant pizzas
directions: Flatten each biscuit to 1/4-inch thickness.
Place on cookie sheet.
Spread each with tomato paste and top with desired topping.
Sprinkle with oregano and cheese.
Bake at 400° for 6 to 8 minutes or until lightly browned.

title: brownie pecan pie
directions: Combine sugar, salt and corn syrup in a small saucepan.
Bring to a boil over medium heat, stirring until sugar is dissolved; boil 2 minutes.
Remove from heat; add chocolate and butter.
Stir until chocolate is melted and mixture is smooth.
Cool.

title: luau ribs
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Place spareribs in 450° oven for 15 minutes.
Spoon off fat.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours continually basting with sauce.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: southern seafood gumbo
directions: Combine 1/2 cup oil and flour in a large Dutch oven; cook over medium heat, stirring constantly until roux is caramel colored, about 15 to 20 minutes.
Stir in celery, onion, green pepper and garlic.
Cook an additional 45 minutes, stirring occasionally. Fry okra in 1 tablespoon hot oil until browned. Add to gumbo; stir well over low heat for a few minutes.
At this stage, the mixture may be cooled, packaged and frozen or refrigerated for later use.
Add broth and next 8 ingredients; simmer 2 1/2 hours. Stir occasionally.
Add shrimp, chicken, crabmeat and oysters, if desired, during the last 10 minutes of simmering period.
Serve over hot rice.
Yield:
14 cups; 10 to 12 servings.

title: strawberry cake
directions: Put all ingredients in a mixing bowl and mix well.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: pumpkin cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together in order given.
Pour into well-greased tube pan; bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes, or until done.
Cool and frost with Cream Cheese Icing.

title: potato soup
directions: Saute onions and celery in butter.
Combine all ingredients in large pot (except milk). Cook until done.
Blend in blender.
Pour back in pot and add 1 cup Pet milk and heat.
Do not boil.

title: harvest corn relish
directions: Combine all vegetables, then add other ingredients.
Over a low heat, bring to the boiling point.
Allow to simmer for 25 minutes.
Seal at once in hot sterilized jars.

title: peanut corn chowder
directions: In hot butter in medium saucepan, saute celery and onion until tender.
Remove from heat.
Add peanut butter, stirring until melted.
Gradually stir in chicken broth, then corn.
Bring to boil, stirring constantly.
Reduce heat and simmer uncovered 10 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Remove from heat.
Stir in light cream; reheat gently.
Makes about 1 quart.

title: english cream scones
directions: Sift into mixing bowl, flour, sugar, salt and baking powder; work in butter.
In another bowl, add eggs (reserve a small amount of egg white for topping) and beat.
Add eggs to flour mixture with milk (you may add a little more milk to make the dough just firm enough to handle, but not soft).
Turn out onto a board and knead for about 1/4 minute.
Pat and roll into an oblong about 1/4-inch thick.
Cut in diamonds with a sharp knife.
Brush with water and sprinkle with sugar.
Bake at 450° for 15 minutes.

title: apple butter
directions: Run cooked apples through ricer.
Mix all ingredients together. Cook like you would jelly, until done.
Pack and seal in jars.

title: pumpkin pie(microwave)
directions: In large bowl, combine all ingredients (except shell) in order given.
Beat until well blended.
Pour mixture into pie shell. Microwave, uncovered, 4 minutes, until edges begin to set.
With a spoon, carefully pull the cooked portions to center of dish. Microwave, uncovered, an additional 6 to 8 minutes.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Turn pie plate one-half turn after 3 minutes and again pull cooked portion to center.
Pie is done when knife inserted is clean.
Cool.
Makes one 9-inch pie.

title: pickled peppers
directions: Heat 1/2 of the vinegar but don't bring to a boil.
Add sugar and dissolve.
Add peppers.
Add allspice and garlic.
Put in rest of vinegar.
Cook 10 minutes.
Pour in jars and seal.

title: tuna in pita pocket
directions: Combine tuna, carrot, apple and onion.
Combine mayonnaise and mustard; toss lightly with tuna mixture.
Cut pita bread in half. Open to form pocket.
Fill with tuna mixture.

title: best bran muffins
directions: Stir together flour, baking powder, salt and sugar and set aside.
Measure All-Bran and milk into large mixing bowl.
Stir to combine.
Let stand 1 or 2 minutes until softened.
Add egg and oil and beat well.
Add flour mixture, stirring only until combined.
Portion batter evenly into 12 greased 2 1/2-inch muffin pan cups.
Bake at 400° for 25 minutes or until lightly browned.

title: hungarian goulash
directions: Saute bacon in Dutch oven until crisp.
Remove with slotted spoon to bowl.
Saute onions in fat until transparent.
Remove to bowl with bacon.
Put peppers in bowl.
Saute meat in bacon fat (add oil if needed) to brown all meat.
Mix marjoram and paprika. Return meat to pan; sprinkle with seasonings.
Add vegetables. Make 1 to 1 1/2 quart of stock according to directions on bouillon.
Add and simmer until meat is tender (1 to 2 hours). Thicken with flour and water.
Serve over cooked noodles.

title: sweet and sour pork
directions: Brown pork in hot oil.
Add 1/4 cup water; cover and simmer for 1 hour or cook in oven until tender.
While pork is cooking, combine everything, except pepper, onion and pineapple.
Cook until thick, stirring constantly.
When pork is tender, pour over and let stand 10 minutes.
Add remaining ingredients and return to stove or oven for 2 to 3 minutes.
Serve over rice.

title: my favorite fruit bread
directions: Cream together butter and sugar.
Add eggs.
Add flour and soda.
Sift.
Stir into creamed mixture.
Add nutmeats, raisins and cocoa.
Add mashed bananas.
Vanilla or maple flavoring may be added; also a little coconut, if desired.
Pour into two greased bread tins and bake in a 350° oven until done, 45 minutes or so.

title: chocolate sheet cake
directions: Place the margarine, hot water and cocoa in a pan and heat until margarine is melted.
Then add the flour, sugar and soda. Mix well.
Add buttermilk, eggs and vanilla.
Mix well and pour into a greased and floured 15 x 10 x 2-inch pan (sheet cake). Bake at 350° for 17 to 20 minutes.

title: orange salad
directions: Mix dry Jell-O into Cool Whip and cottage cheese. Drain the pineapple and orange slices. Mix all of it together and refrigerate.

title: honey butter carrots
directions: Steam carrots until tender; drain off unnecessary juice. Preheat the carrots with remaining ingredients.
Makes 3 servings.

title: cashew chicken
directions: Cut chicken into 1-inch cubes. Brown chicken on both sides in 1 tablespoon oil. When chicken is thoroughly cooked, drain chicken and add chicken broth and carrots. Cover and cook for 5 minutes. Add broccoli and cook another 5 minutes.
Mix cornstarch with water, sugar and soy sauce.
Add to chicken mixture, stirring constantly, until mixture thickens.
Add cashews and heat just until nuts are warm.
Serve over cooked rice.

title: fabulous rolls
directions: Heat milk, butter, sugar and salt in saucepan until butter melts; remove from heat and let cool.
Dissolve yeast in warm water in the large bowl of an electric mixer.
When milk mixture is lukewarm (85°); beat into yeast.
Add 2 cups flour; beat at slow and then medium speed for 2 minutes.
Beat in eggs when well blended.
Slowly add flour, 1 cup, beating at low speed for 2 minutes.
Remove beaters and stir in 3/4 cup flour and beat with a wooden spoon.
Dough will not be stiff.
Pour into large oiled bowl; brush top with oil.
Cover with plastic and let dough rise until double, about 2 hours.
Punch down; divide into 4 equal parts.
Roll each piece into a circle 1/8-inch thick.

title: picnic pork-n-beans
directions: Mix all ingredients together and chill.
Better if made the night before or several hours ahead of time.

title: summer spaghetti sauce
directions: In a large skillet, brown ground beef over medium-high heat, then drain well.
Add remaining ingredients and simmer, covered, for 30 minutes.
Stir often.
Serve with your choice of pasta or steamed vegetables.
Serves 8.

title: sand tarts
directions: Cream the butter and sugar together.
Add flour, pecans and vanilla.
Shape into crescents and place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for about 20 minutes or until slightly brown. Roll in powdered sugar while still warm.

title: flank steak teriyaki barbecue
directions: Combine all ingredients but the flank steak.
Pour over the flank steak.
Marinate 4 hours or overnight.

title: cranberry jello salad
directions: Bring pineapple and juice to boil.
Dissolve Jell-O in pineapple with juice.
Add relish, cold water, nuts and options. Pour in 9 x 13-inch pan or mold.
Serves 15 to 20.
This is a firm salad.

title: okra soup
directions: Slice okra and celery crosswise.
Chop green pepper and onion. Brown in fat for approximately 5 minutes.
Put ham bone in a heavy pot and cover with water.
Add browned pepper and onion. Boil until meat separates from bone.
Cut tomatoes into quarters. Add all other ingredients.
Simmer approximately 1 hour.
Serves 5.

title: banana bread
directions: Mix together sugar, margarine and flavoring.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating
well
after
each.
Add mashed banana. Stir in dry ingredients.
Mix
well and pour into greased loaf pan. Spread batter toward
corners
of
pan,
leaving
middle hollowed out slightly.
Let stand 20 minutes. Bake at 350° for about 45 minutes. Cool before slicing to serve.

title: dump cake
directions: Pour the preceding into the bottom of the pan.
Pat down 1 box Duncan Hines yellow cake mix.
Add 1 1/2 sticks butter.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: chicken tettrazini
directions: Boil chicken and let cool.
Debone.
Cook spaghetti in chicken broth (may add hot water if needed).
Add both cans of soup and the chicken pieces.
Season with salt and pepper to taste.
Place in casserole dish and layer spaghetti mixture and cheese.
Bake at 350° until cheese bubbles.

title: bean dip
directions: Drain kidney beans and relish well.
Combine all ingredients and refrigerate for 1 hour.
Best if served with crackers.

title: poppy seed chicken
directions: Mix soup, sour cream, shredded chicken, chicken broth and salt and pepper.
Pour into 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Top with cracker mixture.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: chicken wilma
directions: Arrange 12 half slices of ham or Canadian bacon in shallow baking dish.
Place half breast of chicken on each slice and top with a half slice of bacon.
Put, uncovered, in 350° oven and bake for 30 minutes.
Meanwhile, mix sour cream and soup.
After chicken has baked for 30 minutes.
Pour soup and cream mixture over it and bake 30 minutes more.
Serve with rice.

title: grandma's chopped apple cake
directions: Cream margarine.
Add sugar and cream well.
Add eggs and beat for 1 minute.
Sift dry ingredients together.
Stir into creamed mixture, then add remaining ingredients.
Stir just to mix well. Pour into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan or 2 (8-inch) pans. Bake at 350° in oven for about 30 minutes or until done.

title: party ham sandwich
directions: Chop ham and cheese fine.

title: peach smash
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients in electric blender container; process until smooth.
Gradually add enough ice cubes to make 5 cups in blender; process until mixture is smooth and thickened. Serve immediately.
Yields 5 cups.

title: clam dip
directions: In one skillet, take juice of the lemon, mix with the clams and simmer 20 minutes.
In saucepan, simmer onion, margarine, garlic, oregano, parsley and the 2 peppers until onion is tender. Mix ingredients together and add bread crumbs.
Top with Cheddar cheese.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes, until bubbly.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Cook mixed vegetables as stated on package with onion and celery.
Remove from heat and add mayonnaise and soup.
Crumble crackers and mix with butter.
Pour vegetables into casserole dish.
Top with crackers.
Cook at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: instant miracle rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water and set aside.
Mix the flour, sugar and soda.
Cut in shortening.
Add buttermilk and yeast and mix.
Place desired amount of dough on floured surface; cut out rolls and let warm to room temperature.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: taco dip casserole
directions: Brown the hamburger.
Add the taco seasoning and make as directed on the package.
Layer in a 9 x 13-inch baking pan with the refried beans, sour cream, cream cheese, 1 1/2 cups Cheddar cheese, tomatoes, pepper, onion, chilies and black olives.
Top with the 1 cup shredded Cheddar cheese.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour.
Serve hot with the chips.

title: baked custard
directions: Pour egg in a medium bowl.
Add all other items and beat well. Rinse custard cups with cold water to prevent sticking.
Pour mixture into cups then place the cups in a shallow pan of water. Bake at 350° until a knife stuck in the center comes out clean about 45 minutes.
Makes 1 cup.

title: chicken with onion rice
directions: Combine rice and mushrooms with 2 1/2 cups water in a bowl. Pour into greased baking dish. Sprinkle soup mix over rice. Dot with margarine.
Arrange chicken pieces over top.
Cover and bake in a 350° oven for
1 1/2 hours.

title: peanut chocolate surprise
directions: Cream peanut butter, brown sugar and margarine.
Beat in eggs. Combine flour, baking powder and cinnamon; gradually add to peanut butter mixture until well blended.
Chill dough for 30 minutes.
Wrap 1 teaspoon of dough around 1 chocolate kiss and place on an ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Cool slightly and roll in 10x sugar a couple of times.

title: beef potato moussaka
directions: Brown beef and onion in a large saucepan.
Drain any grease. Add tomato sauce and seasonings.
Simmer about 30 minutes.

title: people peach cobbler
directions: Melt butter or margarine and pour in the bottom of deep baking dish.
In a separate bowl, mix together the flour, sugar, salt, milk, baking powder, cinnamon and nutmeg.
Beat until smooth. Pour batter into buttered baking dish.
Place peaches in middle of batter.
Pour lemon juice over peaches, not batter.
Bake at 400° for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: walnut cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together and bake at 350° about 1/2 hour.

title: poulet moutarde(don't be put off by the title; it's easy and delicious.)
directions: Marinate chicken in mustard overnight.
Dredge chicken in flour seasoned with salt and pepper.

title: cheese souffle
directions: Remove crusts from bread; butter and cut each slice into 6 pieces.
Cover bottom of 9 x 13-inch baking dish with half the bread squares, buttered side down.
Cover with half the cheese. Layer rest of bread, buttered side up; top with remaining cheese. Beat together remaining ingredients; pour over the bread. Refrigerate overnight.
Bring to room temperature and bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Serves 8.

title: coffee azuki gelatin
directions: Soften gelatine in cold coffee; set aside.
Combine hot coffee and condensed milk and mix.
Add gelatin and stir until dissolved. Add tsubushian and milk thoroughly.
Pour into 8 x 8-inch pan and refrigerate until firm.

title: whipping cream biscuits
directions: Preheat the oven to 425 degrees. Combine the flour and whipping cream.
Mix well. Turn onto a lightly floured surface. Knead gently about 6 times. Roll out and cut with a 2-inch biscuit cutter.
Dip each biscuit in melted butter.
Place on cookie sheet. Bake for about 10 to 15 minutes or until lightly browned. Makes about 10 biscuits.

title: texas sheet cake
directions: Bring 1 stick margarine, cooking oil, water and cocoa to a boil in pan.
Mix flour, sugar, baking soda and salt in large bowl.
Add all the hot mixture to flour and stir well.
Add eggs and mix.
Add buttermilk and vanilla and mix.
Bake on a greased cookie sheet for 15 to 20 minutes at 350°.

title: baked acorn squash with crisp onions
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
With a large knife quarter squash lengthwise.
Scoop out seeds.
Halve squash again lengthwise. Place skin side down in jelly roll pan.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Boil and debone chicken.
Chop into bite size pieces and set aside.
Saute onions, celery and green pepper in shortening.
Add chicken, tomatoes and chili powder; mix well.
Season with salt and pepper to taste.

title: orange salad supreme
directions: Mix gelatin and boiling water.
Let cool, then add all frozen orange juice, crushed pineapple and mandarin oranges.
Let congeal.

title: butter pecan cake
directions: Mix cake, add pecans and bake as directed on box.

title: fish salad
directions: Put all seafood into a bowl.
Chop celery, onions, green pepper and roasted red peppers finely.
Put into same bowl; mix thoroughly with fish and all spices.
Add mayonnaise.
If 2 tablespoons is not enough, add until you have consistency you want.
Serve over crisp romaine lettuce.

title: raspberry pie
directions: Mix Eagle Brand milk and lemon juice.
Fold in jam and pecans.
Whip whipping cream and fold into above.
Pour into baked pie crust.
Chill.

title: shrimp creole
directions: Heat oil; stir in flour.
Add onions, celery, peppers and garlic; cook until soft.
Add tomatoes and tomato paste; mix well. Cook 5 minutes.
Add water, red and black pepper; simmer 1 hour. Add shrimp; cook 15 minutes.
Add parsley and scallions 5 minutes before serving.
Serve over rice.

title: three hole cake
directions: Sift dry ingredients and make 3 holes in it.
Put vanilla in one hole, vinegar in another and the shortening in the last one. Pour cold water over all and mix until smooth.
Bake in a 9 x 9-inch pan at 350° until a toothpick comes out clean when inserted.

title: stained glass fruit salad
directions: Layer in the order given and stir just before serving.
Soak bananas in pineapple juice.

title: faye's christmas party punch
directions: In large bowl, add water to the frozen juices as directed. Add pineapple and cranberry juice.
Mix well.
Chill or serve over ice.

title: cherry pie
directions: Thaw cherries completely in strainer set in bowl; reserve 3/4 cup cherry juice. Mix Equal, flour, cornstarch and nutmeg in small saucepan; stir in cherry juice. Heat to boiling over medium-high heat, stirring constantly; boil and stir 1 minute. Remove from heat and stir in cherries; stir in food color.

title: red velvet cake(pam's birthday cake)
directions: Cream sugar, Crisco, eggs, vanilla and food color.
Sift flour, salt and cocoa 3 times.
Add flour mixture and buttermilk to Crisco mix.
Bake cake at 350° until done.

title: fancy grahams
directions: Line jelly roll pan with foil.
Fill with graham crackers (whole).

title: spaghetti balls
directions: Soak 2 cups dry t.v.p. in 1 3/4 cups boiling water for 10 minutes.
Then add remainder of ingredients.
Mix. Mold into 1-inch diameter balls.
Press firmly.
Fry in oil until crispy.
Serve with spaghetti sauce on noodles.

title: border buttermilk
directions: Place all ingredients in a blender.
Fill with crushed ice, up to 3/4 full.
Blend until ice is mushy.
Pour into individual glasses and decorate each with a fresh pineapple spear garnish. Serve immediately.
Yield: 6 to 8 servings.

title: vegetable salad
directions: Drain all vegetables.
Add celery, onion, green pepper and pimientos.
Toss all together.
In saucepan heat sugar, vinegar and oil until sugar dissolves.
Cool.
Pour over vegetables and mix.
This will keep for several weeks in refrigerator and can also be put in freezer.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Cream shortening, sugar and eggs until light and fluffy.
Mix cocoa and food coloring.
Add to creamed mixture.
Add buttermilk alternately with sifted flour and salt.
Stir in vanilla.
Add soda to vinegar.
Blend into first mixture (do not beat).
For a 2 layer cake, grease and flour 2 (9-inch) pans and bake 30 minutes at 350°.
(This cake has an unusual texture.)

title: kahlua cake
directions: First Layer:
Mix cake mix, Kahlua, oil and eggs.
Pour in a 9 x 13-inch pan and bake for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: chuck wagon beans
directions: Brown ground beef.
Mix all ingredients together and simmer for 15 minutes.
We eat this like chili.

title: cheese salad
directions: Combine sugar, cornstarch, butter, eggs and lemon juice.
Cook over low heat until thick.
Pour over quartered marshmallows and cut up or grated cheese.
Stir and add pineapple.
Stir again. Refrigerate.

title: oatmeal cake
directions: Cream sugar and shortening.
Add eggs one at a time beating after each addition.
Add oats, then dry ingredients. Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: vegetarian chili
directions: Soak TVP in hot vegetable broth for 10 minutes.
Saute chopped onion and TVP in 2 tablespoons of oil until onion begins to soften slightly.
Place in a large soup or stew pot to which the pinto beans, kidney beans (undrained), crushed stewed tomatoes, tomato sauce, chili powder and cumin have been added.
Simmer over low heat, stirring occasionally for 1 1/2 to 2 hours.

title: enchilada dip
directions: Brown ground beef; drain off excess grease.
Add the enchilada sauce and the cheese (cut into cubes).
Warm at low heat until cheese melts.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: stella d'oro cream puffs
directions: Cut anginettis in half.
Beat together, Cool Whip, powdered sugar, instant pudding and cream cheese.
Beat until smooth.
Fold pineapple into blended mixture.
Fill each puff with mixture to make little cream puffs.

title: debbie's "mock" champagne punch
directions: Make mold a day ahead from some of the juices.

title: fudge balls
directions: Melt chocolate chips in microwave.
Add remainder of ingredients.
Roll into balls and roll in powdered sugar.

title: peach parfait pie
directions: Dissolve jello in hot peach liquid in a 2-quart saucepan.
Add ice cream in pieces and stir until melted.
Add almond extract. Chill until thickened, but not set (about 30 minutes).
Fold in peaches.
Turn into pie shell and chill until firm.

title: chocolate intrigue cake
directions: Combine the flour, salt and baking powder.
Cream together the butter and sugar.
Add the eggs, one at a time.
Add the milk and vanilla.
Add the dry ingredients.
Pour 2/3 of the batter in a 10-inch tube pan.
Grease and flour bottom.
Add to remaining batter the chocolate syrup and soda.
Pour over white batter.
Do not mix.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: baked chicken with tarragon
directions: Mix sherry with melted butter.
Liberally brush over chicken; sprinkle spices over chicken.
Bake at 350° for approximately 30 to 45 minutes.

title: lillian's scalloped potatoes
directions: Mix potatoes and carrots, then the following ingredients, rotating vegetables, bacon and flour in a 4 1/2-quart casserole. Salt and pepper each layer of vegetables.
Last, add milk over top layer of bacon (about 1/2 up casserole).
Cover and bake at 375° for 2 hours.

title: smoked baked beans
directions: Cook bacon until done, but not crisp.
Drain and dice. Combine remaining ingredients and bacon, stirring well to blend. Pour into a 3-quart baking dish.
Bake at 325° for 60 minutes.

title: jalapeno bread
directions: In a large bowl, combine first 6 ingredients.
Make a well in the center. In a medium bowl, combine next 6 ingredients.
Pour into well of dry mixture. Add margarine and blend in.
Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes. Sprinkle with Cheddar cheese and bake 5 minutes more to melt cheese.
Serve with salsa or soup, if desired.

title: blueberry muffins
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Cut and chop in butter into dry ingredients.
Stir in egg and milk.
Mix in blueberries.
Pour in muffin pans and bake at 400° for 15 minutes.

title: mississippi mud pie
directions: Mix and mold first 3 ingredients into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.
Let cool.
Mix and beat the next 3 ingredients until creamy.
Put in cooled crust.
Mix pudding and milk.
Pour on second layer.
Use remainder of Cool Whip to top layer and refrigerate for 2 hours.

title: jeffrey's favorite peanut butter candy
directions: Cook the first 3 ingredients until mixture forms a soft ball in cold water.
Add the peanut butter, vanilla and butter; beat until hard.
Put on serving dish.
Refrigerate.

title: half moon cookies
directions: Measure and sift together the flour, baking powder, baking soda and salt.
Work with spoon until soft the shortening and sugar.
Beat until light and fluffy.
Then add the eggs and vanilla.
Beat until well blended.
Add sifted dry ingredients alternately with cup of sour milk.
Mix well.
Drop by tablespoon on a lightly greased cookie sheet.
Bake in a moderate 325° to 350° oven for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: corn pudding
directions: Butter a 1 1/2-quart baking dish.
Mix eggs and corn.
Combine flour, sugar, salt and pepper. Stir into corn.
Stir butter and cream into corn; mix thoroughly.
Pour into prepared dish and place in a large pan of hot water. Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: crock-pot stroganoff
directions: Cut steak in strips.
Put all ingredients but sour cream into crock-pot.
Cook 6 hours on high or 10 hours on low.
